comment: (intermediateGoals AGT CYCFORMULA1 CYCFORMULA2) means agent has CYCFORMULA1 as one of her goals, but for the sake of achieving her goal CYCFORMULA2. This doesn't preclude AGT from having CYCFORMULA1 as an intermediate goal for some further goal also or also as a final goal.
label: Intermediate Goals
intermediateGoals

comment: (ebmtlNLToCycLExpressionFromStringFragment STRING SUBSTRING-SET QUOTE) means that the CycLExpression QUOTE is an acceptable parse target for the combination of string fragments SUBSTRING-SET appearing in STRING, in the context of Cyc example-based machine translation to logic system.
label: Ebmtl NL To Cyc L Expression From String Fragment
ebmtlNLToCycLExpressionFromStringFragment

comment: (termExpansionExpected TERM) indicates that assertions using TERM should be expanded into any and all possible component meanings. For example, (isa HafezAlAssad (SubcollectionOfWithRelationFromFn Person president Syria)) would be 'expanded' into (president Syria HafezAlAssad). Typically, this expansion will happen via rules in the KB, but it could just as easily be a directive that the inference engine takes into account when determine how to perform inference over assertions using these terms.
label: Term Expansion Expected
termExpansionExpected

comment: Where FORMULA is a CycL formula with a single open variable, (evidenceForPlayingRole CANDIDATE-AGENT CANDIDATE-SIT CANDIDATE ROLE FORMULA) means that the fact that CANDIDATE-AGENT is returned as (possibly one of several) bindings for the open variable in FORMULA constitutes weak or prima facia evidence for the claim that (ROLE CANDIDATE-SIT CANDIDATE-AGENT).
label: Evidence For Playing Role
evidenceForPlayingRole

comment: (performsActsOfTypeInLocation_Number AGENT ACTION-TYPE LOCATION NUM) holds just in case NUM of the instances of ACTION-TYPE that AGENT is known by Cyc to perform are performed in (eventOccursAt) location. For instance, if 34 of the instances of TerroristAttack that Hamas is known to perform are performed in Israel, then (performsActsOfTypeInLocation_Number #$TerroristOrganization-Hamas TerroristAttack Israel 34) holds.
label: Performs Acts Of Type In Location Number
performsActsOfTypeInLocation-Number

comment: (actsInCapacity_HobbyCapacity AGENT SLOT EVENT-TYPE) holds just in case AGENT's role in events of type EVENT-TYPE is that of engaging in that role as a hobby.
label: Acts In Capacity Hobby Capacity
actsInCapacity-HobbyCapacity

comment: A predicate used to describe the semantics of instances of Graph_CW. (graphRunDerivedFromRelationArg GRAPH PRED INT) means that the points along the xAxis on the graphical structure of GRAPH represent the values of the INTth argument place for PRED relations encoded in GRAPH.
label: Graph Run Derived From Relation Arg
graphRunDerivedFromRelationArg
subPropertyOf: Field Type Derived From Relation Arg

comment: (prevalenceOfPropertyInReferenceSet PROPERTY SET N) means that N elements of SET are known to have PROPERTY.
label: Prevalence Of Property In Reference Set
prevalenceOfPropertyInReferenceSet

comment: (textStringIsReferenceTypeInWork WORK TEXT REFTYPE) means that the TextString TEXT, which is a reference to something external to WORK (see referenceInWorkTo), has the function or purpose characterized by REFTYPE, a instance of TextStringTypeByReferenceType. For example, a TextString in a BookCopy that attributes a particular photograph reproduced in the BookCopy to an individual photographer would be an instance of AttributiveReference.
label: Text String Is Reference Type In Work
textStringIsReferenceTypeInWork

comment: An assertion of the form (proxyFor EVENT PROXY SOURCE) states that during the Event EVENT the IntelligentAgent PROXY acts on behalf of the IntelligentAgent SOURCE. For a related type-level predicate see usesProxyInEventsOfTypeWith.
label: Proxy For
proxyFor

comment: (increasesPropSlot_Subjective SENT THING SLOT) expresses the fact that, everything else being equal, if SENT is true (asserted) the value of the QuantitySlot SLOT (i.e. the arg2 to SLOT) to be attributed to THING is higher than some default or presupposed base value. The `everything else being equal' clause indicates that the value of SLOT for THING might change, even *de*crease, were more information to become available -- that is, the SLOT-value assignment to THING might change, even holding SENT true, if additional sentences were known to be true. This is the propositional version of increasesSitSlot_Subjective. See that predicate for more extensive documentation.
Mx4rwLSVCpwpEbGdrcN5Y29ycA: subjective increases in quantity slot due to proposition
label: subjective increase in quantity slot due to proposition
increasesPropSlot-Subjective

comment: (opinionOnIssue AGENT ISSUE OPINION) means that AGENT has the opinion PROP, where PROP is an opinion regarding ISSUE. A sentence stating an opinion about an issue typically mentions that issue, but not always. 'People have the right to bear arms' is an opinion about the issue of gun control. Containing a mention of an issue is not sufficient for a sentence to be an opinion about that issue, as in 'The issue of abortion is widely discussed.'
label: Opinion On Issue
opinionOnIssue

comment:
(closestEventOfTypePriorToWithValueFor EVT1 EVT2 TYPE PROPERTY) means that EVT1 is the nearest event of TYPE prior to EVT2 that has some value for PROPERTY. This entails that 
    (thereExists ?VALUE
       (PROPERTY EVT1 ?VALUE))
In medical contexts it is assumed that both events involve the same patient.
label: Closest Event Of Type Prior To With Value For CYC
closestEventOfTypePriorToWithValueFor-CYC

comment: (nthExpressionOfSession SESSION PEG N) means that the LinguisticExpressionPeg PEG is the Nth peg introduced in the #$MySentientSoftwareInteractionSession SESSION. In general, the numbering of pegs should reflect interaction precedence (i.e. pegs of more recent interactions should ordered higher), as well as ordering within user inputs.
label: Nth Expression Of Session
nthExpressionOfSession

comment: (nthWordInNLParagraph PARAGRAPH NUM STRING) holds just in case STRING is the NUMth word in PARAGRAPH. Hyphenated words or words connected by a slash are considered one word for purposes of counting.
label: Nth Word In NL Paragraph
nthWordInNLParagraph

comment: (documentsImprovement OBJ1 OBJ2 ASPECT EXP) says that the improvement in some ASPECT of OBJ1 over OBJ2 is described somehow by the expression EXP
label: Documents Improvement
documentsImprovement

comment: An assertion of the form (prevelanceOfConditionDuring PLACE ORG-TYPE CONDITION PERCENT DATE) states that measurements made of the population of the GeographicalRegion PLACE for the Date DATE indicate that PERCENT of the population were suffering from the PhysiologicalConditionType CONDITION. For example, an assertion of the form (prevelanceOfConditionDuring Syria HomoSapiens AIDS (Percent .05) (YearFn 2005) would state that records indicate that during 2005, .05% of the human population of Syria suffer from AIDS. This represents a measurement and estimate.
label: Prevelance Of Condition During
prevelanceOfConditionDuring

comment:
A predicate that relates an integer (representing an argument-position) and a CycL term to a CycL formula in which the term appears (in that position) and a second CycL formula in which has identical arguments to the first in every argument position save the one represented by the integer; substituteArgIn is a QuaternaryPredicate that relates an instance of NonNegativeInteger to an instance of CycLTerm and two instances of CycLFormula.

(substituteArgIn N TERM FORMULA-OLD FORMULA-NEW) means that TERM occurs as argument N within FORMULA-NEW and that otherwise FORMULA-OLD and FORMULA-NEW have identical arguments.
label: Substitute Arg In
substituteArgIn

comment: commandTemplate relates English sentences meant as commands to the Addressee to CycL.
label: command template
commandTemplate

comment: A predicate relating instances of InternetServicesDaemon with instances of ServerProgram and instances of Computer. (serverInitiatesServerProgramOn DAEMON SERVER COMPUTER) means that DAEMON listens for connections on certain internet sockets for requests to SERVER on COMPUTER. If DAEMON receives a requests, it starts a process of SERVER.
label: Server Initiates Server Program On
serverInitiatesServerProgramOn

comment: This predicate relates a human culture to types of practices that are distinctive of it though normally only participated in by a relatively small number of its participants. (cultureSpecialPractices CULTURE ACTTYPE ROLE) means that a specialized subcollection of the participants in CULTURE play ROLE in instances of ACTTYPE from time to time, and that most participants in CULTURE would consider such activities important to or distinctive of CULTURE itself. Examples include religious ceremonies and artistic endeavors that, while distinctive of a given culture, are only directly participated in by a fraction of its members. For a similar predicate that applies to characteristic practices that are participated in by most or many of a culture's participants, see culturePractices.
label: Culture Special Practices
cultureSpecialPractices

comment: (synonymousRelnArgs RELN SOURCE LIST) means that when it is known that (synonymousExternalConcept RELN SOURCE STRING) or (overlappingExternalConcept RELN SOURCE STRING) and STRING appears with an associated set of arguments in an output deriving from SOURCE, the appropriate argument order to observe on the corresponding Cyc relation RELN is given by LIST. For example suppose (synonymousExternalConcept ethnicity SRATemplateExtractionOntology 'NATIONALITY') and suppose NATIONALITY appears in an SRATemplateExtractionOntology mediated output with the arguments 'Sudanese' 'Abu Doha' in that order and , where additional mapping info tells us that 'Abu Doha' corresponds to AbuDoha and 'Sudanese' to EthnicGroupOfSudaneseArabs. (synonymousRelnArgs ethnicity SRATemplateExtractionOntology (TheList 2 1) means that AbuDoha (corresponding to the second argument associated with NATIONALITY) should appear as the first argument to ethnicity, and EthnicGroupOfSudaneseArabs (corresponding to the first argument shown with NATIONALITY) should appear as the second argument to ethnicity.
label: Synonymous Reln Args
synonymousRelnArgs

comment: (importCapacityDuring REGION PRODUCT-TYPE THING AMOUNT) means that the ScalarInterval AMOUNT is a measure of the greatest possible amount of instances of the ProductType PRODUCT-TYPE that could be imported by the GeographicalRegion REGION during the temporal extent of the TemporalThing THING. THING will often be a calendar time period; but it may also be, for instance, a particular Event. In the case of automobile imports, for example, AMOUNT might be an Integer indicating the number of cars that could be imported. In the case of oil imports, AMOUNT might be a Volume (a number of barrels) indicating the total quantity of oil that could be imported, or it might be an instance of MonetaryValue indicating the monetary value of all the oil that could be imported. Alternatively, AMOUNT might be a Rate, characterizing what would be the average rate of import of instances of PRODUCT-TYPE to REGION during the temporal extent of THING if REGION were importing PRODUCT-TYPE at the limit of its capacity. Oil imports, for example, might be expressed in terms of so many million barrels per day or in terms of so many dollars per day (again, indicating the monetary value of the oil).
label: Import Capacity During
importCapacityDuring

comment:
An ArgConstraintPredicate (q.v.) that can be used to put a cardinality-based constraint on a predicate with respect to a given argument-place. (argCardinality PRED N CARD) means that, for any particular way of fixing the other arguments to PRED besides the Nth, there are at most CARD distinct things such that, if any one of them is taken as the _Nth_ argument, PRED holds of those arguments. That is, there are at most CARD distinct sequences of the form <... ARGN(i) ...> that differ from one another only in their Nth members (their respective ARGN(i)) and are such that (PRED ... ARGN(i) ...) holds.

Note that CARD is simply the _maximum_ number of such sequences that there can be. There is no guarantee that there will be _at_least_ CARD such sequences; in any given case there might be fewer than CARD such sequences, and possibly none at all. On the other hand, there is a default assumption that the presence of an assertion of the form (argCardinality PRED N CARD) in the Knowledge Base indicates that the relation PRED is such that no number lower than CARD could correctly have been used instead. (Given that the above argument-cardinality assertion is true, (argCardinality PRED N CARD+1) is trivially true as well; the default assumption reflects the idea that it would nevertheless be misleading to assert the later.)

Most of the argument-cardinality sentences worth asserting are where CARD is 1, which entails that PRED is "strictly functional" in its Nth argument (see strictlyFunctionalInArgs). As an upper limit, CARD might be PlusInfinity, which amounts to an explicit denial that any finite cardinality restriction is correct for the argument-place in question, which amounts to no restriction at all; so such sentences are worth asserting to the KB only in cases where this lack of any cardinality restriction is likely to be surprising or unexpected, in order to document the fact that the question has already been considered and thereby reduce the potential for an unnecessary duplication of effort. As a lower limit, CARD might be 0, which entails that PRED holds of _no_ argument-sequence whatsoever; but it is unlikely that any such assertion should appear in the KB, since there would be little point to having such a predicate in the CycL language in the first place. See also interArgCardinality, assertedArgCardinality, and intraArgReln.
label: Arg Cardinality
argCardinality

comment: (authorListStringStartingWithNthAuthor WORK STYLE-SPECIFICATION MARKUP-LANGUAGE N STRING) means that STRING is the canonical representation of the author list for WORK according to STYLE-SPECIFICATION, for rendering using MARKUP-LANGUAGE, starting with the author at position N in the canonical list of authors for WORK.
label: Author List String Starting With Nth Author
authorListStringStartingWithNthAuthor

comment: (cblTaskFromHumanCyclist ASSIGNED-TASK PARAMETER-VALUES-LIST HUMAN-CYCLIST) means that the HUMAN-CYCLIST has assigned the ASSIGNED-TASK to Cyc via the CycBehaviorEngine with the given PARAMETER-VALUES-LIST.
label: Cbl Task From Human Cyclist
cblTaskFromHumanCyclist

comment: This predicate is similar to explicitRelationshipPredicateList, as it uniquely identifies a RelationshipDefiningSchema, however in this case the schema is only 'implicit' as a relationship between some ObjectDefiningSchema, ODS and one or more of its logical fields that references some other ObjectDefiningSchema, OTHER-ODS in one of ODS's meaning sentences. In this case, we record the meaning sentence predicate that participates in the relationship, together with a list of the object defining schemas and logical fields that participate in the relationship, where the order of the list reflects the order in which they appear as arguments to the meaning sentence template. That is, (implicitRelationshipPredicateList IMPLICIT-RDS PREDICATE LIST) means that IMPLICIT-RDS is the RelationshipDefiningSchema that is implicitly defined by some meaning sentence of ODS and LIST is the list of the object defining schemas and logical fields corresponding to the arguments of the meaning sentence.
label: Implicit Relationship Predicate List
implicitRelationshipPredicateList

comment: If FUNCTION is a PhysicalQuantityFunction, EVENT is a PhysicalEvent, and THING is an actor in EVENT, then (maximumValueOfFunctionForThingThroughoutEvent FUNCTION THING EVENT MAXIMUM) means that the maximum value of (FUNCTION THING TIME) where TIME ranges over all TimePoints subsumed by EVENT.
label: Maximum Value Of Function For Thing Throughout Event
maximumValueOfFunctionForThingThroughoutEvent

comment: This expresses the percentage of HMO clients who are employees of a certain employer.
label: Percent Of Clients With Employer
percentOfClientsWithEmployer

comment: (stateOfPortalInSituation SIT PORTAL STATE) means that during the Situation SIT the Portal DEV is in the #PortalTypeByState STATE.
label: State Of Portal In Situation
stateOfPortalInSituation

comment: This predicate relates roles according to nearness conventions associated with an event type. (nearnessForRolesInEventType ROLE1 ROLE2 EVENTTYPE MAX-DISTANCE) means that things playing ROLE1 and ROLE2 respectively in an instance of EVENTTYPE are considered near each other according to the conventions for EVENTTYPE if the distance between them is less than or equal to MAX-DISTANCE. See nearForRolesInEventType to express the fact that two objects are actually near each other according to the conventions articulated in this predicate. Other nearness predicates include near, nearRelativeTo and nearToDegree.
label: Nearness For Roles In Event Type
nearnessForRolesInEventType

comment: (receivesTreatmentTypeForType ORG TREAT-TYPE AIL-TYPE) means that the instance of Organism_Whole ORG receives a MedicalTreatmentEvent of type TREAT-TYPE for an instance of AilmentCondition of type AIL-TYPE.
label: Receives Treatment Type For Type
receivesTreatmentTypeForType

comment: (incorrectlyParsedSentence SENTENCE) means that a reviewer who looked at the CycLPropositionalSentence SENTENCE felt that the information the sentence expresses is incorrectly parsed from a text source or a text sentence. For example, (objectFoundInLocation #$KuKluxKlan BillingsMustangs_BaseballTeam) is an incorrect parse of 'Ku Klux Klan was located in Billings'. Whether the sentence is correctly/incorrectly parsed depends on a reviewer's subjective judgement, the context within which the claim is being made, and what other information is available to the system. Also see correctlyParsedSentence.
label: Incorrectly Parsed Sentence
incorrectlyParsedSentence

comment: A predicate relating instances of Firewall_Network with instances of Computer in the firewall's network. (unfilteredPorts FIREWALL PROTOCOL NUM COMPUTER) means that FIREWALL lets through all packets that conform to PROTOCOL coming from outside the network bound for port number NUMBER on COMPUTER.
label: Unfiltered Ports
unfilteredPorts

comment:
A ternary RelativeLocationalPredicate that relates a PartiallyTangible to a Direction to a PartiallyTangible that is part of the first. (partFarthestInDirection OBJ DIR PART) means that PART is the (possibly discontinuous) part of OBJ that is located farther in direction DIR than any part of OBJ that is not part of PART.

For example, if Tom (who has exceptionally big feet) is standing up and facing East with his arms akimbo, we might have: 

(partFarthestInDirection Tom Up_Directly TopOfTomsHead)
(partFarthestInDirection Tom Down_Directly SolesOfTomsFeet)
(partFarthestInDirection Tom East_Directly TipsOfTomsToes)
(partFarthestInDirection Tom South_Directly TomsRightElbow)
.
label: Part Farthest In Direction
partFarthestInDirection

comment: (ratificationEventOfAgreementByAgent AGENT AGREEMENT EVENT) means that AGREEMENT is ratified by AGENT during EVENT.
label: ratification
ratificationEventOfAgreementByAgent

comment: (playsRoleInActionTypeRegularly THING SITTYPE ROLE) means that the TemporalThing THING takes part in Situations of type SITTYPE in the role ROLE multiple times, and there is a fairly predictable temporal interval between such occurrences. If the frequency is known and/or relevant, the more specific predicate frequencyOfActionType can be used.
label: Plays Role In Action Type Regularly
playsRoleInActionTypeRegularly

comment: (posesGreaterVulnerabilityTo_Object OBJ TARGET1 TARGET2 HARM-TYPE) means that, all other things being equal, OBJ poses a greater potential harm of HARM-TYPE to TARGET1 than to TARGET2. By implication this means that TARGET1 is at least vulnerable to OBJ (although TARGET2 may not be). This is one of several comparative vulnerability predicates. posesGreaterVulnerabilityTo_Object differs from makesMoreVulnerableThan_Object in that the former expresses a comparative difference in the things threatened (TARGET1 is more vulnerable than TARGET2), whereas the latter expresses a comparative difference in the threats. As a rule you should use posesGreaterVulnerabilityTo_Object when comparing how one object threatens two distinct targets; use makesMoreVulnerableThan_Object when comparing two threats to one object. See #$NoteAboutVulnerability for more on these distinctions.
label: Poses Greater Vulnerability To Object
posesGreaterVulnerabilityTo-Object

comment: (interestInVenture PARTNER VENTURE INTEREST) is true iff PARTNER is an instance of CommercialOrganization that is one of the partners in JointVentureActivity VENTURE and has INTEREST -- e.g. 15% -- interest in VENTURE.
label: Interest In Venture
interestInVenture

comment: An instance of InterArgFormatPredicate (q.v.). (interArgFormat1_4 PRED COL FORMAT) means that FORMAT is a Format (q.v.) requirement for the fourth argument-place of PRED when PRED's first argument is an instance of COL. That is, with respect to a sentence of the form (PRED ARG1 ARG2 ARG3 ARG4 ... ARGN) in which ARG1 is an instance of COL, PRED's arg4 position (i.e. the position occupied by the metavariable `ARG4' in the preceding sentence-form) is subject to FORMAT. See Format and its instances for further explanation.
label: Inter Arg Format 1 4
interArgFormat1-4

comment: A Predicate mapped in from the NWU Trafficability and Terrain Engine. (fastestRouteForVehicleType PATH VEHICLETYPE LOC1 LOC2) means that of the paths available, taking PATH will oridinarily be the fastest route for getting a vehicle of type VEHICLETYPE from LOC1 to LOC2.
label: Fastest Route For Vehicle Type
fastestRouteForVehicleType

comment: This is a type-constrained version of the primitive role inequivalence predicate, differentRolePlayers. (differentRolePlayersOfType SIT-TYPE SUBSIT-TYPE1 SUBSIT-TYPE2 ROLE1 ROLE2 ACTOR-TYPE) means that where SIT is an instance of SIT-TYPE, any actor of type ACTOR-TYPE that plays the role ROLE1 in an instance of SUBSIT-TYPE1 that is a subSituations of SIT is different from any actor of type ACTOR-TYPE that plays the role ROLE2 in an instance of SUBSIT-TYPE2 that is a subSituations of SIT.
label: Different Role Players Of Type
differentRolePlayersOfType

comment:
A ternary predicate that relates a BinaryPredicate to a Collection to a Set_Mathematical. (slotValueRangeWRTCollection PRED COL SET) means that SET is the set of all (and only those) things to which some instance of COL is related by PRED. That is, a thing OBJ is an element of SET if and only if there is at least one instance INST of COL such that (PRED INST OBJ) holds. For example, the value-range of cityInState for USCity is the set of US states.

See also slotInverseValueRangeWRTCollection.
label: Slot Value Range WRT Collection
slotValueRangeWRTCollection

comment: (supplyRateFromThrough PT1 COL PT2 PT3 RATE) means that the instance of PartiallyTangible PT1 is supplied with instances of the Collection COL from the instance of PartiallyTangible PT2 through the instance of PartiallyTangible PT3 (on their way from PT2 to PT1) at the Rate RATE. Like the predicate suppliedWith (q.v.), supplyRateFromThrough is very general. In various assertions PT1 might, for instance, be a Cell, a Person, a Business, or a GeographicalRegion; and likewise for PT2. And PT3 might, for example, be a Hose, a Railway, a GeographicalRegion, or a BloodVessel. The range of possible supplies is similarly broad.
label: Supply Rate From Through
supplyRateFromThrough

comment: (lastEventOfType EVENT EVENTTYPE ROLE ACTOR BEFORE) means that EVENT was the last time ACTOR filled the actor slot ROLE in an instance of event type EVENTTYPE. (Prior to BEFORE.) For example : 'The last time Liz sneezed was at 9 a.m.' (lastEventOfType LizSneezingAt9am Sneezing bodilyDoer Liz Now). Also, 'Before the 1992 summer Olympics, the last time a Bulgarian won an Olympic gold medal was in 1980.' (lastEventOfType OlympicEvent1980 OlympicCompetition winner Bulgaria SummerOlympicsOfTheYear1992).
label: Last Event Of Type
lastEventOfType

comment: The corresponding predicate for the function AllotmentForOfDuringFn.
label: Allotment For Of During
allotmentForOfDuring
Role In Sit Type Requires Pos
roleInSitTypeRequires-Pos

comment: (valueFromColumnInSKS SKS LFI NUM) means that the value of the logical field indexical for the row in question corresponds to the value in the cell of the NUMth column.
label: Value From Column In SKS
valueFromColumnInSKS

comment: An instance of RuleMacroPredicate, a type-level version of playsRoleWithFrequency. (typePlaysRoleWithFrequency TYPE SITTYPE ROLE FREQ) means that every instance of TYPE plays ROLE in instances of SITTYPE with the frequency FREQ.
label: Type Plays Role With Frequency
typePlaysRoleWithFrequency

comment: (documentsDifference OBJ1 OBJ2 ASPECT EXP) says that the difference in some ASPECT between OBJ1 and OBJ2 is described somehow by the expression EXP
label: Documents Difference
documentsDifference

comment: An assertion of the form (actFulfillsAssignmentForSubPeriod ACTION ASSIGNMENT INTERVAL) asserts that the instance of Action ACTION partially satisfies the #$RegularyRecurringAssignment ASSIGN by being the sort of action specified by ASSIGN and by being performed during the TimeInterval INTERVAL (where INTERVAL is an instance of the type of time interval to which ASSIGN bears the relation assignmentRepetitionPeriod (q.v.) and INTERVAL falls within the period of ASSIGN (assignmentPeriod (q.v.))).
label: Act Fulfills Assignment For Sub Period
actFulfillsAssignmentForSubPeriod

comment: An instance of RuleMacroPredicate. (opponentsInSitType AGT1 AGT2 TYPE) says that (situationTypeIsSuchThat TYPE (opponents AGT1 AGT2))). In other words, situations of type TYPE are typically such that the Agent_PartiallyTangibles AGT1 and AGT2 are opponents. TYPE need not be a spec of ConflictEvent; two units could be opponents in a CourseOfAction without directly engaging each other (see, #$coaOpponents).
label: opponent in situation type
opponentsInSitType
Backchain Required
backchainRequired
comment: (backchainRequired PREDICATE) means that rules that conclude PREDICATE must be used in order to prove literals involving PREDICATE. In other words, when performing inferences, all literals involving PREDICATE must be eliminated using rules since there won't be any other way to prove them. See also backchainEncouraged, backchainDiscouraged, and backchainForbidden.

label: Will Be (unary predicate)
willBe
comment: willBe is a ModalOperator, commonly referred to as a `future-tense operator'. For each #$ELSentence-Assertible PROP, (willBe PROP) means that it will be the case that PROP. For example, (willBe `Amy and Bob are friends') means that Amy and Bob will be friends. willBe has a dual operator: willAlwaysBe. Note that (willBe PROP) does not imply that (not PROP). Note also that willBe should be used only in instances of TemporalMicrotheory. Strictly speaking, (willBe PROP) is true in a temporal microtheory MT with time index t and time parameter p (two `dimensions' in the context space, see mtTimeIndex and mtTimeIndexWithParameter) iff PROP is true in a temporal microtheory MT' with time index t' > t and time parameter p', which has the same values of all other dimensions as MT. Here t > t' means (startsAfterEndingOf t' t). It is easy to verify that (willBe PROP) is true in a temporal microtheory MT with time index t and time parameter p iff it is true in every temporal microtheory MT' that has the same values of all dimensions except the time parameter (another way to put this is that time parameters doesn't matter when dealing with (willBe PROP)). (See other tense operators was, willAlwaysBe and hasAlwaysBeen, and metric tense predicates willBe_Metric and was_Metric etc.)
(medicationStopDaysPriorToEvent MED-TYPE EVENT INT) means that medication of type MED-TYPE ceased being administered INT days ago to the patient treated in EVENT.
label: Medication Stop Days Prior To Event
medicationStopDaysPriorToEvent

comment: (terrainRestrictionForUnitSpecialty REGION SPECIALTY OP LEVEL) means that REGION has TerrainTypeByTrafficabilityLevel LEVEL for a unit of any echelon level and of military specialty SPECIALTY undertaking military operation type OP.
label: Terrain Restriction For Unit Specialty
terrainRestrictionForUnitSpecialty

comment: (increasedChanceForRoleBecause AGENT EVTTYPE ROLE PROP) means that the chance of AGENT's playing the role ROLE in a situation of type EVTTYPE is increased because PROP is true in the reasoning domain.
label: Increased Chance For Role Because
increasedChanceForRoleBecause
Isit: Participants
isit:Participants
comment:
A variable arity predicate from the IKRIS scenario inner theory. This predicate is designed to translate assertions made with fluents and holds, occurs, etc. into ICL. The number of arguments it takes is determined by the orignal fluent predicate it was translated from plus one for the situation generated. For example a sentence in the native KANI KB like this: 
(holds (ownerOf Bob Car01) April_1_2006)
would be translated into ICL as 
 (thereExists ?S 
       (and 
        (isa ?S kani:ownerOf)
        (t:during ?S kani:April_1_2006)
        (isit:Participants ?S Bob Car01)))
This predicate has been recreated in CycL so we can convert sentences like the one above into proper CycL. For example there will be support to convert the above ICL sentence into the CycL that follows: 
  (thereExists ?S
        (and 
         (isa ?S OwningSomething)
         (ownerInSituation ?S Bob)
         (thingOwnedInSit ?S Car01)
         (temporallySubsumes (DayFn 1 (MonthFn April (YearFn 2006))) ?S)))
.

(changeAccountOnSystem AGENT ACCOUNT1 ACCOUNT2 SYSTEM) means that AGENT, who currently has access to ACCOUNT1, gains access to ACCOUNT2, where ACCOUNT1 and ACCOUNT2 are in the same AccountSystem SYSTEM. Usually this predicate is used to represent an escalation of privilege, e.g., when ACCOUNT1 is a user account and ACCOUNT2 isa root account. However, its use is not limited to this kind of case.
label: Change Account On System
changeAccountOnSystem
Multi Word String Speculative
multiWordString-Speculative
comment: (multiWordString_Speculative . ARGS) means that (multiWordString . ARGS) is believed to hold, but has not been verified by a native speaker or qualified linguist.

An instance of both FunctionalPredicate and QuaternaryPredicate. (incapacitatingConcentrationForOrganismType SUBSTANCE-TYPE PERCENTAGE ORGANISM CONCENTRATION) means that exposure to CONCENTRATION of SUBSTANCE-TYPE will incapacitate PERCENTAGE of ORGANISM-TYPE.
label: incapacitating concentration
incapacitatingConcentrationForOrganismType

comment: (defaultDefiningMtForBinaryPredicateOnType BIN-PRED COL MT) means that, by default, assertions asserting (BIN-PRED INS VALUE) where (isa INS COL) should go in MT.
label: Default Defining Mt For Binary Predicate On Type
defaultDefiningMtForBinaryPredicateOnType

comment: (numInhabitantsOfTypeInRegion PLACE TYPE INT) means that INT number of entities of TYPE reside in PLACE.
label: Num Inhabitants Of Type In Region
numInhabitantsOfTypeInRegion

comment: (exchangeRateDuring_Market UM1 UM2 THING NR) means that NR is the average market exchange rate of the UnitOfMoney UM1 for the UnitOfMoney UM2 during the temporal extent of the TemporalThing THING. (THING will often be a calendar time period.) That is, NR UM1's can be traded for 1 UM2, and conversely, in a market that is not controlled by the GeopoliticalEntity whose currency UM1 is. For example, the fact that during October of 1995 the market exchange rate between Liberian and United States dollars was 50 Liberian dollars for 1 US dollar can be expressed as (exchangeRateDuring_Market Dollar_Liberia Dollar_UnitedStates (MonthFn October (YearFn 1995)) 50). See also exchangeRateDuring_Official and exchangeRateDuring.
label: market exchange rate
exchangeRateDuring-Market

comment: An assertion of the form (argIsaInstanceOfType RELN N COLL) asserts that in any assertion using the relation RELN, the Nth argument slot must be filled by some instance of Thing that is an instance of one of the collections that is an instance of the Collection COLL; otherwise the assertion is not semantically well-formed. For example, the assertion (argIsaInstanceOfType solute 2 ExistingStuffType) asserts that anything that fills the second argument place in an assertion using the predicate solute must be an instance of one of the collections that is an instance of ExistingStuffType.
label: Arg Isa Instance Of Type
argIsaInstanceOfType

comment: (limitPriceOfStockTypeForAgent_Buy STOCK-TYPE AGENT VALUE) holds just in case the maximum price at which AGENT will buy shares of STOCK-TYPE is VALUE.
label: Limit Price Of Stock Type For Agent Buy
limitPriceOfStockTypeForAgent-Buy

comment: (suppressReplacementForPosition TEMPLATE POS SET-OR-COLLECTION) means that for formula template TEMPLATE, the replacement options generated for arg position POS of the formula should exclude any member of SET-OR-COLLECTION. It also means that (positionInFormulaTemplateIsReplaceable TEMPLATE POS). See also candidateReplacementForPosition.
label: Suppress Replacement For Position
suppressReplacementForPosition

comment: Any sale which is governed by the agreement ARG1 must have a sales value of at least ARG2, or else a service charge of ARG3 is added to the total cost.
label: Min Purchase Amount
minPurchaseAmount

comment: (portalConnectsRegions PORTAL HERE THERE) means that the regions HERE and THERE are connected via PORTAL, and that at least one of HERE and THERE contains PORTAL as a physical part.
label: Portal Connects Regions
portalConnectsRegions

comment: (reformulationPrecondition DIRECTION PRECONDITION RULE), asserted in the microtheory MT, means that the CycLReformulator may only use RULE in MT in the DIRECTION direction (reformulating the 'from' arg into the 'to' arg) if PRECONDITION holds. PRECONDITION must be a closed CycL query, which will be asked during reformulation, and either proven true or fail to be proven.
label: Reformulation Precondition
reformulationPrecondition

Mx4rv3W2hJwpEbGdrcN5Y29ycA: No Gen Quant Reln To From Type
comment: (interArgNotIsa1_2 PRED COL1 COL2) means that, when an instance of COL1 appears as the first argument to PRED, the second argument in that assertion is constrained not to be an instance of COL2 and vice versa.
label: Inter Arg Not Isa 1 2
interArgNotIsa1-2
subPropertyOf: No Gen Quant Reln To From Type

comment: (subworkIsNthOfType SUB-WORK WORK N TYPE) identifies SUB-WORK as the Nth sub-work of the conceptual work WORK of type TYPE. The value of N is determined by the structure of WORK (see correspondingAIS) and the conventions for interpreting such structures.
label: Subwork Is Nth Of Type
subworkIsNthOfType

comment: (copyFileFromTo AGENT FILE FROM_COMPUTER TO_COMPUTER) means that AGENT copies the ComputerFile_AIS from FROM_COMPUTER and creates a new copy on TO_COMPUTER. Note that (copyFileFromTo AGENT FILE FROM_COMPUTER TO_COMPUTER) may be accomplished in a number of ways: by calling the cp function, by cutting-and-pasting, etc.
label: Copy File From To
copyFileFromTo

comment: (infersParseTemplate RELATION) means that the usual requirement that a CycL relation have an assertion associating it with a natural language template (these are usually made in the form of assertTemplate_Reln RELATION ...) does not apply because a parse template on a genlPreds of RELATION should be used during parsing instead. Example: #$hasAttributes does not need a parse template assertion since all of the ways one would make the assertion (#$hasAttributes X Y) in NL apply equally to a genlPreds of #$hasAttributes, is_Underspecified. In these cases we want to parse to the general term and reason to the more specific level. For example, if we know that Y is an attribute, then we'll use (#$hasAttributes X Y) rather than (is_Underspecified X Y) in the final CycL. These assertions will be used in NL quality control to determine whether a relation is appropriately lexified.
label: Infers Parse Template
infersParseTemplate

comment: A ternary ArgFormatPredicate (q.v.) used to put Format (q.v.) constraints on a specified argument-place of a given predicate. (argFormat PRED N FORMAT) means that the Nth argument of PRED has the format FORMAT. See the reified instances of Format for further explanation. Note that there are binary predicates that mean essentially the same thing as argFormat, but are restricted to some particular argument-place: arg1Format, arg2Format, etc.
label: Arg Format
argFormat

comment: This predicate allows representations of the subcatFrames that a verb can alternate between. (alternationSubcatFrames ALTERNATION SUBCAT1 SUBCAT2) means that for VERB participating in ALTERNATION, given that the arguments remain the same, the verbSemTrans that has VERB and SUBCAT1 as an arg. and the verbSemTrans that has VERB and SUBCAT2 as an arg. are semantically equivalent.
label: Alternation Subcat Frames
alternationSubcatFrames
Constraint (metaknowledge predicate)
constraint
comment: (constraint RULE) labels a given RULE assertion as a constraint. Constraints are typically used to verify that a given logical expectation is already true, rather than to deduce (and then add) a new formula which would satisfy the expectation. In other words, if a rule (implies P(?X) Q(?X)) is labelled as a constraint, then when P(?X) is determined to be true, we verify that Q(?X) is already true rather than add a new argument for Q(?X) using the rule and P(?X) as justification.

(predicateLicensesSenseExtensionFromArgToArg PREDICATE N M) means that PREDICATE, an instance of SenseExtensionPredicate, licenses the extension of the sense of some word that denotes arguments appearing in its Nth place to arguments appearing in its Mth place. For example, 
(predicateLicensesSenseExtensionFromArgToArg woodTypeOfPlantType 2 1)
means that for WOOD-TYPE and PLANT-TYPE such that 
(woodTypeOfPlantType WOOD-TYPE PLANT-TYPE),
there is likely to be some word(s) that denotes PLANT-TYPE whose sense can be extended to also denote WOOD-TYPE. For example, there is a count-noun sense of the word "redwood" (see #$Redwood-TheWord) that denotes the tree (c.f., RedwoodTree); that the collection of such trees bears the woodTypeOfPlantType relation to the collection of samples of wood from such trees, licenses a mass-noun sense extension of "redwood" to denote that second collection.
label: Predicate Licenses Sense Extension From Arg To Arg
predicateLicensesSenseExtensionFromArgToArg

comment: A QuaternaryPredicate that relates an Agent_Generic to a quoted instance of CycLPropositionalSentence to a quoted instance of CycLPropositionalSentence to an Real0_1. (conditionalProbabilityForAgent AGT EVIDENCE HYPOTHESIS N) means that the (subjective) probability of HYPOTHESIS for AGT, given only the knowledge that EVIDENCE holds, is N.
label: Conditional Probability For Agent
conditionalProbabilityForAgent
Semantically Related Affixes
semanticallyRelatedAffixes
comment: (semanticallyRelatedAffixes AFFIX1 AFFIX2 ... AFFIXN) means that the LexicalAffixes (AFFIX1 AFFIX2 ... AFFIXN) are subtle semantic variants of one another but they all share the same affixString. The differences will generally be found in the derivationalAffixBasePOS, the derivationalAffixResultPOS, and the affixSemantics. Example: Ese_NounProducing_TheSuffix Ese_AdjectiveProducing_TheSuffix are so related.

An assertion of the form (fertilityRateInOfDuring PLACE TYPE N DATE) states that measurements made of the population of the type of Organism_Whole TYPE in the GeographicalRegion REGION for the period of DATE indicate that the average number of offspring for that population is N. For example, (fertilityRateInOfDuring Syria FemaleHuman 2.3 (YearFn 2000)) would state that records indicate that the women of Syria have an average of 2.3 children during 2005. This represents a measurement and estimate.
label: Fertility Rate In Of During
fertilityRateInOfDuring

comment: This is sort of a specialization of negativeVestedInterest. The agent ARG1 has a negative vested interest in the value of the slot ARG3 on the thing ARG2. For example, (hasNegativeInterestIn AmericanAirlines UnitedAirlines financialState) means that the corporate entity AmericanAirlines cares about (has a negative vested interest in) the financial health of UnitedAirlines. But AmericanAirlines probably doesn't care what color United paints their planes, etc.
label: Has Negative Interest In
hasNegativeInterestIn

comment:
A ternary MetaRelation that relates a given function and a sequence of arguments on which it is defined to the value the function has for those arguments. (valueOfFunctionForArgs FUNCTION ARGLIST VALUE) means that FUNCTION maps ARGLIST to VALUE. More precisely: when FUNCTION is applied to the (say) N items in ARGLIST (with the i-th item of ARGLIST serving as the i-th argument to FUNCTION, for 1 <= i <= N), it yields VALUE.

A necessary condition for the above is that ARGLIST is inDomainOf (q.v.) FUNCTION and VALUE is inRangeOf (q.v.) FUNCTION.
label: Value Of Function For Args
valueOfFunctionForArgs

comment: A ternary SpaceRegionPredicate. (collinearPoints POINT1 POINT2 POINT3) is true if and only if the Points POINT1, POINT2, and POINT3 all lie on a common Line_Straight.
label: Collinear Points
collinearPoints

comment: The predicate normativeSpecificationDescribesRoleForType is used for partially specifying the satisfaction conditions for an instance of NormativeSpecification Specifically, it assocates an instance of NormativeSpecification with a BinaryRolePredicate ROLE an a subcollection of SomethingExisting TYPE, to state that part of satisfying SPEC involves a situation in which an instance of TYPE fills ROLE. This predicate works in conjunction with normativeSpecificationDescribesSituationType. In short, given assertions of the form (normativeSpecificationDescribesSituationType SPEC SIT-TYPE) and (normativeSpecificationDescribesRoleForType SPEC ROLE TYPE), then the satisfaction of SPEC will involve an instance of SIT-TYPE, SIT, such that there is an instance of TYPE, THING, such that the assertion (ROLE SIT THING) is true. This predicate only provides a partial specification because any number of assertions using it or the predicate normativeSpecificationDescribesRoleForInd can be used with normativeSpecificationDescribesSituationType to represent what needs to be done to satisfy SPEC See also the predicates normativeSpecificationSatisfactionPredicate and completeSpecification for more information on constructing rules using these predicates.
label: Normative Specification Describes Role For Type
normativeSpecificationDescribesRoleForType

comment: overlapFraction(COLL SETEXP N) states that the fraction of the instances of collection COLL which are also elements of the set SETEXP is N. Thus, you can state things like 52% of people are female as (overlapFraction Person (#$FemalePerson allInstances) 0.52)
label: Overlap Fraction
overlapFraction

comment: (shortestTrafficableRouteToFor PATH OBJ AGT) means that PATH is the shortest trafficable route for AGT, between OBJ and AGT. For example, in the context of a COA if (shortestTrafficableRouteToFor I-35 AustinTexas TankUnit001) is true, then I-35 is the most direct route between TankUnit001 and AustinTexas, and I-35 is a trafficable route for TankUnit001.
label: shortest trafficable route
shortestTrafficableRouteToFor
Count Of Cyclists Assigned To Projects
countOfCyclistsAssignedToProjects

comment: (lifeExpectancyForGroupInRegion REGION GROUP YEARS) means that the average lifetime of a member of GROUP residing in REGION is YEARS.
label: Life Expectancy For Group In Region
lifeExpectancyForGroupInRegion

comment: (subcollectionOfWithRelationFromType SUPER-COL PREDICATE TYPE SUB-COL) means that SUB-COL is the collection of all instances INSTANCE of SUPER-COL for which there is some instance of TYPE, INS-TYPE such that (PREDICATE INS-TYPE INSTANCE) holds. See the function that corresponds to this predicate, SubcollectionOfWithRelationFromTypeFn.
label: Subcollection Of With Relation From Type
subcollectionOfWithRelationFromType

comment: An assertion of the form (allotmentReservesQuantityOfIndForInterval ALLOT QUANT INDIVIDUAL INTERVAL) states that the Allotment represents a reservation of the Quantity QUANT, that is a 'part' of the Individual INDIVIDUAL, during the TimeInterval INTERVAL. This predicate assumes that for any set of values for ALLOT, INDIVIDUAL, and INTERVAL, there can be at most one value of QUANT. Further, every individual assertion using this predicate in a given context is assumed to represent a different reservation. Therefore, for the same ALLOT and INDIVIDUAL, even if there are two assertions where the TimeInterval of one bears the relation temporalBoundsContain to the TimeInterval of the second assertion, then ALLOT is assumed to have reserved the sum of those two quantities. This is a core predicate for describing what an Allotment reserves. The amount that ALLOT reserves of INDIVIDUAL can also be represented using the allotmentReservesPercentageOfIndForInterval (q.v.).
label: Allotment Reserves Quantity Of Ind For Interval
allotmentReservesQuantityOfIndForInterval

comment: A predicate used to relate instances of Computer with instances of FileDirectory. (exportsDirectoryToComputer SERVER DIRECTORY CLIENT) means that SERVER allows CLIENT to mount DIRECTORY, which is located on SERVER. Thus the user of CLIENT can access to files and subdirectories of DIRECTORY. That is, SERVER and CLIENT participate in a file sharing system, which could be implemented by NFS, AFS, NTFS, etc.
label: Exports Directory To Computer
exportsDirectoryToComputer

comment: (genlsWRTSubSituations SPEC-TYPE SPEC-SUBTYPE1 GENL-TYPE GENL-SUBTYPE1) means that (genls SPEC-TYPE GENL-TYPE), SPEC-SUBTYPE1 is a scene of SPEC-TYPE, GENL-SUBTYPE1 is a scene of GENL-TYPE, and for any other SPEC-SUBTYPE and GENL-SUBTYPE where (genlsWRTSubSituations SPEC-TYPE SPEC-SUBTYPE GENL-TYPE GENL-SUBTYPE) holds, the quasi-temporal partial ordering in SPEC-TYPE of SPEC-SUBTYPE1 relative to SPEC-SUBTYPE is the partial ordering in GENL-TYPE of GENL-SUBTYPE1 relative to GENL-SUBTYPE, and the role-player identity constraints across GENL-SUBTYPE and GENL-SUBTYPE1 for GENL-TYPE apply to SPEC-SUBTYPE and SPEC-SUBTYPE for SPEC-TYPE.
label: Genls WRT Sub Situations
genlsWRTSubSituations

comment: (unknownTermForTemplatePosition TEMPLATE ARG-POS THING) means that, if ARG-POS in TEMPLATE is unknown, it may be substituted with THING. This is useful for allowing the user to assert a formula when it is perfectly reasonable for one of the positions in the formula to be unknown. THING may thus be a signal to the reformulator to manipulate the formula into the appropriate assertion.
label: Unknown Term For Template Position
unknownTermForTemplatePosition

comment: (readFileOfTypeOn AGENT FILE-TYPE COMP) means that AGENT reads a file of type FILE-TYPE found on the computer COMP.
label: Read File Of Type On
readFileOfTypeOn

comment: If (keRelationStrengthensViaArg_Inverse RELATION BINPRED ARGNUM) and (BINPRED STRONG WEAK), then (keStrengtheningSuggestion (RELATION ... WEAK ...) (RELATION ... STRONG ...)). In other words, (keRelationStrengthensViaArg_Inverse RELATION BINPRED ARGNUM) means that the binary predicate BINPRED can be used to weaken a sentence with arg0 RELATION (or used inversely to strengthen it) by replacement of the ARGNUMth argument. It is not a requirement that all potential replacement sentences be well-formed.
label: Ke Relation Strengthens Via Arg Inverse
keRelationStrengthensViaArg-Inverse

comment: (binPredBetweenRolePlayers SIT-TYPE SUBSIT-TYPE1 SUBSIT-TYPE2 ROLE1 ROLE2 BINPRED) means that any actor that plays ROLE1 in an instance of SUBSIT-TYPE1 that is a subSituations of an instance of SIT-TYPE is related to any actor that plays ROLE2 in an instance of SUBSIT-TYPE2 that is a subSituations of the same instance of SIT-TYPE by BIN-PRED.
label: Bin Pred Between Role Players
binPredBetweenRolePlayers

comment: This predicate expresses a template for the relationship between collections denoted by transitive verbs, prepositions with which they co-occur, and the semantic interpretation of the verb and particle preposition together.
label: Verb Prep Transitive Template
verbPrep-TransitiveTemplate

comment: (argIsaWRTDeterminationArgIsaMaxColls PRED N COLLECTION DET) means that relative to the InductiveLogicProgrammingDetermination DET, and the maximumly general set of collections that is a subset of the asserted arg constraints on the predicates in DET, values for the Nth argument of the Predicate PRED are constrained to instances of the Collection COLL.
label: Arg Isa WRT Determination Arg Isa Max Colls
argIsaWRTDeterminationArgIsaMaxColls

Mx4rvWEKXJwpEbGdrcN5Y29ycA: Market Demand Is Price Elastic WRT Change
comment: (marketDemandIsPriceInelasticWRTChange MARKET PRODUCT OLD-PRICE NEW-PRICE) means that given a change in MARKET's price of PRODUCT from OLD-PRICE to NEW-PRICE, there will be little to no change in demand; precisely speaking, theabsolute value of the elasticity of demand in response to this change is between 0 and 1. To represent this value, use marketPriceElasticityOfDemand.
label: Market Demand Is Price Inelastic WRT Change
marketDemandIsPriceInelasticWRTChange

comment: (positivelyCorrelatedWith ?SET ?DEP-PRED ?INDEP-PRED) means that the second arguments to ?DEP-PRED are positively correlated with those for ?INDEP-PRED, when elements of ?SET appear in the first argument position. In other words, given the range of bindings for DEP-VAL and INDEP-VAL in (and (elementOf X ?SET)(?DEP-PRED X DEP-VAL) (?INDEP-PRED X INDEP-VAL)), whenever INDEP-VAL is high for a particular X, DEP-VAL will also be high and whenever INDEP-VAL is low, DEP-VAL will be low. Note that negativelyCorrelatedWith and positivelyCorrelatedWith don't entail a particular directionality of the causal relationship between arg2 values for ?DEP-PRED and ?INDEP-PRED. It might go either direction, or there may be no direct causal link, with instead arg2 values for ?DEP-PRED and ?INDEP-PRED actually being independent but subject to some common causal mechanism.
label: positive correlation
positivelyCorrelatedWith

comment: (typicallyLikesRoleInActivity AGENT_TYPE ROLE EVENT_TYPE) means that a typical instance of AGENT_TYPE likes to play the role ROLE in events of EVENT_TYPE.
label: Typically Likes Role In Activity
typicallyLikesRoleInActivity

comment: ARG1 is a list of things (item1, item2, ...) which, taken together, satisfy the descriptions in the MT ARG3 of the roles listed in ARG2 (role1, role2, ...). For example, we might see (satisfiesDescription (Joe Jane) (TheHusband TheWife) HumanSocialLifeMt).
label: Satisfies Description
satisfiesDescription

comment:
An instance of KEFacilitationPredicate expressing the fact that the interval assigned as the value of a property for a given object is too indeterminate to be pragmatically relevant, in the sense of keRelevantPrecisionValueForSlotOnType.

Specifically, (keUselessPrecisionValueForSlotOnTerm BINPRED TERM INTERVAL) is true iff (i) TERM is an instance of TYPE, and (ii) (keRelevantPrecisionValueForSlotOnType BINPRED TYPE SIZE), and (iii) (greaterThan INTERVAL-SIZE SIZE), where (intervalSize INTERVAL INTERVAL-SIZE).
label: Ke Useless Precision Value For Slot On Term
keUselessPrecisionValueForSlotOnTerm

comment: A predicate relating an object to the space it would occupy if it shifted one entire footprint to the left or right. (#$lateralShiftRegion STHING DIRFN LAT-REGION) means that the GeographicalRegion LAT-REGION is adjacent to (FootprintOfObjectFn STHING) in the direction denoted by (DIRFN STHING), and has the same area as (FootprintOfObjectFn STHING). If STHING were to shift one footprint in that direction, it would occupy LAT-REGION.
label: Lateral Shift Footprint Region
lateralShiftFootprintRegion

comment: An assertion of the form (urlRankForStringWithEngine URL N STRING ENGINE) means that the UniformResourceLocator URL was the Nth result from a search using the SubLString STRING on the SearchEngine ENGINE. This is a temporally qualifiable relation.
label: Url Rank For String With Engine
urlRankForStringWithEngine

comment: (predicateIsComposedOfThroughArg2Positions COMP-PRED PRED-1 PRED-2) means that the binary predicate COMP-PRED is the composition of the binary predicates PRED-1 and PRED-2 such that if (predicateIsComposedOfThroughArg2Positions COMP-PRED PRED-1 PRED-2), then (COMP-PRED X Z) if and only if there is something, Y, such that (PRED-1 X Y) and (PRED-2 Z Y).
label: Predicate Is Composed Of Through Arg 2 Positions
predicateIsComposedOfThroughArg2Positions

comment: (verbSemTransPartial VERB NUM FRAME TRANS) means that part of the translation of word sense number NUM of VERB, appearing with subcategorization frame FRAME, is TRANS. verbSemTransPartial assertions are designed to facilitate the specification of the semantic translations templates for a series of related frames. For example, for the verb 'model', the 'on' prepositional phrases typically indicate what is being modelled, as in "But for Private Ryan, DreamWorks canceled a G.I. Joe action figure modeled on Hanks.". To avoid having to duplicate the information from the verbSemTrans assertion for the TransitiveNPFrame frame in that for the TransitivePPCompFrame-On frame, verbSemTransPartial can be used. For 'model', the verbSemTransPartial assertion for TransitiveFrameType would specify that the general interpretaiton for the transitive usage, such as (and (isa :ACTION (MakingFn Model_Artifact)) (performedBy :ACTION :SUBJECT) (outputsCreated :ACTION :OBJECT)), whereas the assertion for TransitivePPCompFrame-On, would just need to specify (similarTo :OBJECT :OBLIQUE-OBJECT).
label: Verb Sem Trans Partial
verbSemTransPartial

comment: (actsInCapacity_DeniedFunction AGENT SLOT EVENT-TYPE) holds just in case agent is not permitted to act in the way indicated by SLOT in events of EVENT-TYPE. For instance, if Bob is not permitted to be the buyer in instances of StockTrading, we can assert (actsInCapacity_DeniedFunction Bob buyer StockTrading) which means Bob is not allowed to buy stocks.
label: Acts In Capacity Denied Function
actsInCapacity-DeniedFunction

comment: (regularSuffix DPRED BPRED SUFFIX) means that a regular word form whose part of speech is DPRED can be derived from a word form whose part of speech is BPRED by adding the suffix SUFFIX.
label: Regular Suffix
regularSuffix

comment: (dateRangeForMedicationStop MED DATE1 DATE2) means that if MED is an instance of MedicationPrescribedOrTaken, then MED has as the min-Date DATE1 and max-Date DATE2 as the bounds of its MedicationStopTime.
label: Date Range For Medication Stop
dateRangeForMedicationStop

comment: This predicate is a specialization of physicalFieldTranslation which translates 'virtual' physical field values into 'literal' or 'virtual' physical field values. Here, a 'literal' physical field is one that is actually present in the underlying knowledge source, whereas a 'virtual' physical field is constructed in the mapping process. See also the dual relation physicalFieldDecoding.
label: Physical Field Encoding
physicalFieldEncoding

comment: (agentHasMotiveForAction_Ternary AGENT ACT MOTIVE) means that the IntelligentAgent AGENT has the motive MOTIVE to see that Action ACT occurrs. To say that AGENT has acted on MOTIVE so as to be the performer of ACT, use the more specific agentsActionHasMotive.
label: Agent Has Motive For Action Ternary
agentHasMotiveForAction-Ternary

comment: '(preConditionFor_Ternary SCRIPT SCENE1 SCENE2)' means that SCENE1 and SCENE2 are both scenes in the #$ScriptedEventType SCRIPT, and that SCENE1 is a precondition for SCENE2. This means both that SCENE1 comes before, and is a necessary condition for SCENE2. Cf. necConditionFor_Ternary.
label: Pre Condition For Ternary
preConditionFor-Ternary

comment:
(multiWordStringSenseExtension WORD SPEECH-PART-1 DENOTATION SPEECH-PART-2 EXTENSION LIST) means that the use the string picked out by LIST followed by the word WORD with speech part SPEECH-PART-2 to mean EXTENSION is an extension of the sense of the multiWordString associated with LIST and WORD -- in particular the sense with speech part SPEECH-PART-1 and denotation DENOTATION. For example, 
(multiWordStringSenseExtension 
#$Lion-TheWord CountNoun Chicken MassNoun (MeatFn SeaLion))
means that the use of "sea lion" as a mass noun to refer to sea lion meat is an extension of the count noun sense of "sea lion" meaning the SeaLion.
label: Multi Word String Sense Extension
multiWordStringSenseExtension

comment: (satisfiableExpression EXPRESSION) means that it is possible, at least in principle, to simultaneously meet all conditions represented by EXPRESSION, even if currently no bindings meeting all such conditions can be found.
label: Satisfiable Expression
satisfiableExpression

comment: (exchangeRateDuring UM1 UM2 THING NR) means that in some market or markets NR is the average exchange rate of the UnitOfMoney UM1 for the UnitOfMoney UM2 during the temporal extent of the TemporalThing THING. (THING will often be a calendar time period.) That is, NR UM1's can be traded for 1 UM2, and conversely. Thus two assertions of the form (exchangeRateDuring UM1 UM2 THING NR1) and (exchangeRateDuring UM1 UM2 THING NR2), where NR1 differs from NR2, can both be true if different exchange rates prevail in different markets. In particular, the official and the (financial) market exchange rates of a currency may not be the same. For example the official exchange rate of the Liberian currency during October of 1995 was 1 Liberian dollar for 1 United States dollar, but the market exchange rate for the same period was 50 Liberian dollars for 1 United States dollar. So it is the case both that (exchangeRateDuring Dollar_Liberia Dollar_UnitedStates (MonthFn October (YearFn 1995)) 1.0) and (exchangeRateDuring Dollar_Liberia Dollar_UnitedStates (MonthFn October (YearFn 1995)) 50). (It is desirable to use the more specific predicates exchangeRateDuring_Official and exchangeRateDuring_Market, when the information to be represented is precise enough to select for one of these predicates. However, vaguer information is still meaningful, and can be represented with this predicate.)
label: exchange rate
exchangeRateDuring
Use Reformulation Rule For Quantifier Processing
useReformulationRuleForQuantifierProcessing
comment: (useReformulationRuleForQuantifierProcessing RULE) indicates that RULE will be used by the QuantifierProcessingRLModule.

(numOfTypeTargetedInAttack ATTACK TYPE NUM) says that during ATTACK, NUM instances of TYPE are being targeted. For example, (numOfTypeTargetedInAttack TodaysAttackOnTelAviv IsraeliPerson 8), says that eight Israelis were targeted during today's attack on Tel Aviv. Note that arg3 allows a range of values.
label: Num Of Type Targeted In Attack
numOfTypeTargetedInAttack

comment: (relationExistsUniqueAll PRED COL1 COL2) means that, for every instance of COL2 (such as INS2), there is exactly one instance of COL1 (INS1) such that (PRED INS1 INS2) holds. This is the same as (relationExistsCountAll PRED COL1 COL2 1).
label: Relation Exists Unique All
relationExistsUniqueAll
Metric Comparison Types Via Function Definite
metricComparisonTypesViaFunction-Definite

comment: numericFluentGTOrET(OBJ F(X) G(X)) states that F(OBJ) >= G(OBJ)
label: Numeric Fluent GT Or ET
numericFluentGTOrET

comment: (programRunningOnComputerHasFault_ReportIndexed SOFT COMP FAULT REP) means that the software SOFT, as it is installed and configured on COMP, manifests the FAULT reported in the ComputerVulnerabilityReport_CW REP.
label: Program Running On Computer Has Fault Report Indexed
programRunningOnComputerHasFault-ReportIndexed
subPropertyOf: Software On Computer Has Fault Report Indexed

comment: A predicate used to state the midpoint between the "ask price" and the "bid price" market price of a single share of a company's Stock at a given time. (stockPrice_Mid STOCK PRICE DATE EXCHANGE) means that PRICE is the average of the stockPrice_Ask (q.v.) and the stockPrice_Bid (q.v.) for STOCK at DATE on EXCHANGE.
label: mid price
stockPrice-Mid

comment: (mtTimeIndexWithParameter MT INTERVAL PARA) means that the instance MT of TemporalMicrotheory has INTERVAL as its value of the dimension `time index' and PARA as `time parameter'. See also mtTimeIndex and mtTimeParameter.
label: Mt Time Index With Parameter
mtTimeIndexWithParameter

comment: (preventsFromPlayingRoleInType SIT OBJ ROLE SIT-TYPE) means that the occurance of the Situation SIT prevents OBJ from playing the role ROLE in any Situation of the type SIT-TYPE.
label: Prevents From Playing Role In Type
preventsFromPlayingRoleInType

comment: An assertion of the form (roleInScriptRequires_Neg SIT-TYPE ROLE QUERY) states that any instance of SomethingExisting cannot play ROLE, an instance of BinaryRolePredicate, in some instance of SIT-TYPE, a specialization of Situation, if the conditions represented via QUERY, some sub-collection of CycLQuerySpecification, and the InferenceSentenceParameter of the softwareParameterValueInSpecification associated with QUERY are true. In short, these are conditions which would prevent an individual from playing ROLE in an instance of SCRIPT.
label: Role In Script Requires Neg
roleInScriptRequires-Neg

comment: (suppliedWithFromExclusivelyThrough PT1 COL PT2 PT3) means that the instance of PartiallyTangible PT1 is supplied with instances of the Collection COL from the instance of PartiallyTangible PT2 through the instance of PartiallyTangible PT3 (on their way from PT2 to PT1), and that PT1 is supplied with instances of COL from PT2 only through PT3. Like the predicate suppliedWith (q.v.), suppliedWithFromExclusivelyThrough is very general. In various assertions PT1 might, for instance, be a Cell, a Person, a Business, or a GeographicalRegion; and likewise for PT2. And PT3 might, for example, be a Hose, a Railway, a GeographicalRegion, or a BloodVessel. The range of possible supplies is similarly broad.
label: Supplied With From Exclusively Through
suppliedWithFromExclusivelyThrough

comment: (consumerSurplusAtQuantityOfProductType MARKET PRODUCT-TYPE SURPLUS QUANTITY) identifies SURPLUS as the monetary value of purchasing QUANTITY of PRODUCT-TYPE in MARKET, above the actual price per instance of PRODUCT-TYPE in that market.
label: Consumer Surplus At Quantity Of Product Type
consumerSurplusAtQuantityOfProductType

comment: An instance of GeneralizedQuantifierRelation (q.v). (num_GenQuantRelnFrom RELN THING COL NUM) is true if for exactly NUM instances X of COL (RELN THING X) holds. For example, (num_GenQuantRelnFrom neighbors BillClinton #$AdultMalePerson 3) means there are exactly three adult males among Bill Clinton's neighbors. The third argument place of this of this predicate is constrained to instances of SetOrCollection -- the more specific relationInstanceExistsCount (the third argument place of which is constrained to instances of Collection) should be used instead of num_GenQuantRelnFrom whenever possible.
label: Num Gen Quant Reln From
num-GenQuantRelnFrom

comment: The functionCorrespondingPredicate_Canonical of ChangeInValueReturnedByFn. Where FN is a scalar-denoting function whose value on the admittedArgument ARG changes over time, (changeInValueReturnedBy FN ARG COMPARE COL) means that COL is the collection of all events such that the value given by (FN ARG) at (EndFn COL) has the relationship COMPARE to the value given by (FN ARG) at (StartFn COL).
label: Change In Value Returned By
changeInValueReturnedBy

comment: (syntacticNodeNthContributor MOTHER N NODE) means that NODE's proposedMeaning is contributing to the overall meaning of MOTHER. If MOTHER's syntacticNodeNthDaughter is a standard SyntacticNode, then that daughter is also the Nth contributor. However, SyntacticChoiceNodes don't have meanings in and of themselves, so their chosenOptionNode, if any, is MOTHER's Nth contributor instead.
label: Syntactic Node Nth Contributor
syntacticNodeNthContributor

comment: Asserting omitFromIKB of a constant ensures that it will not make it into the IKB. Note that asserting #$redo of a constant typically ensures that omitFromIKB will be asserted of a constant, because the following rule is asserted forward in the BaseKB : (implies (#$redo ?CYC-TERM ?STRING) (omitFromIKB ?CYC-TERM)).
label: Omit From IKB
omitFromIKB

comment: A predicate relating instances of SoftwareObject_Individual with ports on instances of Computer. (programOnPort PROGRAM PROTOCOL PORT COMPUTER) means that a copy of PROGRAM is currently listening for packets conforming to PROTOCOL on PORT on COMPUTER. (See NetworkPortNumber).
label: Program On Port
programOnPort

comment: The corresponding predicate of MarketSupplyInUnitsFn.
label: Market supply
marketQuantitySupplyInUnitsForPrice

comment: (importCapacity REGION PRODUCT-TYPE RATE) means that the Rate RATE is the greatest possible rate at which instances of the ProductType PRODUCT-TYPE could be imported by the GeographicalRegion REGION. Note that RATE may be expressed as a MonetaryRate, but also as rate of volume, mass or number depending on the type of product.
label: import capacity
importCapacity
Language Posted On UIA
languagePostedOnUIA
comment: (languagePostedOnUIA LANGUAGE) means that LANGUAGE is merely listed as a language option on the UIA login screen, regardless of whether it is supported.

(industrialGrowthRateDuring REGION INDUSTRY TIME RATE) means that the total value of goods and services produced by the Industry_Localized INDUSTRY within REGION grows at a rate of RATE per year. See also productionValueOfIndustryDuring.
label: Industrial Growth Rate During
industrialGrowthRateDuring

comment: (<font color="#ff0000">#$stopDateOfMostRecentOccOfTypeRelativeToOperation</font> OP TYPE DATE) means that there is an instance INST of TYPE that is situationally associated with the <font color="#ff0000">#$CCFEvent</font> OP, and which starts prior to OP, and that there is no other known instance of TYPE which is part of the same situational complex as OP and whose date (as given by <font color="#ff0000">#$minDateForEvent</font>)  is later than the date of INST, and that the stopping date of INST as given by <font color="#ff0000">#$minEventStopDate</font> is DATE.
label: Stop Date Of Most Recent Occ Of Type Prior To Operation
stopDateOfMostRecentOccOfTypePriorToOperation

comment: '(typeDegreeOfDifficulty AGT-TYPE ACT-TYPE DEGREE)' means that the type of agent AGT-TYPE typically has the degree of difficulty DEGREE doing actions of type ACT-TYPE.
label: Type Degree Of Difficulty
typeDegreeOfDifficulty
Not Assertible
notAssertible
comment:
A MetaPredicate for stating a certain restriction regarding the use of a given Predicate in assertions to the Cyc Knowledge Base. (notAssertible PRED) means that no ground atomic formula (or "GAF"; see CycLClosedAtomicSentence) whose initial (or "0th" argument-place) term denotes PRED can be asserted to the KB. In many cases, PRED will be an EvaluatablePredicate whose extent is (re)computed as necessary and never cached in the KB.

See also notAssertibleCollection, which constrains collections in a similar fashion.
(nounCompoundParsesUsingRule STRING CYCL RULE) means that CYCL is a possible meaning of STRING, interpreted as a noun compound licensed by RULE.
label: Noun Compound Parses Using Rule
nounCompoundParsesUsingRule

comment: (totalBudgetExpenditures ORG THING MONEY) means that MONEY is a measure of the amount of money spent by the Organization ORG during the temporal extent of the TemporalThing THING. ORG might, for example, be a Business, a LegalGovernmentOrganization, or a Country. THING will often be a calendar time period; but it may also be, for instance, a particular Event.
label: Total Budget Expenditures
totalBudgetExpenditures

comment: An assertion of the form (approximateAllottedQuantityForMonth ALLOTMENT QUANTITY MONTH) represents, in some cases only approximately, the amount of work time that is allotted for a particular Assignment_Specification during a particular CalendarMonth. In cases where the allotmentForInterval value of Allotment intersects several CalendarMonths, the calculation of QUANTITY assumes a uniform distribution of effort across that interval and multiplies the original quantity (as represented with the predicate allottedQuantityOfWorkTime) by the fraction of the duration of the original interval that is temporally assumed by the CalendarMonth MONTH. The rules supporting this predicate are not senstive to such things as week-ends and holidays. So, those factors can contribute to errors in some of the error in the calculations.
label: Approximate Allotted Quantity For Month
approximateAllottedQuantityForMonth

comment: The predicate corresponding to QuotientFn. (ratioOfTo NUM-1 NUM-2 NUM-3) holds just in case the ratio of NUM-1 to NUM-2 is NUM-3; that is, just in case (QuotientFn NUM-1 NUM-2) = NUM-3. For example, (ratioOfTo 1 2 0.5) is true because 1 divided by 2 is 0.5.
label: ratio between two numbers
ratioOfTo

comment: The collection of all things by how normal a thing is to a particular agent. (normalityForAgent OBJ COL AGT NORMALITY) means that for the observer AGT, OBJ has the 'normality level' NORMALITY for an element of collection COL. For example (normalityForAgent 'Piranha001' Fish Charles Exotic_Unusual) means that for Charles, the 'Piranha001' is an exotic fish. The COLL attribute is important here: 'Piranha001' could. be a perfectly normal piranha, yet still be an exotic fish. Normality is different from but related to frequency (e.g. frequencyOfActionType, Frequency). For example, a mechanic sees broken cars every day; such cars are common for the mechanic, but not for the general population. To assert the normality of a thing for a normal observer, see normalityOfThing.
label: Normality For Agent
normalityForAgent

comment: (forceElement_FromGIS MIL-AGT) means that MIL-AGENT is an instance of MilitaryAgent, according to some GeographicInformationSystem to which Cyc has access.
label: force element in the GIS
forceElement-FromGIS

comment: A FunctionalSlot that relates intelligent agents to the microtheories that contain the propositions they go on the record as endorsing. (contextOfAgentOnTheRecord AGENT CONTEXT TIME) means that CONTEXT is the context that contains all the propositions endorsed by AGENT on the record (and their closure) at TIME.
label: Context Of Agent On The Record
contextOfAgentOnTheRecord

comment: (commitsCrimesInLocation AGENT CRIME-TYPE LOCATION) means that AGENT is the perpetrator of crimes of CRIME-TYPE in LOCATION. For example, (commitsCrimesInLocation #$RevolutionaryArmedForcesOfColombia DrugTrafficking Colombia) means that the Revolutionary Armed Forces of Colombia engages in drug trafficking in Colombia.
label: crime committed in a location
commitsCrimesInLocation

comment: (businessGrossProfitForPeriod BUSINESS VALUE PERIOD) means that VALUE is amount BUSINESS made in sales less all costs directly attributable to those sales (e.g. costs for raw materials and manufacturing labor).
label: gross profit
businessGrossProfitForPeriod

comment: (nodesCut_SubSystem SYS SET SUB_SYS) means that SUB_SYS is the path system obtained by subtracting SET from SYS. This is the predicate corresponding to the function NodesCut_SubSystemFn; i.e., (nodesCut_SubSystem SYS SET (NodesCut_SubSystemFn SYS SET)) is true just in case (NodesCut_SubSystemFn SYS SET) a well-formed term.
label: Nodes Cut Sub System
nodesCut-SubSystem

comment: An instance of InterArgFormatPredicate (q.v.). (interArgFormat1_3 PRED COL FORMAT) means that FORMAT is a Format (q.v.) requirement for the third argument-place of PRED when PRED's first argument is an instance of COL. That is, with respect to a sentence of the form (PRED ARG1 ARG2 ARG3 ... ARGN) in which ARG1 is an instance of COL, PRED's arg2 position (i.e. the position occupied by the metavariable `ARG3' in the preceding sentence-form) is subject to FORMAT. See Format and its instances for further explanation.
label: Inter Arg Format 1 3
interArgFormat1-3

comment: This predicate relates cultures to other cultures that have influenced them, and to the areas in which this influence has occurred. (cultureInfluences CULTURE1 CULTURE2 THING) means that the character of CULTURE1 has been significantly influenced by that of CULTURE2 with respect to THING. THING might concern language, law, religion, agriculture, politics, arts and crafts, or anything else having to do with culture. The influence might have occurred strictly in the past, or might be ongoing.
label: Culture Influences
cultureInfluences

comment: This predicate gives the different parts of the phone number of the voice mail at a given location.
label: Voice Mail Number
voiceMailNumber

comment: An assertion of the form (notAbducibleWRTValueInArg PRED THING N) states that abductive inferences should not seek to posit hypothetical values for the other arguments of PRED when THING fills the PRED's Nth argument position. Abductive inferences sometimes involving hypothesizing the existence of states of affairs. Abductive inferences often seek to explain an assertion or set of assertions by hypothesizing the truth of other assertions. However, we wish to restrict the kinds of assertions which Cyc will hypothesize such that Cyc does not hypothesize new theoretical or conceptual knowledge, or even contingent states of affairs that are quite rigidly constructed in the actual world. Thus, the assertion (notAbducibleWRTValueInArg cityInState NewYork_State 1) would prevent the Cyc inference engine from hypothesizing the existence of unknown cities within the state of New York.
label: Not Abducible WRT Value In Arg
notAbducibleWRTValueInArg

comment: (ridiculousSentence SENTENCE) means that the content of CycLPropositionalSentence SENTENCE (which is usually the subject of a #$suggestedSentence assertion) is patently inappropriate, usually because of type or obvious disjointness checking that should have been performed. As an example, (isa #$Cynthia InferenceParameter) is ridiculous.
label: Ridiculous Sentence
ridiculousSentence

comment: (trademarkStringOf AGENT GOOD STRING) means that company or person AGENT (an Agent_PartiallyTangible) has a government-granted right to market product or service GOOD using as mark some physical embodiment of the string STRING.
label: Trademark String Of
trademarkStringOf

comment: The corresponding predicate of CourtCaseDecisionFn. (decision_CourtCase CASE DECISION) relatest the CourtCase CASE to the Proposition expressed by the decision rendered in the case.
label: Decision Court Case
decision-CourtCase

comment: (ownsDuring AGT OBJ TEMP-THING) states that AGT owns OBJ during the temporal extent of TEMP-THING.
label: Owns During
ownsDuring

comment: (durationUntilStormLandfallInFacility STORM FACILITY DURATION) means that STORM is due to hit FACILITY within DURATION according to the source associated with the microtheory in which the sentence is asserted. For instance, if the Patrick Airforce Base weather services state that the storm is due to hit the base in 72 hours, then this predicate holds of the storm, Patrick Airforce Base and (HoursDuration 72).
label: Duration Until Storm Landfall In Facility
durationUntilStormLandfallInFacility

comment: (prepositionalPhrasePresupposesWithRemainder PP DENOT SENTENCES UNPRESUPPOSED) means that if PP is predicated of DENOT, then PP presupposes all sentences in SENTENCES except for those in UNPRESUPPOSED.
label: Prepositional Phrase Presupposes With Remainder
prepositionalPhrasePresupposesWithRemainder

comment: (setOrCollectionIntersection2 INT SOC1 SOC2) means that INT is the intersection of SOC1 and SOC2. This is the predicate corresponding to SetOrCollectionIntersection2Fn (q.v.).
label: Set Or Collection Intersection 2
setOrCollectionIntersection2

comment: (laborForceDuring REGION THING NR) means that NR is average labor force of the GeographicalRegion REGION during the temporal extent of the TemporalThing THING, where the labor force of a region at point in time is the sum of the number of employed and unemployed persons in the region. THING will often be a calendar time period; but it may also be, for instance, a particular Event.
label: Labor Force During
laborForceDuring

comment: An InferenceRelatedBookkeepingPredicate (q.v.) that appears in system-generated assertions. skolem holds of all instances of SkolemFunction, and exists solely for internal bookkeeping purposes. The set of supports for a skolem assertion of the form (skolem FUNCTOR) is the set of defining assertions of FUNCTOR.
label: Skolem (bookkeeping predicate)
skolem

comment: (glossForFormulaTemplate TEMPLATE TOPIC POS STRING ORDER) means that, for TEMPLATE, when we are dealing with TOPIC, the gloss for the replaceable position POS is STRING, and it should be displayed in ORDER. If a particular template has more than one replaceable position, it will have more than one gloss. ORDER denotes the ranked order in which to display the glosses for that template. To specify a gloss for the entire template, see formulaTemplateGloss.
label: Gloss For Formula Template
glossForFormulaTemplate

comment: (subordinatingConjunctionSemTrans WORD INT FRAME TRANS) means that the TRANS is the translation template which can be used to relate the semantics of the matrix and subordinate clauses of a sentence for which WORD is used as a SubordinatingConjunction.
label: Subordinating Conjunction Sem Trans
subordinatingConjunctionSemTrans

comment:
A ternary RuleMacroPredicate that can be used to state that a given binary predicate stands in a certain relation to two collections. (relationAllOnly BINPRED COL1 COL2) means that for any instance INST1 of COL1, only instances of COL2, say INST2, are such that (BINPRED INST1 INST2) holds. It is equivalent to (and can thus be used in effect as shorthand for) the more complex form: 
(implies
  (and
    (isa ?INST1 COL1)
    (BINPRED ?INST1 ?INST2))
  (isa ?INST2 COL2)) .
So relationAllOnly (and its defining axiom; see expansion) enables this common type of rule to be stated more tersely.

For example, '(relationAllOnly eatsWillingly_Instance Herbivore PlantBLO)' means that every herbivore willingly eats only plants or parts thereof. See also relationOnlyAll and #$NoteAboutUseOfRuleMacroPredicates.
label: Relation All Only
relationAllOnly

comment: (tacticalTerrainTypeFromPosition TERRAIN-TYPE TACTIC-TYPE LOCATIONAL-PRED) means that instances of TERRAIN-TYPE can often act as a type of TACTIC-TYPE for objects holding a LOCATIONAL-PRED relation to them. For example, (tacticalTerrainTypeFromPosition Hill ObservationFacilitatingTerrain on_Physical) means that observation (in general) done by objects that are on_Physical instances of Hill will often be facilitated because they are on the hill. Similarly one might say (tacticalTerrainTypeFromPosition Hill ObservationLimitingTerrain near), meaning that observation (in general) done by objects that are near instances of Hill will often be limited because they are near the hill.
