means that the use of "chicken" as a mass noun to refer to chicken meat is an extension of the count noun sense of "chicken" meaning the bird.
label: Word Sense Extension
wordSenseExtension

comment: This predicate relates a customary path such as a street to two objects such that one is directly across the path from the other. (oppositeOnPath_Directly OBJ1 OBJ2 PATH) means that OBJ1 and OBJ2 are onPath_Alongside opposite sides of PATH, and the middle of OBJ1 is directly across PATH from some part of OBJ2. More precisely: a vertical plane passing through the volumetric center of OBJ1 and perpendicular to the vertical ''plane'' defined by the centerline of PATH (or, even more precisely, by the centerline of the segment of PATH that OBJ1 is related to by alongsidePathSegment) would pass through some point in OBJ2. Note that oppositeOnPath_Directly is _not_ commutativeInArgs with respect to its arg1 and arg2 positions, for if OBJ1 is narrower than OBJ2, it can happen that OBJ1 is directly opposite OBJ2 but not vice versa. For a generalization of this predicate that allows the objects to be less directly across the path from each other, see oppositeOnPath_Generally.
label: directly on opposite side of path
oppositeOnPath-Directly
subPropertyOf: somewhere on opposite side of path

comment: Let SLOT denote an QuantitySlot, SLOT-ARG1 denote the arg1Isa constraint on SLOT, SLOT-ARG2 denote the arg2Isa constraint on SLOT, and VALUE denote the instance of SLOT-ARG2 such that (SLOT PATH VALUE). Then (maximumTrafficableValue_PathConstraint PATH O-TYPE SLOT MAX) means that PATH is pathTrafficableForTransportVia transporters of type O-TYPE only if (greaterThanOrEqualTo MAX VALUE). See also the related predicates minimumTrafficableValue_PathConstraint, maximumTrafficableValue_TransporterConstraint, and minimumTrafficableValue_TransporterConstraint.
label: maximum trafficable value
maximumTrafficableValue-PathConstraint

comment: (mtDimensionValue MT DIM SFD-MT) means that the SingleFixedDimensionMicrotheory, SFD-MT, is the DIM slice of MT. Microtheorys can be factored into their different dimensions with mtDimensionValue relations. cf mtDimensionComplementValue.
label: Mt Dimension Value
mtDimensionValue

comment: (productionQuotaDuring PT PRODUCT-TYPE THING AMOUNT) means that the NonNegativeScalarInterval AMOUNT is a measure of the production quota of instances of the ProductType PRODUCT-TYPE for the instance of PartiallyTangible PT during the temporal extent of the TemporalThing THING. (Of course, the existence of production quotas is the exception rather than the rule.) PT will most commonly be a Country. THING will often be a calendar time period; but it may also be, for instance, a particular Event. For example, to express the fact that Algeria's 1997 crude oil production quota was 750,000 barrels per day, we can say (productionQuotaDuring Algeria Petroleum_CrudeOil (YearFn 1997) (BarrelsPerDay 750000)).
label: Production Quota During
productionQuotaDuring

comment: (typicallyRelnFrom PRED SET-OR-COL-2 SET-OR-COL-1) means that typically (i.e., most and some) elements EL-1 of SET-OR-COL-1 are such that (PRED SET-OR-COL-2 EL-1).
label: Typically Reln From
typicallyRelnFrom

comment: (behaviorIncapable_CapabilityCompromised OBJ SITTYPE ROLE ROOT) means that OBJ is incapable of playing ROLE in any instance of SITTYPE, as a consequence of malfunctioning or being a defective instance of its type due to the further malfunctioning of ROOT, which provides critical sub-functionality for OBJ. Thus, (behaviorIncapable_CapabilityCompromised EddieTheAdultEagle Flying_FlappingWings doneBy EddiesLeftWing) means that EddieTheAdultEagle is incapable of flying due to some particular thing being wrong with Eddie's left wing, whereas it is generally true that ((TypeCapableFn behaviorCapable) Eagle Flying_FlappingWings doneBy) . Cf. behaviorIncapable and functionalityCompromised.
label: Behavior Incapable Capability Compromised With Root
behaviorIncapable-CapabilityCompromised-WithRoot

comment:
A ternary predicate that is an instance of AbductionConstraintConstant (q.v.) and that can apply to a predicate and a specified value for a specified argument-place.

(nonAbducibleWithValueInArg PRED VALUE N) means that, if asked a query of the form (PRED ... VALUE ...), where VALUE appears in the Nth argument-position and all of the other positions (>= 1) are filled with variables, the Inference Engine cannot use abduction to hypothesize that any non-abduced terms are legitimate bindings for those variables.

For example, (nonAbducibleWithValueInArg hasMembers InternationalMonetaryFund 1) holds, so Cyc cannot use abduction to hypothesize that Sealand is a member of the IMF. (Note that this does not mean that Cyc cannot prove that some abduced term is a member of the IMF.)
label: Non Abducible With Value In Arg
nonAbducibleWithValueInArg

comment: (rectangleTypeOfExtensionParameters DIST1 DIST2 REC) means that REC is the collection of all and only Rectangles (q.v.) that have two sides of length DIST1 and two sides of length DIST2.
label: Rectangle Type Of Extension Parameters
rectangleTypeOfExtensionParameters

comment: (rankOfFluentValue OBJ COLL F(X) N) states that OBJ has the Nth largest value for F(X) among objects in the collection COLL. For example, (rankOfFluentValue Texas_State State_UnitedStates areaOfRegion 2) states that of the US states, Texas has the 2nd largest area.
label: Rank Of Fluent Value
rankOfFluentValue

comment: (comparableRanks RANK1 ORGTYPE1 RANK2 ORGTYPE2) means that RANK1 inthe rank hierarchy of ORGTYPE1 is parallel with or comparable to RANK2 in ORGTYPE2, to the extent that whatever RANK1 authorizes a holder of that rank to do in ORGTYPE1, RANK2 authorizes a holder of that rank to do in ORGTYPE2. Note that ORGTYPE1 and ORGTYPE2 must be instances of MilitaryOrgTypeByGeoAndBOS.
label: Comparable Ranks
comparableRanks
Unlocked Situation
unlockedSituation
comment: (unlockedSituation LOCK) means that the Lock LOCK is unlocked.

(many_GenQuantRelnToType RELN COL1 COL2) means that for many instances X of COL1 there is an instance INST of COL2 such that (RELN X INST) holds. "Many" in this sense need not mean "many relative to the total number of the instances of COL1 that exist".
label: Many Gen Quant Reln To Type
many-GenQuantRelnToType

comment: This predicate is the predicateUnion of schemaIntegrationTypeForInputExplicitRDSSet and schemaIntegrationTypeForInputImplicitRDSSet.
label: Schema Integration Type For Input RDS Set
schemaIntegrationTypeForInputRDSSet

comment:
This predicate is the analogue of schemaIntegrationTypeForTargetODS, however it relates a schema integration to a predicate and the relationship defining schema relating target object defining schemas using the predicate. That is, (schemaIntegrationPredicateForTargetExplicitRDS INTEGRATION PREDICATE TARGET-RDS) means that:

1. TARGET-RDS is a RelationshipDefiningSchema that states a relationship between two or more target object defining schemas in INTEGRATION;

2. PREDICATE is the CycL predicate that states the relationship between the object defining schemas participating in the relationship.
label: Schema Integration Predicate For Target Explicit RDS
schemaIntegrationPredicateForTargetExplicitRDS
Infelicitous Query Sentence
infelicitousQuerySentence
comment: (infelicitousQuerySentence SENTENCE) means that SENTENCE is an inappropriate form question for the CycSalientDescriptor to ask. See also uninterestingQueryForRelnWithTypeInArg.

label: Exempt From CR Forward Rules
exemptFromCRForwardRules
comment: (exemptFromCRForwardRules TERM) states that TERM should not trigger in candidateReplacement forward rules.

A sentence of the form (evaluationOfAs EVAL HYP-SENTENCE EVALUATION) states that during the Evaluating EVAL, the sentence represented by the HypotheticalContext HYP-SENTENCE was categorized as an instance of EVALUATION, which is some collection that is an instance of SentenceEvaluationOutput, a second order collection whose instances are collections of sentences that share a common evaluation.
label: Evaluation Of As
evaluationOfAs
Literal Has Variable In Arg
literalHasVariableInArg
comment: An assertion of the form (literalHasVariableInArg LIT VAR N) states that the (CycLObjectTypeFn CycLAtomicSentence) LIT has the CycLVariable VAR as the value of its Nth argument.
The agent ARG1 is accompanied by the agent ARG2 in the event ARG3.
label: accompaniment
accompaniedBy

comment: (sitResultsInProp FORMULA1 FORMULA2 SIT-TYPE PRED) means that FORMULA2 becomes true when FORMULA1 becomes true, where FORMULA1 contains a clause of the form (thereExists ?SIT SIT-TYPE), and where ?SIT changes some assertion of the form (PRED ...).
label: Sit Results In Prop
sitResultsInProp

comment: (prefers AGT PROP1 PROP2) means that the state of affairs picked out by the CycLSentence_Assertible PROP1 is preferred by the Agent_PartiallyTangible AGT to the state of affairs picked out by the CycLSentence_Assertible PROP2. See also prefersToMaximize, prefersToMinimize.
label: Prefers (ternary predicate)
prefers

comment: The predicate corresponding to SampleInstanceOfTypeForProgramFn (q.v.).
label: Sample Instance Of Type For Program
sampleInstanceOfTypeForProgram

comment: A quaternary predicate, (assertionProducedByReformulation ASST TERM SENT SPEC) means that the CycLAssertion ASST about the term TERM was created by the CycLReformulator, using CycLSentence SENT as the input sentence and SPEC as the reformulation specification. Assertions on assertionProducedByReformulation will keep a record of the origins of reformulated assertions.
label: Assertion Produced By Reformulation
assertionProducedByReformulation

comment:
A quaternary QueryMacroPredicate (q.v.). (pairwisePropertyOfCollection_IncludeReferenceEntities MODIFIER COLLECTION THING SET) states that THING is the property described by MODIFIER and SET is a set of instances of COLLECTION that jointly satisfy the final comparision in terms of MODIFIER. This is a very general predicate and its meaning in a given context is determined by what stands in its arg1. For example, 
  (#specifiedPropertyOfCollection-IncludeReferenceEntities Longest_Between COLLECTION DURATION SET)
means that DURATION is the longest duration between (the respective ending and starting points of) sequential intances of COLLECTION, and SET is a set of sequential instances that have DURATION between them. (Note that, in this case, COLLECTION must be a collection of temporal things for which the start and end dates are known.)
label: Pairwise Property Of Collection Include Reference Entities
pairwisePropertyOfCollection-IncludeReferenceEntities

comment: (culturePrescribes_Hypothetical CULTURE COND ACTTYPE ROLE) means that within CULTURE, when COND is true, it is considered good or proper or right for one to play ROLE in an instance of ACTTYPE, and bad or improper or wrong not to do so. For example, some cultures expect one to help others in need when one is in a position to do so. This predicate applies equally to moral rules, rules of conduct or etiquette, and customs. See also culturePrescribes_Categorical, cultureProscribes_Categorical, and cultureProscribes_Hypothetical.
label: Culture Prescribes Hypothetical
culturePrescribes-Hypothetical

comment: If SPACE is a TopologicalSpace with base set BASE (see baseSetOfTopologicalSpace), NEIGHBORHOOD is a subset of BASE, and THING is an element of NEIGHBORHOOD, then NEIGHBORHOOD is a neighborhood of THING if and only if there exists an open set OPENSET of SPACE which contains THING and is a subset of NEIGHBORHOOD. In CycL, this relation is expressed as (neighborhoodOfThingInTopologicalSpace THING NEIGHBORHOOD SPACE).
label: Neighborhood Of Thing In Topological Space
neighborhoodOfThingInTopologicalSpace

comment: An instance of TernaryPredicate. glfComponentSemanticsWRTGraph is used to relate an instance of GLFGraphComponent to the object it denotes in the context of some instance THING of Thing with a graphical structure. In particular, there is a graphical depiction of THING in which the relevant instance of GLFGraphComponent represents the relevant object. For example, (glfComponentSemanticsWRTGraph GLFNODE002 (CycQueryRunningFromFn VegetationConcealsDefenderFromLOSFlanksQuerySpec) VegetationAnalysis) says that there is a graphical depiction of the collection of all vegetation analysis events in which GLFNODE002 represents the running of the query, VegetationConcealsDefenderFromLOSFlanksQuerySpec).
label: Glf Component Semantics WRT Context
glfComponentSemanticsWRTContext

comment: A unary predicate which pertains to instances of CycLSentence. (rejectedSentence FORMULA) states that FORMULA is a CycL formula which although syntactically well-formed is not semantically well-formed with respect to argument constraints only. For example, (rejectedSentence (bordersOn Canada Country)). See also admittedSentence.
label: Rejected Sentence
rejectedSentence

comment: A sentence of the form (datedCandidateNCTestHasResults NC-RULE DATE RESULTS SEARCH-ENGINE) means that a group of candidate noun compounds were generated for NC-RULE on DATE and evaluated against the corpus covered by SEARCH-ENGINE with a result of RESULTS. In general, RESULTS consist of list of lists where each element of the top-level list has the following form: (TheList NC-STRING MOD-STRING HEAD-STRING MOD-TERM HEAD-TERM (TheList NC-HIT-COUNT MOD-HIT-COUNT HEAD-HIT-COUNT)). NC-STRING is a CharacterString that represents a particular noun compound that Cyc recognizes as satisfying the constraints of NC-RULE. MOD-STRING and HEAD-STRING represent substings corresponding to the modifier and head of the compound (respectively). MOD-TERM and HEAD-TERM are the denotations of MOD-STRING and HEAD-STRING wrt.which NC-STRING is recognized as satisfying the constraints of NC-RULE. NC-HIT-COUNT, MOD-HIT-COUNT, and HEAD-HIT-COUNT are the numbers of hits that were found by SEARCH-ENGINE for NC-STRING, MOD-STRING, and HEAD-STRING, respectively.
label: Dated Candidate NC Test Has Results
datedCandidateNCTestHasResults

comment: A TernaryPredicate that relates a SetOrCollection to a SetOrCollection to a Real0_1. (probabilityOfInsBeingIns SOC1 SOC2 N) means that the probability that something is an instance of SOC2, given only the information that it is an instance of SOC1, is N. See also likelihoodOfInsBeingIns.
label: Probability Of Ins Being Ins
probabilityOfInsBeingIns

comment: attitudeTowardsEvent(AGT EVT DEGREE-OF-EMOTYPE) means that the SentientAnimal AGT has the instance of FeelingAttribute DEGREE-OF-EMOTYPE about the Event EVT. By `attitude' we mean a feeling which may be latent and/or long-lasting. The third argument to this predicate is usually constructed by wrapping a specialization of FeelingAttribute in a generic value function such as HighAmountFn. Please avoid using these functions with FeelingAttribute itself. To refer to feelings that AGT experiences immediately and consciously towards EVT, use feelsTowardsEvent.
label: Attitude Towards Event
attitudeTowardsEvent

comment:
An instance of both ArgCardinalityPredicate and InterArgConstraintPredicate (qq.v.) that can be used to put a conditional argument-cardinality constraint on a specified argument-place of a predicate, dependent upon the type of thing occupying that or another specified argument-place.

(interArgDependentCardinality PRED M COL1 N COL2 CARD) means that when PRED's Mth argument is an instance of COL2, INS1, then, however the rest of the arguments are fixed, there is at most CARD things, INS2, that are instances of COL3 that stand in PRED to INS1. For example, a relation like currentlyFieldedPlayerForTeam that relates a sports team in arg1 to a player in arg2 that is playing in a game the team is involved in the current context might have the following cardinality restriction

(interArgDependentCardinality currentlyFieldedPlayerForTeam 1 BaseballTeam 2 Outfielder 3)

This would entail that in a given context there are at most 3 outfielders playing in a game for a given team. The most useful assertions of this type are when CARD=1. In cases like those, simplification modules can utilize this information to unify distinct variables that may have arisen from independent transformations.
label: Inter Arg Dependent Cardinality
interArgDependentCardinality

comment: (determinationOfValueOfArgInReln EVENT N PRED) means that in EVENT, an instance of DeterminingTheValueOfASlot, the value of the Nth argument of a formula FORMULA of the form (PRED . ARGS) where all of the argument-places in FORMULA were bound but for the Nth. For example, (determinationOfValueOfArgInReln CalculatingTheAPROnLoan001 2 annualPercentageRate) says that in this particular event of calculating the APR on Loan001, the value of ?X in (annualPercentageRate Loan001 ?X) is determined.
label: Determination Of Value Of Arg In Reln
determinationOfValueOfArgInReln
Effective Dispersal Tool For Bio Agent
effectiveDispersalToolForBioAgent

comment: (subcatFrameDependentKeyword FRAME NUM KEYWORD) indicates that KEYWORD is the SubLKeyword for the NUM-th dependent in phrases headed by SubcategorizationFrame FRAME.
label: Subcat Frame Dependent Keyword
subcatFrameDependentKeyword

comment: (doesntNeedParseTemplate RELATION) means that the usual requirement that a CycL relation have an assertion associating it with a natural language template (these are usually made in the form of assertTemplate_Reln RELATION ...) does not apply. infersParseTemplate is an important specPred of this term.
label: Doesnt Need Parse Template
doesntNeedParseTemplate

comment: (definitionInDictionary DICT TERM DEFINITION) means that the structurally specific Dictionary DICT contains (see containsStructure_CW) the TextString TERM and the GraphicalStructure DEF, that TERM is one of the terms defined in DICT, and that DEF is the definition of TERM in DICT.
label: Definition In Dictionary
definitionInDictionary

comment: This ternary predicate is used to indicate that a borrower is required, by the terms of a type of loan agreement, to play a particular role in a particular kind of situation. (loanAgreementTypeRequiresOfBorrower AGREEMENT-TYPE SIT-TYPE ROLE) means that entering into an instance of AGREEMENT-TYPE (a specialization of LoanAgreement) requires the borrower to play the Role ROLE in some situation that is an instance of the subcollection of Situation SIT-TYPE. Cf. loanAgreementTypeRequiresOfCreditor.
Mx4rwLSVCpwpEbGdrcN5Y29ycA: loan agreement type requirement on the borrowers
label: loan agreement type requirement on the borrower
loanAgreementTypeRequiresOfBorrower

comment: (travelLegs TOUR PATH LOCFROM LOCTO) means that PATH constitutes a 'leg' on the itinerary of TOUR from the location LOCFROM to the location LOCTO.travelLegs are usually represented as running between well-known locations, such as instances of City, and are often composed of a single Path_Customary or several instances of Path_Customary. In a graphical representation of a TravelTour in which tourDestinations and/or tourVisits are the nodes, the instances of Path_Simple that are second arguments of the travelLegs GAFs for the tour will be the links.
label: Travel Legs
travelLegs

comment: (remapMatch OLD CONSTRAINTS NEW) carries out a remapping operation on OLD, under CONSTRAINTS, resulting in NEW.
label: Remap Match
remapMatch

comment:
(endsAfterEndOfInSituationType SIT-TYPE SUBSIT-TYPE1 SUBSIT-TYPE2) means that in any instance SIT of SIT-TYPE (a specialization of Situation), if instances SIT1 and SIT2 of SUBSIT-TYPE1 and SUBSIT-TYPE2 occur as subsituations, then SIT1 ends after SIT2 ends.

Note that (endsAfterEndOfInSituationType SIT-TYPE SUBSIT-TYPE1 SUBSIT-TYPE2) does not imply that instances of SUBSIT-TYPE1 or SUBSIT-TYPE2 occur as subsituations of every instance of SIT-TYPE, since SUBSIT-TYPE1 and SUBSIT-TYPE2 may be merely candidate subsituation types of SIT-TYPE (see candidateProperSubSituationTypes).
label: Ends After End Of In Situation Type
endsAfterEndOfInSituationType
subPropertyOf: Ends After Start Of In Situation Type

comment: (patientPlacedOnIABPInEventWRTOperationDate EVT OP WHEN) means that in EVT, the patient treated in OP is placed on an intra-aortic balloon pump at time WHEN, and this is placement is relevant to OP. E.g., for the purposes of STS reporting, EVT occurs within 2 weeks prior to OP.
label: Patient Placed On IABP In Event WRT Operation Date
patientPlacedOnIABPInEventWRTOperationDate

comment: (cityBlockBoundedBy BLOCK ST1 ST2 ST3 ST4) means that BLOCK is bounded by streets ST1 - ST4 such that if one starts on ST1 (where it borders BLOCK) and circles around BLOCK making only right-hand turns one will travel along ST1, ST2, ST3, and ST4, in that order. The region immediately surrounding the block must be an UrbanArea that has a GridStreetSystem running through it. To have this predicate correctly relate a given city block BLOCK to its bordering streets, one can fill its arg2 position with any of the four streets that borders BLOCK, and then continue to fill in the remaining argument-places according to the order in which one would travel along the other three streets if one were circling BLOCK in a clockwise fashion (i.e. by making only right-hand turns). See also CityBlockFn and CityGridSectionFn.
label: City Block Bounded By
cityBlockBoundedBy

comment: This predicate is a specialization of logicalFieldTranslation which translates logical field values into simpler logical field values. It is used in cases where additional logical fields, or more complex expressions can be decomposed into other existing logical field values. See also the dual relation logicalFieldEncoding.
label: Logical Field Encoding
logicalFieldEncoding

comment: (productionAmount PRODUCER PRODUCT-TYPE AMOUNT) means that the ScalarInterval AMOUNT is a measure of the amount of instances of the ProductType PRODUCT-TYPE produced by the instance of SomethingExisting, PRODUCER. PRODUCER might, for example, be a Country, a Business, or a GeographicalRegion. If AMOUNT is a Rate, AMOUNT indicates the average rate of production of instances of PRODUCT-TYPE by PRODUCER. This predicate should be used when the time period of production is unknown. If the time period is known, use productionAmountDuring.
label: production amount
productionAmount

comment: A cleans B using C.
label: Cleans With
cleansWith

comment: This is the corresponding predicate of the function SubSitRoleSpecFn.
label: Role Specificationfor Sub Sit Type And Role
roleSpecificationforSubSitTypeAndRole

comment: (genMassNoun TERM) means that the CycLReifiableDenotationalTerm TERM should be treated as a mass noun when CycL formulae containing TERM are paraphrased into English. See also the related predicate #$prettyName.
label: Gen Mass Noun
genMassNoun

comment: An assertion of the form (usesProxyInEventsOfTypeWith SOURCE PROXY TYPE TARGET) is used to represent that the IntelligentAgent SOURCE uses the IntelligentAgent PROXY to interact with the IntelligentAgent during instances of TYPE, some sub-collection of SocialOccurrence. So an assertion of (usesProxyInEventsOfTypeWith Bob Joe Negotiating Sue) would mean that Joe acts as a proxy for Bob during some Negotiating events involving Sue. See the related predicate proxyFor.
label: Uses Proxy In Events Of Type With
usesProxyInEventsOfTypeWith

comment: (industryFractionOfGDP GE COL THING NR) means that NR is the quotient of the monetary value of the goods and services produced by the specialization of Industry_Localized COL within the GeopoliticalEntity GE during the temporal extent of the TemporalThing THING (as dividend) and the monetary value of GE's total domestic production of goods and services (its gross domestic product) during the temporal extent of THING (as divisor). A country would be a typical instance of GE. COL can range from a broad economic sector, such as agriculture, manufacturing, or services to a more specific segment of the economy such as the automobile industry. THING will often be a calendar time period; but it may also be, for instance, a particular Event. For example, to express the fact that services accounted for 41 percent of Saudi Arabia's gross domestic product for 1994, we can say (industryFractionOfGDP SaudiArabia ServiceEconomicSector (YearFn 1994) (Percent 41)). See also grossDomesticProduct and productionValueOfIndustryDuring.
label: Industry Fraction Of GDP
industryFractionOfGDP

comment: (almostIntervalOfType INTERVAL-TYPE NUMBER-TYPE NUMBER RANGE) holds just in case RANGE is the instance of INTERVAL-TYPE that consists of all the instances of NUMBER-TYPE that are "almost" NUMBER. For TKB, we define "almost" NUM as being less than NUM and within 10 percent of NUM (rounded down). This is the corresponding predicate to AlmostIntervalOfTypeFn.
label: Almost Interval Of Type
almostIntervalOfType

comment:
A ternary MetaRelation predicate that is used to state that a given thing meets the argument-type constraints on a given argument-place of a given relation. (admittedArgument THING ARGNUM RELN) means that THING satisfies all of the (single-argument) argument-type constraints (see ArgIsaPredicate and ArgGenlPredicate) for the ARGNUM-th argument position of RELN.

For example, both of the following sentences hold: 

  (admittedArgument AbrahamLincoln 1 wife)

  (admittedArgument Cougar 1 JuvenileFn) .
See also admittedAllArgument and admittedSentence.
label: Admitted Argument
admittedArgument

comment: (correlatedWith SET DEP-PRED INDEP-PRED) means that the second arguments to DEP-PRED are either positively or negatively correlated with those for INDEP-PRED. Note that correlatedWith assertions don't entail a particular directionality of the causal relationship between arg2 values for DEP-PRED and INDEP-PRED. It might go either direction, or there may be no direct causal link, with instead arg2 values for DEP-PRED and INDEP-PRED actually being independent but subject to some common causal mechanism. See also dependsOn, positivelyCorrelatedWith and negativelyCorrelatedWith.
label: Correlated With
correlatedWith

comment: typeRequiresToPlayRole is an instance of ResourcePredicate. (typeRequiresToPlayRole OBJTYPE1 OBJTYPE2 EVENTTYPE ROLE) means that, in order to play ROLE in an event of EVENTTYPE, instances of OBJTYPE1 require some single instance of OBJTYPE2. Note that this is neutral as to whether or not the instance of OBJTYPE1 desires to, needs to, or actually will play ROLE in an event of EVENTTYPE. See also requiresToPlayRole.
label: Type Requires To Play Role
typeRequiresToPlayRole

comment: (doGetTrojanProgramToExecuteAsOn AGENT CODE ACCOUNT MACHINE) means that AGENT takes steps toward the goal of having CODE executed on MACHINE with the privilege-level of ACCOUNT, where it is understood that AGENT has previously inserted CODE into the filesystem on MACHINE in the appropriate location and under the appropriate name.
label: Do Get Trojan Program To Execute As On
doGetTrojanProgramToExecuteAsOn

comment: An assertion of the form (collectionWithKBTermRanking COLL KB MODULE INT) states that COLL, an instance of CycKBTermRank, is the collection of all individuals who receive the ranking INT, some PositiveInteger, when the instance of CycTermRankModule MOD is run against the instance of CycKB KB.
label: Collection With KB Term Ranking
collectionWithKBTermRanking

comment: A ternary instance of InterArgIsaPredicate (q.v.). (interArgIsa1_3 RELN INDEPENDENT-ARG-COL DEPENDENT-ARG-COL) means that, when an instance of INDEPENDENT-ARG-COL appears as the first argument to RELN, a necessary condition for semantic well-formedness is that the third argument must be an instance of DEPENDENT-ARG-COL. That is, if INST is an instance of INDEPENDENT-ARG-COL, then (RELN INST ARG2 ARG3 ... ARGN) is semantically well-formed only if ARG3 is an instance of DEPENDENT-ARG-COL. For an explanation of semantic well-formedness, see CycLExpression_Assertible and its direct specializations.
label: Inter Arg Isa 1 3
interArgIsa1-3

comment:
A ternary predicate that relates an agent to an object or situation (see TemporallyExistingThing) to a level of Presence (q.v.). (levelOfPresenceIn AGENT TEMP-THING PRESENCE) means that in TEMP-THING AGENT exhibits PRESENCE. TEMP-THING might be a GeographicalRegion in which AGENT is located or is active, a Group of which AGENT is a member, or an Event (or StaticSituation) in which AGENT plays a role (or is a constituent). For example, 
  (levelOfPresenceIn UnitedStatesArmy Iraq (HighAmountFn Presence))
means that the US Army has a strong presence in Iraq.
label: Level Of Presence In
levelOfPresenceIn

comment: (wnSenseDefinition WORD POS NUM DEFINITION) is a #$senseAnnotation that gives the natural language definition for the specified word sense from WordNet.
label: Wn Sense Definition
wnSenseDefinition

comment: (averageDailyHighTemperature REGION TEMP TYPE) means that during instances of TYPE, the average daily high temperature in the GeographicalRegion REGION is TEMP. Note that TYPE will often be a type of calendar time period, such as a subset of CalendarMonth.
label: Average Daily High Temperature
averageDailyHighTemperature

comment: (relationNotAmenable REL THING-1 THING-2) means that it is expected that the relation REL does not hold between THING-1 and THING-2; that is, it is expected that (not (REL THING-1 THING-2)) holds. See also relationExpected.
label: Relation Not Amenable
relationNotAmenable

comment:
A MetaRelation that is used to state that the referenced predicate relates the referent of the referenced function applied to a list of arguments and those arguments, themselves, with the argument order for the predicate being described by a list of the order in which the corresponding arguments appear in the function (with "0" denoting the functional result).

The argument and result restrictions on FUNC must be the same as the corresponding argument restrictions on PRED. The predicate must be functional in the argument place corresponding to the functional result, allowing the value of the function for a list of arguments to be derived from an assertion based on the predicate.

For example, (functionCorrespondsToShuffledPredicate PerFn multiplicationUnits (TheList 0 2 1)) means that means that (multiplicationUnits (PerFn METERS SECONDS) SECONDS METERS) for SECONDS and METERS being any instance of UnitOfMeasure.
label: Function Corresponds To Shuffled Predicate Symmetric
functionCorrespondsToShuffledPredicate-Symmetric

comment: `(drugForDiseaseAvailableToOrg ORGTYPE DRUGTYPE AILTYPE)' means that instances of DRUGTYPE (which is a type of drug effective against the disease AILTYPE) are available to the members of ORGTYPE. By available, we intend to say that instances DRUGTYPE could actually be given to the members of ORGTYPE and not that it merely exists.
label: Drug For Disease Available To Org
drugForDiseaseAvailableToOrg

comment: This predicate can be used to assert that an agent has made a certain essentially subjective assessment or value judgment about a particular individual in relation to a topic. (subjectivelyEvaluatesIndividualToThing AGENT INDIV TOPIC EVAL) means that the AGENT projects upon INDIV the EvaluativeQuantity (q.v.) EVAL in regard to the TOPIC. As the evaluation in question is essentially subjective, the above formula of course does not entail either (i) that INDIV actually has the feature it is subjectively thought to have (or some "objective" counterpart thereof) or (ii) that any other given agent would also attribute EVAL to INDIV. Indeed, outside of contexts explicitly defined so as to represent some particular agent's point of view (e.g. some sentient agent's inner mental world or the world-view espoused by a particular religion), it arguably makes no sense to attribute an EvaluativeQuantity to an individual directly.
label: Subjectively Evaluates Individual To Thing
subjectivelyEvaluatesIndividualToThing

comment:
A ternary MetaRelation predicate that relates a Collection to an integer (representing an argument-place) to a Relation such that collection contains all of and only the admittedArguments (q.v.) to the specified argument-place of the relation. (admittedAllAndOnlyArgument COL ARGNUM RELN) means that, for any thing THING, THING is an instance of COL if and only if THING satisfies all of the (single-argument) argument-type constraints (see ArgIsaPredicate and ArgGenlPredicate) for the ARGNUMth argument position of RELN.

If a given relation has an argument-place on which there is only one arg-isa constraint, and no arg-genl constraints, the collection used in the arg-isa constraint is related to the given relation by admittedAllAndOnlyArgument. Thus (admittedAllAndOnlyArgument HomoSapiens 1 spouse) holds. Otherwise, things get a bit more complicated. For example, the collection of all and only the admitted-arguments for the first argument-position of JuvenileFn is (SubcollectionOfWithRelationToFn ExistingObjectType genls Animal).

See also admittedAllArgument and admittedSomeArgument.
label: Admitted All And Only Argument
admittedAllAndOnlyArgument

comment: (pegDerivedSentenceDrawsOnInterpretations PEG CYCL MT) means that the Microtheory MT represents a possible interpretation of the LinguisticExpressionPeg_CompleteUtterance PEG that properly contains (see termFormulas and different) a closed CycL sentence S, provable from the content model of PEG (see contentModelFocalPeg), that is also contained in CYCL, a CycL sentence that (thus) entails S and, like S is also true from the content model of PEG.
label: Peg Derived Sentence Draws On Interpretations
pegDerivedSentenceDrawsOnInterpretations

comment: (compatibleWithStandard PROD STAND SCRIPT ASLOT) states that instances of product type PROD are compatible in scripts of type SCRIPT with anything which meets standard STAND when it is the actor ASLOT in the script.
label: Compatible With Standard
compatibleWithStandard

comment:
A MetaRelation that is used to state that the referenced predicate relates the referent of the referenced function applied to a list of arguments and those arguments, themselves, with the argument order for the predicate being described by a list of the order in which the corresponding arguments appear in the function (with "0" denoting the functional result. For example, (functionCorrespondsToShuffledPredicate natArgument FormulaArgFn (TheList 2 1 0)) means that means that (natArgument NAT N (FormulaArgFn N NAT)).

The argument and result restrictions on FUNC must be equal to or more specific than the corresponding argument restrictions on PRED.

If PRED is functional in the argument which corresponds to the function denotation, use the more specific predicate, functionCorrespondsToShuffledPredicate_Symmetric.
label: Function Corresponds To Shuffled Predicate
functionCorrespondsToShuffledPredicate

comment: (typesChemicalBondTypeBetweenCapable BOND-TYPE COL1 COL2) means that instances of COL1 can form chemical bonds of type BOND-TYPE with instances of COL2, where 'can' means that it is chemically possible (or maybe even likely).
label: Types Chemical Bond Type Between Capable
typesChemicalBondTypeBetweenCapable

comment: This ternary predicate relates a ConceptualWork, a Thing, and a string that the work uses to describe that thing, possibly as a definition or glossary entry.
label: Cw Term Description
cwTermDescription

comment: (#$intendsByInUtterancePeg SPEAKER PEG INTERPRETATION UTTERANCE-PEG) says that SPEAKER, an instance of IntelligentAgent, in the context of the (possibly larger) instance of LinguisticExpressionPeg_CompleteUtterance UTTERANCE-PEG, intended to refer to INTERPRETATION when introducing the instance of LinguisticExpressionPeg PEG (a sub-expression of UTTERANCE-PEG -- see subExpressions). So, for example, if PEG is a linguistic expression peg for "my dog" and UTTERANCE-PEG is a peg for "I fed my dog some tuna," then (#$intendsByInUtterancePeg SPEAKER PEG Dog001 UTTERANCE-PEG) says that by introducing "my dog" in the context of the utterance that introduced "I fed my dog some tuna," "my dog" was intended to refer to Dog001. The purpose of representing UTTERANCE-PEG is to provide a larger context that might help one deduce the intended referent of PEG; contrast the Dog001 interpretation with the empty-set interpretation were UTTERANCE-PEG the peg for, "She asked me how my dog is, not knowing that I've never owned one."
label: Intends By In Utterance Peg Context
intendsByInUtterancePegContext

comment: (extractedFromCorpusUsingTool THING CORPUS TOOL) means that the instance TOOL of ConceptExtractionTool was used to extract (identify a mention of) THING in the instance of Corpus CORPUS. Note that extractedFromCorpusUsingTool is an instance of TemporallyQualifiableRelation. (extractedFromCorpusUsingTool THING CORPUS TOOL) is true at time T iff there is an <font color="#ff0000">#$ConceptExtraction</font> event that has completed at T or earlier, such that TOOL is the programUsed, CORPUS is the <font color="#ff0000">#$conceptExtractionSource</font> and THING is the <font color="#ff0000">#$conceptExtracted</font>.
label: Extracted From Corpus Using Tool
extractedFromCorpusUsingTool
Sksi Source Queryable
sksiSourceQueryable
comment: (sksiSourceQueryable SKS) is true iff (and (sksiSourceRegistered SKS) (sksiSourceActivated SKS) (sksiSourceAccessible SKS)) is true.

(doOutputCommentString HACKER FILE STRING) means that the HACKER adds the comment string STRING to the end of FILE. This method should be decomposed differently in specific programming domains depending on that language's style of comment. For instance, in the C language comments are bracketed by "/*" and "*/", and in lisp programs comments are preceded by a ";" on each line.
label: Do Output Comment String
doOutputCommentString

comment: This predicate relates a OpenGISGeometryComposite to its Nth component part or maximally strongly connected part. That is, (nthGeometryInComposite GEOMETRYCOMPOSITE N MEMBER) means that MEMBER is the Nth such part of GEOMETRYCOMPOSITE.
label: Nth Geometry In Composite
nthGeometryInComposite

comment: (minQuantityInBinPredDamagesObjectType BIN-PRED VALUE OBJECT-TYPE) means that in situations where INS is an instance of OBJECT-TYPE and (BIN-PRED INS VALUE2) holds where VALUE2 is greater than or equal to VALUE, it is highly likely that INS will suffer non-trivial damage.
label: Min Quantity In Bin Pred Damages Object Type
minQuantityInBinPredDamagesObjectType

comment: (approximateIntervalOfType INTERVAL-TYPE NUMBER-TYPE NUMBER RANGE) holds just in case RANGE is the instance of INTERVAL-TYPE that consists of all the instances of NUMBER-TYPE that are "approximately" NUMBER. For TKB, we define "approximately" as plus or minus 10 percent of NUMBER (rounded down). This is the corresponding predicate to ApproximateIntervalOfTypeFn.
label: Approximate Interval Of Type
approximateIntervalOfType

comment: (supplyFromCapacityDuring PT1 COL PT2 THING AMOUNT) means that that the ScalarInterval AMOUNT is a measure of the greatest possible amount of instances of the Collection COL with which the instance of PartiallyTangible PT1 could be supplied from the instance of PartiallyTangible PT2 during the temporal extent of the TemporalThing THING. Like the predicate suppliedWith (q.v.), supplyFromCapacityDuring is very general. In various assertions PT1 might, for instance, be a Cell, a Person, a Business, or a GeographicalRegion; and likewise for PT2. The range of possible supplies is similarly broad. THING will often be a calendar time period; but it may also be, for instance, a particular Event. If AMOUNT is a Rate, AMOUNT indicates what would be the average rate of supply of instances of PRODUCT-TYPE to PT1 from PT2 during the temporal extent of THING if PT1 were supplied with PRODUCT-TYPE from PT2 at the limit of its capacity.
label: Supply From Capacity During
supplyFromCapacityDuring

comment: This predicate is the predicateUnion of explicitRelationshipPredicateList and implicitRelationshipPredicateList.
label: Relationship Predicate List
relationshipPredicateList

comment: (specifiedPropertyOfCollectionMember MODIFIER COLLECTION THING) states that THING is the member of collection that has the property described by MODIFIER. For instance, if MODIFIER=DeadliestFn, then THING will be the event in which more people were killed than any other event in COLLECTION .
label: Specified Property Of Collection Member
specifiedPropertyOfCollectionMember

comment: A ternary complex action predicate. (doCloseFunctionDefinition PROGRAMMER FILE FUNCTION) means that PROGRAMMER appends to the end of FILE code which closes the declaration of the program function FUNCTION.
label: Do Close Function Definition
doCloseFunctionDefinition
Graduation Date
graduationDate

(exportCapacity REGION PRODUCT-TYPE RATE) means that the Rate RATE is the greatest possible rate at which instances of the ProductType PRODUCT-TYPE could be exported by the GeographicalRegion REGION. Note that RATE may be expressed as a MonetaryRate, but also as rate of volume, mass or number depending on the type of product.
label: export capacity
exportCapacity
Default Defining Mt For Sentence On Term
defaultDefiningMtForSentenceOnTerm

comment: (credibleToOn ARG1 ARG2 ARG3 ARG4) means that ARG2 has a credibility of level ARG4 for the agent ARG1 with respect to an event ARG3 .
label: Credible To On
credibleToOn

comment: The sales contract (item) Arg 1 stipulates the price Arg 3 for the type of product Arg 2.
label: Contract Price
contractPrice

comment: (sinceStartDatePerRecord DATE SYS STATUS RECORD-MT) means that since DATE, the system SYS has had the status STATUS, per the information in the microtheory, RECORD-MT.
label: Since Start Date Per Record
sinceStartDatePerRecord

comment: (lessVulnerableToBecause AGENT EVTTYPE ROLE PROP) means that there is an decreased chance of AGENT's playing the role ROLE in a situation of type EVTTYPE because PROP is true (decreasedChanceForRoleBecause AGENT EVTTYPE ROLE PROP) and AGENT has the goals (not (ROLE EVTTYPE AGENT)).
label: Less Vulnerable To Because
lessVulnerableToBecause

comment: This is the corresponding predicate of the function TemporalStageFn.
label: Temporal Stage Is Nth For Sit Type
temporalStageIsNthForSitType

comment: This is the corresponding predicate of the function StreetNumberFn. An assertion of the form (locationAtNumberOnStreet LOCATION NUMBER STREET) means that the PhysicalContactLocation LOCATION is the one designated by the Integer NUMBER on the Street_Generic STREET.
label: Location At Number On Street
locationAtNumberOnStreet

comment: Use this predicate to indicate the group of relations that should be used when representing assertions involving the preposition in question. Example: (denotation_Prep #$In-TheWord Preposition_Locative in_UnderspecifiedContainer) means that sentences using the locative "in" should use in_UnderspecifiedContainer or one of its specpreds in representation. The corresponding prepSemTrans assertions will provide an exact specification of how such relations should be used. For example, (prepSemTrans #$In-TheWord 4 VerbPhraseModifyingFrame (objectFoundInLocation :MOD-OBJ :OBJECT)) and (prepSemTrans #$In-TheWord 1 VerbPhraseModifyingFrame (eventOccursAt :ACTION :OBJECT))
label: Denotation-Prep
denotation-Prep

comment: (prospectiveRuleForCompound MOD MOD-DENOT HEAD HEAD-DENOT RULE) means that the phrase consisting of MOD and HEAD, under the semantic interpretations MOD-DENOT and HEAD-DENOT, may meet the syntactic and semantic constraints specified by RULE.
label: Prospective Rule For Compound
prospectiveRuleForCompound

comment: (conceptInSystemDefaultDisplayString THING SYSTEM STRING) means that when displaying the concepts of the system SYSTEM, an instance of AspatialInformationStore, it is preferred that THING be represented using the string STRING.
label: Concept In System Default Display String
conceptInSystemDefaultDisplayString

comment: (terrainTypeSideSlope TERRAIN-TYPE NUM DIRECTION) means that side number NUM of instances of TERRAIN-TYPE have a DIRECTION slope. NUM is an integer from 1 to n, where (terrainTypeNumberOfSides TERRAIN-TYPE n). The 'side' chosen to be side number 1 is completely arbitrary, but side 2 will be the next side in a clockwise direction from the point of reference of the central feature of the terrain. For example, if (terrainTypeNumberOfSides Saddle 4), and if (terrainTypeSideSlope Saddle 1 Down-Generally), then from the reference point of the 'seat' of the saddle, (terrainTypeSideSlope Saddle 2 Up_Generally), (terrainTypeSideSlope Saddle 3 Down_Generally) and (terrainTypeSideSlope Saddle 4 Up_Generally).
label: Terrain Type Side Slope
terrainTypeSideSlope

comment: (largerThan LARGER SMALLER SLOT) means that LARGER's value on the QuantitySlot SLOT is larger than SMALLER's value on that slot.
label: Larger Than
largerThan
subPropertyOf: amount comparison : greater than or equal to with respect to scalar

comment: (prepSemTrans_New WORD PREP FRAME TRANS) means that the translation of the preposition WORD of type PREP in frame FRAME is TRANS. Example: (prepSemTrans_New #$In-TheWord Preposition_Locative VerbPhraseModifyingFrame (eventOccursAt :ACTION :IND-OBJECT)).
label: Prep Sem Trans New
prepSemTrans-New

comment: (organizationIsRegularServiceProvider AGT-1 ORGANIZATION-TYPE AGT-2) means that AGT-1 has a relationship with AGT-2, such that if AGT-1 needs a service that is provided by instances of ORGANIZATION-TYPE, by default they will go to AGT-2 first.
label: Organization Is Regular Service Provider
organizationIsRegularServiceProvider

comment: (schemaObjectID SCHEMA OBJECT ID) means that OBJECT _is_ the object defined by SCHEMA with the unique id, ID. OBJECT is typically referred to functionally using SchemaObjectFn.
label: Schema Object ID
schemaObjectID

comment: An assertion of the form (indMightPlayRoleInSitType_Linkage IND ROLE SIT-TYPE) means that there is speculative evidence that the SomethingExisting IND might play the BinaryRolePredicate ROLE in an instance of the sub-collection of Situation SIT-TYPE. By speculative evidence, we mean evidence that is based on other hypotheses. Contrast with indMightPlayRoleInSitType_Evidential.
label: Ind Might Play Role In Sit Type Linkage
indMightPlayRoleInSitType-Linkage

comment:
A ternary predicate that relates a pair of tangible objects, space regions, or spatially-localized events to their mereological sum or union. (spatialSum SUM THING1 THING2) means that SUM is the unique SpatialThing (of the same basic type as THING1 and THING2) such that a spatial thing intersects (see spatiallyIntersects) SUM if and only if it intersects with either THING1 or THING2.

Note that "of the same basic type" in the above means that the three relata are either all PartiallyTangibles, all SpaceRegions, or all Event_Localizeds. This restriction is needed in order to ensure the uniqueness of SUM, since a tangible object, a space region, and an event can have the same spatial extent (see cospatial), despite their being distinct things.

See the corresponding function SpatialSumFn. Also see spatialProduct and spatialDifference.
label: spatial sum
spatialSum

comment: This is a specialized representation (semiotic) predicate meaning representation due to causation, such as when a deer track 'represents' the deer to a tracker because the deer caused the deer track to be the way it is. Similarly, a weathervane 'represents' the wind direction because of the way the wind direction has caused the vane to move. (signifiesTo_Index THING1 THING2 AGENT) means that, to AGENT, THING1 represents THING2 because AGENT regognizes that THING2 has caused THING1 to be the way it is. This is called 'indexical' representation. Compare this with the predicates signifiesTo_Icon and signifiesTo_Symbol. It's possible for all three to apply to the same representation. If the basis for the representation is unknown, use the more general predicate signifiesTo.
label: index
signifiesTo-Index

comment: An instance of SummaryPredicate useful for summarizing knowledge about more than one term. (predicateTypeSummaryForThing_Set PRED-TYPE SET SENTENCE) means that SENTENCE's arg0 slot is occupied by an instance PRED of PRED-TYPE and that all of the terms in the set of terms SET occupy other argument positions in SENTENCE. For example, (predicateTypeSummaryForThing_Set LikesPredicate (TheSet #$JenniferSullivan #$Cynthia) (likesAsFriend #$JenniferSullivan #$Cynthia)) is true, and means that some instance of LikesPredicate occurs as the arg0 in (likesAsFriend #$JenniferSullivan #$Cynthia), and that all of the terms in the set denoted by (TheSet #$JenniferSullivan #$Cynthia) also occur in (likesAsFriend #$JenniferSullivan #$Cynthia). This predicate is particularly useful for asking queries with the first and second argument slots bound and the third slot open. For example, asking (predicateTypeSummaryForThing_Set OrganismRequirementsPredicate (TheSet (AdultFn Dog) (AdultFn Cat)) ?SENTENCE) will mean the system will find any assertions whose arg0 is an instance of OrganismRequirementsPredicate that also contain the terms (AdultFn Dog) and (AdultFn Cat). See also predicateTypeSummaryForThing.
label: Predicate Type Summary For Thing Set
predicateTypeSummaryForThing-Set

comment: (logicalFieldValueForSchemaMeaningSentenceInArg LS LFVI ARG-POS) means that in a meaning sentence for LS the logical field value indexical LFVI is the term in ARG-POS. This is a useful abstraction of information for logical schemas which have exactly one meaning sentence with a binary predicate in arg0.
label: Logical Field Value For Schema Meaning Sentence In Arg
logicalFieldValueForSchemaMeaningSentenceInArg

comment: (vehicleConeIndex VEHICLE NR-OF-PASS VCI-VALUE) indicates the VCI value for both the type of vehicle and their number of passes over the same path . The VCI value is necessary for determining whether a vehicle is able to traverse a soil, especially if the soil is wet or damp. For a particular soil type, compare the ratingConeIndex to the vehicle's vehicleConeIndex. The military usually calculates with one pass, VCI-1, and fifty passes, VCI-50. For example, one M1A1AbramsTank (VCI-1 = 25) can traverse wet clay (RCI=40). However, 50 M1A1AbramsTank (VCI-50 = 58) will not be able to traverse the same wet clay.
label: Vehicle Cone Index
vehicleConeIndex

comment: (generalizationOfNCR NEW-RULE OLD-RULE OLD-CONSTRAINT NEW-CONSTRAINT)means that NEW-RULE is a new NounCompoundRule derived from OLDRULE by replacing OLD-CONSTRAINT (cf. NounCompoundRuleConstraint) with NEW-CONSTRAINT.
label: Generalization Of NCR
generalizationOfNCR
Use Reformulation Rule For Relational NP Tersification
useReformulationRuleForRelationalNPTersification
comment: This predicate is used to mark rules which clean-up (tersify) the translation of relational nouns.

This predicate can be used to indicate a type that an object is (correctly) identified as in some instance of IdentifyingObjectAsType. (identifiedAsType IDENT OBJ COL) means that in the instance IDENT of IdentifyingObjectAsType, the instance OBJ of Individual is identified as being of the type COL, a collection. See also IdentifyingAsTypeFn as well as Identifying and identifiedThing.
label: Identified As Type
identifiedAsType

comment:
A KEFacilitationPredicate and RuleMacroPredicate. (keSuggestionPreds_InsIns COL1 BINPRED COL2) means that for every known instance INS1 of COL1, it is suggested that there be some instance INS2 of COL2 such that (BINPRED INS1 INS2) is known in the knowledge base.

For example,

(keSuggestionPreds_InsIns DefaultDisjointEdibleStuffType typicalTasteOfType ObjectTypeByTaste)

means that for every known instance ES-TYPE of DefaultDisjointEdibleStuffType, it is suggested that there be some instance TASTE of ObjectTypeByTaste such that (typicalTasteOfType ES-TYPE TASTE) is known in the knowledge base.

See also keSuggestionPredsInverse_InsIns.
label: Ke Suggestion Preds Ins Ins
keSuggestionPreds-InsIns

comment: (predHoldsBetweenRolePlayers_SitTypeToSubSitType SITTYPE SITTYPE_ROLE SUBSITTYPE SUBSITTYPE_ROLE BIN_PRED) means that in an instance SIT of SITTYPE an agent playing the role SITTYPE_ROLE will be related to an agent playing the role SUBSITTYPE_ROLE in the instance of the SUBSITTYPE that is a subsituation of SIT by the relation BIN_PRED.
label: Pred Holds Between Role Players Sit Type To Sub Sit Type
predHoldsBetweenRolePlayers-SitTypeToSubSitType

comment: A predicate used to state the lowest price that a share of a company's Stock (of a given class, e.g. common or preferred) has traded at on the current day. (stockPrice_High STOCK PRICE DATE EXCHANGE) means that PRICE is the lowest price paid for a share of STOCK so far on the CalendarDay that temporally subsumes DATE (i.e. the lowest price paid for such a share between that day's market opening and the end of DATE). Before the market opens, and on days the market is closed, the low for the last day the market was open remains in effect. Cf. stockPrice_High.
label: low price
stockPrice-Low

comment: (performSubL SUBL) states that the SubL expression SUBL has been successfully evaluated for side-effect. performSubL is evaluated as late in an inference proof as possible. See also trueSubL which evaluates usually as soon as possible in an inference. For example, (performSubL (ExpandSubLFn () (print "Done"))) will print out the string "Done" as a given proof path completes. See ExpandSubLFn for a way to denote SubL within CycL. See also EvaluateSubLFn.
label: Perform Sub L
performSubL

comment: (hasPositionInOrgDuring PERS ORG POS-TYPE INTERVAL) means that during the TimeInterval, INTERVAL, PERS holds the position POS-TYPE in the organization ORG.
label: Has Position In Org During
hasPositionInOrgDuring

comment:
(startsAfterEndOfInSituationType SIT-TYPE SUBSIT-TYPE1 SUBSIT-TYPE2) means that in any instance SIT of SIT-TYPE (a specialization of Situation), if instances SIT1 and SIT2 of SUBSIT-TYPE1 and SUBSIT-TYPE2 occur as subsituations, then SIT1 starts after SIT2 ends.

For example, (startsAfterEndOfInSituationType GoingOutToEat Paying HavingAMeal) means that when going out to eat, people pay after they finish eating.

Note that (startsAfterEndOfInSituationType SIT-TYPE SUBSIT-TYPE1 SUBSIT-TYPE2) does not imply that instances of SUBSIT-TYPE1 or SUBSIT-TYPE2 occur as subsituations of every instance of SIT-TYPE, since SUBSIT-TYPE1 and SUBSIT-TYPE2 may be merely candidate subsituation types of SIT-TYPE (see candidateProperSubSituationTypes).

comment: (completeExtentDecidableForValueInArg PRED VALUE ARGNUM) means that when the CycInferenceEngine is asked a closed query of the form (PRED ... VALUE ...) where VALUE appears in the ARGNUMth position, either it can prove (PRED ... VALUE ...) without transformation, or (not (PRED ... VALUE ...)) is true.
