comment:
(constructActionType NAME SCRIPTTYPE (TheList ACTORSLOT ...)) means construct a function that is a CollectionDenotingFunction, whose name is NAME and whose arguments must be appropriate for assertions of the form (ACTORSLOT ?x@SCRIPTTYPE <argument>). By having this predicate actions in plans can be stated more teresely in an active form, and we should be able to do plan and plan-recognition level reasoning over such GAFs. What happens as a result of asserting this is a bit of SubL gets called to actually add a new action-type constructor named NAME.

The effect of the afterAdding is to assert (for the following sample) Add: (constructActionType #$HitsFn HittingAnObject (TheList doneBy objectActedOn))

Results in: (isa #$HitsFn BinaryFunction); from number of items in TheList (isa #$HitsFn CollectionDenotingFunction) ; because it denotes a type (resultGenl #$HitsFn HittingAnObject) (arg1Isa #$HitsFn SomethingExisting) ; arg2Isa from the doneBy (arg2Isa #$HitsFn SomethingExisting) ; arg2Isa from the objectActedOn (expansion #$HitsFn (CollectionSubsetFn HittingAnObject (TheSetOf ?hitting (and (doneBy ?hitting :arg1) (objectActedOn ?hitting :arg2)))))
label: Construct Action Type
constructActionType
Sksi Source Accessible
sksiSourceAccessible
comment: (sksiSourceAccessible SKS) is true iff it is possible for Cyc to establish a connection to SKS. That is, i) if SKS is a database then Cyc should be able to open up an SQL connection to it; ii) if SKS is a web page then an empty http request to it should succeed (which basically amounts to being able to open a TCP connection to it); iii) if SKS is a file hash table then Cyc should be able to open it. See also sksiSourceRegistered, sksiSourceActivated, and sksiSourceQueryable.

(endsDurationAfterStartOfInSituationType SIT-TYPE AFTER-TYPE TIME BEFORE-TYPE) means that in any instance SIT of SIT-TYPE (a specialization of Situation), if instances AFTER and BEFORE of AFTER-TYPE and BEFORE-TYPE occur as subsituations, then AFTER ends TIME after BEFORE starts.
label: Ends Duration After Start Of In Situation Type
endsDurationAfterStartOfInSituationType

comment: (customary_SitRelationToSitType SIT PRED CUSTOMARY-SIT-TYPE) means that it would follow custom or convention in some culture (see CulturalConvention_Specification) if SIT were related by PRED to a situation of CUSTOMARY-SIT-TYPE. That is, it would follow custom if there were an instance CUSTOMARY-INS of CUSTOMARY-SIT-TYPE such that (PRED SIT CUSTOMARY-INS). Assertions involving this predicate should be made in a context that reflects the contents of some IndividualCustom, or larger CulturalConvention_Specification.
label: Customary Sit Relation To Sit Type
customary-SitRelationToSitType
subPropertyOf: Permitted Sit Relation To Sit Type

comment: If SPACE is a TopologicalSpace with base set BASE and SET is a subset of BASE, then the closure of SET is the set of all elements THING of SPACE for which the intersection of SET with every neighborhood of THING is non-empty. (See neighborhoodOfThingInTopologicalSpace) In CycL, this relation is expressed as (closureOfSetInTopologicalSpace CLOSURE SET SPACE).
label: Closure Of Set In Topological Space
closureOfSetInTopologicalSpace

comment: enables_RemovesDisablingFactors expresses the notion that an agent may be 'enabled' by an event in the following sense: the event removes all factors that are 'disabling', i.e., that would cause the agent not to be capable of doing a given action -- put another way: all factors that would prevent the agent from performing the action. More accurately, (enables_RemovesDisablingFactors SIT AGENT ACT_TYPE) is true iff SIT obtains, there are no factors preventing AGENT from performing an instance of ACT_TYPE, and SIT is the cause of there being no such disabling factors. Hence enables_RemovesDisablingFactors does not imply that the agent is in fact capable of doing a token of ACT_TYPE: it merely entails that no factor that would disable her is present. Note that in general this is a stronger notion than merely removing incapacitating factors. Example: giving an ax or a saw to a physically fit adult individual would typically enable him to chop down a tree in this sense, since in typical circumstances not having an ax would be disabling -- though perhaps not incapacitating. Complex events such as military tasks may also be regarded as typical examples of this concept -- e.g., in a ReliefInPlace_MilitaryTask the relieved unit is enabled in this sense to disengage and perform service support tasks.
label: Enables Removes Disabling Factors
enables-RemovesDisablingFactors

comment: (toFacetGLFArc NODE1 NODE2 SYSTEM ARC) means that ARC is the SOEFacetingArc that links NODE1 to NODE2 in SYSTEM, and that ARC has facets_Generic as its semantics.
label: To Facet GLF Arc
toFacetGLFArc

comment: (referencedAuthorOfPublication PERSON LITERARYWORK N) means that PERSON is one of the authors of LITERARYWORK, and is the Nth author credited in references to LITERARYWORK. For example, if ARTICLE's authors are referenced as 'SMITH, JONES, and BROWN,' then (referencedAuthorOfLiteraryWork-CW BROWN ARTICLE 3).
label: Referenced Author Of Publication
referencedAuthorOfPublication

comment: An assertion of the form (actFulfillsRecurringDistributedAssignmentForAgentForSubPeriod ACT ASSIGN AGENT INTERVAL) represents the fact that the Situation ACT satisfies the portion of ASSIGN, an instance of both DistributedAssignment and RegularlyRecurringAssignment, which represents the IntelligentAgent AGENT's obligation with regard to ASSIGN during the TimeInterval INTERVAL.
label: Act Fulfills Recurring Distributed Assignment For Agent For Sub Period
actFulfillsRecurringDistributedAssignmentForAgentForSubPeriod

comment: A ternary predicate. (capabilityToRoleSitType ROLE SIT-TYPE CAP) holds just in case CAP is the instance of Capability that is the capability to play ROLE in instances of SIT-TYPE. The is the corresponding predicate to CapabilityFn.
label: Capability To Role Sit Type
capabilityToRoleSitType

comment: An assertion of the form (relevanceInformingTerm TERM) is used to inform a Cyc inference of the appropriate term ranking to use. That is, when a Cyc query is run, all of the assertions using the predicate relevanceInformingTerm that are visible from the Microtheory in which that query is run will contribute to the calculation of the term ranking to be used by that query. More specifically, the instances of CycLTerm associated with relevanceInformingTerm will be equal valued in the weighting vector, while all other terms not associated will have a null value. The weight vector governs how new value enters into the term ranking, so terms that are inferentially related to terms that are relevanceInformingTerms will be more highly valued than those that are not.
label: Relevance Informing Term
relevanceInformingTerm

comment: (culturePrescribes_Categorical CULTURE ACTTYPE ROLE) means that within CULTURE it is considered good or proper or right to play ROLE in instances of ACTTYPE on a regular basis, and bad or improper or wrong not to do so. For example, some cultures consider it proper to make an offering to a deity each day. This does not entail, however, that CULTURE has a (hypothetical) prescription for playing ROLE in instances of ACTTYPE with respect to every possible condition; i.e. there might exist exceptional situations in which playing ROLE in an ACTTYPE is not prescribed (and might even be proscribed) by CULTURE. One might be temporarily exempted from the daily religious offering duty, for example, while engaged in a protracted military battle. This predicate applies equally to moral rules, rules of conduct or etiquette, and customs. See also culturePrescribes_Hypothetical, cultureProscribes_Categorical, and cultureProscribes_Hypothetical.
label: Culture Prescribes Categorical
culturePrescribes-Categorical

comment:
This predicate relates an IntegratingASetOfKnowledgeSources event with a LogicalField that is part of one of the input schemas and its corresponding logical field in the appropriate target schema. That is, (schemaIntegrationInputLFHasTargetLF INTEGRATION INPUT-LF TARGET-LF) means that:

1. INPUT-LF is a logical field in some ObjectDefiningSchema, INPUT-ODS;

2. INPUT-ODS is an element of some input schema set, INPUT-ODS-SET that is related to a target schema, TARGET-ODS, via schemaIntegrationInputODSSetHasTargetODS;

3. TARGET-LF is a logical field in TARGET-ODS;

4. INPUT-LF and TARGET-LF share the same field type and multiplicity. See logicalSchemaFieldOfTypeWithMultiplicity.

This predicate is used to determine the mapping from source schema meaning sentences to target schema meaning sentences.
label: Schema Integration Input LF Has Target LF
schemaIntegrationInputLFHasTargetLF

comment: (normalMarketSizeOfStockTypeInExchange STOCK-TYPE EXCHANGE NUM) holds just in case NUM which is the maximum number of shares of STOCK-TYPE that a market maker is obliged to deal in at the quoted price.
label: Normal Market Size Of Stock Type In Exchange
normalMarketSizeOfStockTypeInExchange

comment: (doLocalBufferOverflowAttack AGENT COMPUTER TARGET) means that AGENT performs a local buffer overflow attack on TARGET using COMPUTER. It is "local" in the sense that it does not exploit a program listening on a port on TARGET, but the program exploited must be running on TARGET. Cf. doRemoteBufferOverflowAttack.
label: Do Local Buffer Overflow Attack
doLocalBufferOverflowAttack

comment: A sentence of the form (wordSynonymStringsRankedNthForPOS WORD SET-OF-STRINGS RANK POS) means that a consultation of a WordNetKnowledgeBase using the LexicalWord WORD for the WordNetSpeechPart POS returned a ranked-list of sets of strings each representing the words that appear in a synset of WORD and that SET-OF-STRINGS with the Nth element of that list.
label: Word Synonym Strings Ranked Nth For POS
wordSynonymStringsRankedNthForPOS

comment: (kSHasFieldQueryReplacementPositionAndTransformation PS FIELD-NAME QUERY TRANSFORMATION) means that PS has a field with NAME with a value provided by QUERY that undergoes TRANSFORMATION in the encoding statement.
label: KS Has Field Query W Focal Arg Pos And Transformation
kSHasFieldQueryWFocalArgPosAndTransformation

comment: The corresponding predicate of the function StageSubSitRoleSpecFn.
label: Role Specification For Stage Sub Sit And Role
roleSpecificationForStageSubSitAndRole

comment: This predicate expresses the relationship between nouns, prepositions with which they co-occur, and the semantic interpretation of the noun and preposition together. Example: 'investment in IBM'
label: Noun Prep
nounPrep

comment: (interArgNotIsa2_4 PRED COL1 COL2) means that, when an instance of COL1 appears as the second argument to PRED, the fourth argument in that assertion is constrained to not be an instance of COL2 and vice versa.
label: Inter Arg Not Isa 2 4
interArgNotIsa2-4

comment: An assertion of the form (leastRequestedInstanceOfCollForOrgDuring INDIVIDUAL COLLECTION ORGANIZATION INTERVAL) is used to express the least 'in demand' element of a collection of resources for a particular organization during a particular time interval. So, INDIVDIUAL would be the instance of the FirstOrderCollection COLLECTION that the Organization has some rights over (i.e., employees) during the ContinuousTimeInterval INTERVAL. So, the assertion (leastRequestedInstanceOfCollForOrgDuring Joe #$CurrentCycorpEmployee Cycorp (MonthFn March (YearFn 2004))) would mean that Joe is the least requested instance of #$CurrentCycorpEmployee by Cycorp for March, 2004.
label: Least Requested Instance Of Coll For Org During
leastRequestedInstanceOfCollForOrgDuring

comment:
A specialization of followingValueOnScale (q.v.) that is used to compare the positions or "ranks" of adjacent quantities/attributes/properties on the same scale. More precisely, (succeedingValueOnScale VALUE1 VALUE2 SCALE) means that VALUE1 and VALUE2 are both instances of the CollectionWithAnEventLikeOrder SCALE, and that VALUE2 is the successor of (i.e. comes immediately after) VALUE1 in the ordering scheme conventionally associated with SCALE.

Typically, VALUE1 and VALUE2 will either (i) both be instances of Quantity (q.v.) or (ii) both be instances of FirstOrderCollection (q.v.) such that they correspond to properties of individuals. In case (i), SCALE will be a TotallyOrderedQuantityType, and (followingValue VALUE1 VALUE2) will hold.

For example, this holds: 

  (succeedingValueOnScale
    (MilitaryUnitTypeOfSizeFn Platoon_MilitaryEchelon)
    (MilitaryUnitTypeOfSizeFn Squad_MilitaryEchelon)
    MilitaryUnitTypeByEchelonSize) .
label: Succeeding Value On Scale
succeedingValueOnScale

comment: An expression of the form (orthogonalArgIsasWithLink PRED1 ARG1 PRED2 ARG2 COLL1 COLL2) means that the collection that is the argIsa value for the Predicate PRED1's ARG1th argument and the collection that is the argIsa value for the Predicate PRED2's ARG2th value are such that neither is a sub-collection of the other and are they are not disjoint. Further, COLL is the CollectionIntersectionFn of their arguments' constraining collections.
label: Orthogonal Arg Isas With Link
orthogonalArgIsasWithLink

comment: (amountForGenValueColAndPred VALUE PRED COL GVP) means that VALUE is the amount which is in the range of the quantity expressed by the NART '(RelativeGenericValueFn PRED COL GVP)'. Consider this example, Assertion A: (amountForGenValueColAndPred (Foot_UnitOfMeasure 6.5) heightOfObject BasketballPlayer highAmountOf). This means that 6.5 feet is subsumed by (GenValueFn heightOfObject BasketballPlayer highAmountOf). The NART itself is the quantity of height that is had by basketball players we consider "tall". So, such an assertion entails that 6.5 feet is tall for a basketball player. In other words, 6.5 is a high value on the slot heightOfObject for any BasketballPlayer.
label: Amount For Gen Value Col And Pred
amountForGenValueColAndPred

comment: (positivelyDependsOn SET DEP-PRED ?INDEP-PRED) means that the second arguments to DEP-PRED are positively dependent on those for INDEP-PRED, when elements of ?SET appear in the arg1 position. In other words, given the range of bindings for DEP-VAL and INDEP-VAL in (and (elementOf X SET)(DEP-PRED X DEP-VAL) (INDEP-PRED X INDEP-VAL)), whenever INDEP-VAL is high for a particular X, DEP-VAL will also be high and whenever INDEP-VAL is low, DEP-VAL will be low. Unlike the more general positivelyCorrelatedWith, positivelyDependsOn means that there is some causal link from INDEP-PRED affecting arg2 values for ?DEP-PRED. See also dependsOn_Pairwise.
label: Positively Depends On
positivelyDependsOn
Do Program Step Sequence
doProgramStepSequence
comment: A variable arity complex action predicate. (doProgramStepSequence PROGRAMMER FILE . STEPS) means that PROGRAMMER appends code to the end of FILE that implements STEPS, in the programming language determined by the current context. Each element of STEP is implemented in sequence.
arg1 has an authorized agreement of type arg2 that has id agr3 (e.g., (hasIDOfType Fred #$DriverLicense 15142515)).
label: Has ID Of Type
hasIDOfType

comment: An assertion of the form (literalHasConstantInArg LIT CONST N) states that the CycLConstant CONST is the value of the Nth argument in the (CycLObjectTypeFn CycLAtomicSentence )LIT.
label: Literal Has Constant In Arg
literalHasConstantInArg

comment:
(typeMinimizesTypeWRTType SIT-TYPE-1 SLOT SIT-TYPE-2)
holds just in case being the performer or doer of instances of SIT-TYPE-1 will tend to minimize the second argument of SLOT with respect to SIT-TYPE-2.
label: Type Minimizes Type WRT Type
typeMinimizesTypeWRTType

comment: (nearestDifferentGenlPreds PRED-1 PRED-2 NEAR-DIFF) relates predicates PRED-1 and PRED-2 to the nearest unsubsumed predicates NEAR-DIFF of which PRED-1 is a spec predicate but PRED-2 is not. nearestDifferentGenlPreds is notAssertible, since it must always be recomputed from the current state of the genlPreds hierarchy. For comparison, see nearestDifferentGenls.
label: Nearest Different Genl Preds
nearestDifferentGenlPreds

comment:
(resultGenlWhenArgIsa FN COLL NUM TYPE) means that when the NUMth argument to a well-formed application of the function FN is an instance of the collection TYPE, that application of FN will denote a subcollection of COLL.

For example, (resultGenlWhenArgIsa FlagFn NationalFlag 1 Country) means that any expression of the form (FlagFn AGENT) will denote a subcollection of NationalFlag if (isa AGENT Country).
label: Result Genl When Arg Isa
resultGenlWhenArgIsa

comment: An expression of the form (parsesStringToCycL EVT STRING CYCL) means that during the IBTTranslating EVT, the CharacterString STRING is parsed to the (quoted) CycLExpression CYCL.
label: Parses String To Cyc L
parsesStringToCycL

comment: Performing instances of ARG1 in role ARG2 is popular (to the degree ARG4) to instances of ARG3.
label: Popularity Of Activity
popularityOfActivity

comment: (explains_RelationTo BINARY-PRED SIT VALUE) means that (BINARY-PRED SIT VALUE) is true and in some way helps explain SIT. The notion of explanation at work here is very general. So, (BINARY-PRED SIT VALUE) might help explain the *occurrence* of SIT, e.g., by citing one of its causes or precipitating events. Or, (BINARY-PRED SIT VALUE) may help explain the *signficance* of SIT (cf., signifies and related predicates).
label: Explains Relation To
explains-RelationTo

comment: (grievanceInDispute DISPUTE AGENT ISSUE) means that ISSUE is a grievance or complaint which is prompting AGENT to be involved in DISPUTE. 'Grievances' as understood here can be involved in both formal and informal conflicts (lawsuits, physical confrontations, etc.). ISSUE can be a state of affairs that AGENT wishes to change -- e.g., an agent's complaint in a lawsuit or contract dispute -- or a state of affairs with respect to which AGENT is seeking revenge, restitution, punishment, etc. In the case of the U.S. criminal justice system, a charge against a defendant can be considered a 'grievance' of the prosecuting agent.
label: Grievance In Dispute
grievanceInDispute

comment: The predicate corresponding to DrivingTimeBetweenFn. (drivingTimeBetween PLACE1 PLACE2 DURATION) means that according to the Google Maps website, the approximate driving time between PLACE1 and PLACE2 is DURATION.
label: Driving Time Between
drivingTimeBetween

comment: An expression of the form (#$disJointArgGenls PRED1 ARG1 PRED2 ARG2) means that the collection that is the value for the Predicate PRED1's ARG1th argument is a type of collection, such that it is incompatible with the values for PRED2's ARG2th argument. This predicate does not assume that PRED2's ARG2th argument also takes a collection as a value.
label: Incompatible Arg Genls
incompatibleArgGenls

comment: (resemblesInValue THING1 THING2 COLL) means that the two things THING1 and THING2 resemble each other in their values of the collection type COLL. Here 'resembles' means has a "close" or similar value in that property -- what this means, and what the standard of closeness or similarity is, depends on the context. At the very least, THING1 and THING2 will both be instances of some instance of COLL. If COLL is an instance of CollectionWithAnEventLikeOrder, then it is likely the resemblance consists in each being an instance of some instance of COLL and the collections they belong to are "close" to each other in the ordering on COLL. See also identicalInValue and differentInValue. For similar predicates that utilize specializations of Quantity in the third argument place see resemblesInQuantity, identicalInQuantity, and differentInQuantity.
label: Resembles In Value
resemblesInValue

comment:
This predicate relates a translational movement event to the distance travelled by the objectMoving in that event in some particular direction. (displacementInDirection MOVE DIST DIRECTION) means that at the end of the event MOVE, the objectMoving is distance DIST away from its original position in the direction DIRECTION.

For example (displacementInDirection Movement001 (Meter 400) Horizontal_Generally) could be true of a projectile launched from the top of a building, even if the total distance travelled by the projectile is over (Meter 500) because the projectile also happened to fall downward a distance of (Meter 300). In that case, (displacementInDirection Movement001 (Meter 300) Down_Directly) would be true and the total distance travelled by the projectile could be over 500 meters (see distanceTranslated).
label: Displacement In Direction
displacementInDirection

comment: A predicate used to identify subcollections that are important exception-classes to default truths about a more general collection. (exceptionalSpecWRTSlot SPEC GENL SLOT) says that SPEC is an exception to (relationAllInstance SLOT GENL VALUE), whatever the value is of VALUE. So for example, as a default, we might assert (relationAllInstance numberOfInningsPlayed BaseballGame 9). But we might also wish to assert (relationAllInstance numberOfInningsPlayed LittleLeagueBaseballGame 6), where (genls LittleLeagueBaseballGame BaseballGame). Cyc's behavior will be to use the assertion on LittleLeagueBaseballGame to override the assertion on BaseballGame, treating LittleLeagueBaseballGame as an exception-sub-class of BaseballGame with respect to numberOfInningsPlayed: (exceptionalSpecWRTSlot LittleLeagueBaseballGame BaseballGame numberOfInningsPlayed).
label: Exceptional Spec WRT Slot
exceptionalSpecWRTSlot

comment: The amount (mass, volume, amount of money, whatever) moving in a MovingProcess.
label: Amount Moving
amountMoving

comment: (necConditionFor_Ternary SCRIPT EVENT-TYPE1 EVENT-TYPE2) means that in the #$ScriptedEventType SCRIPT, EVENT-TYPE1 is a causally necessary condition for EVENT-TYPE2. This means that if an instance INS2 of EVENT-TYPE2 is part of an instantiation S of SCRIPT, then INS2 will start after INS1 -- an instance of EVENT-TYPE1 that instance is also part of S. This is a ternary version of the binary predicate necConditionFor_Events -- (necConditionFor_Ternary SCRIPT EVENT-TYPE1 EVENT-TYPE2) is equivalent to (necConditionFor_Events (#$SceneFn SCRIPT EVENT-TYPE1) (#$SceneFn SCRIPT EVENT-TYPE2)). See necConditionFor_Events for more information.
label: Nec Condition For Ternary
necConditionFor-Ternary

comment: (planResourceQuantForTime PLAN STUFFTYPE QUANT TEMPTYPE) means that in an execution of PLAN the executing agent needs to have control of quantity QUANT of some stuff of type STUFFTYPE for the duration of an event of type TEMPTYPE in the plan execution, in order for the execution to be successfulForAgents.--Rode, May 26, 1999
label: Plan Resource Quant For Time
planResourceQuantForTime

comment: (exportsThrough REGION PRODUCT-TYPE PT) means that the GeographicalRegion REGION exports significant amounts of instances of the ProductType PRODUCT-TYPE through the instance of PartiallyTangible PT on their way to their destination. PT might, in the case of oil exports, for example, be a GeographicalRegion or a Pipeline.
label: Exports Through
exportsThrough

comment: (comparableFluents OBJ F(X) G(X)) states that the order of magnitude of F(OBJ) is also the order of magnitude of G(OBJ). Another way of thinking of it is that F(OBJ) and G(OBJ) are of comparable orders of magnitude, and neither one is negligible with respect to the other.
label: Comparable Fluents
comparableFluents

comment: (numberOfErrorsOfType SET ERR-TYPE NUM) means that the number of errors in SET that are members of #$Malfunction ERR-TYPE is NUM.
label: Number Of Errors Of Type
numberOfErrorsOfType

comment: (secondVADInsertOfOperationHasOrganTransplantAtDate INDEX-OP INSERT TRANSPLANT-OP DATE) means that the operation INDEX-OP has INSERT as its second VAD insertion, and TRANSPLANT-OP is a cardiac transplant that occurs after INSERT (and is performed on the same patient as INSERT).
label: Third VAD Insert Of Operation Has Organ Transplant At Date
thirdVADInsertOfOperationHasOrganTransplantAtDate

comment: (doInstallMaliciousProgramOfType AGENT MALPROGRAMTYPE COMPUTER) means that AGENT installs, with or without permission, an instance of MALPROGRAMTYPE on COMPUTER.
label: Do Install Malicious Program Of Type
doInstallMaliciousProgramOfType

comment: (fileTypeRelativeBasePath APP FILETYPE PATH) means that the default directory location for storing files of type FILETYPE managed by APP on COMPUTER can be determined by appending PATH to BASEPATH, where (applicationBasePath APP COMPUTER BASEPATH).
label: File Type Relative Base Path
fileTypeRelativeBasePath

comment: (assistedReaderSourceSpindleHeadForTaskAndUser TASK USER MT) means that MT is the Microtheory that is the head (see mtSpindleHead) of the MicrotheorySpindle designed to hold source microtheories whose contents are authored using the CycAssistedDocumentReader by USER while working on TASK.
label: Assisted Reader Source Spindle Head For Task And User
assistedReaderSourceSpindleHeadForTaskAndUser

comment:
A quaternary RuleMacroPredicate that is used to state that a given binary predicate holds between a specified number of instances of a given collection and a given thing. (relationExistsCountInstance BINPRED COL THING N) means that there are exactly N instances (INST(1), ..., INST(N)) of COL such that (BINPRED INST(i) THING) holds (for 0 <= i <= N). It is equivalent to (and so can be used in effect as shorthand for) the more complex form:

(thereExistExactly N ?INST (and (isa ?INST COL) (BINPRED ?INST THING))) .

For example, (relationExistsCountInstance authorOfLiteraryWork_CW Person Waverley 1) means that there is exactly one author of Waverley. Cf.relationInstanceExistsCount, and see the shared #$NoteAboutUseOfRuleMacroPredicates.
label: Relation Exists Count Instance
relationExistsCountInstance
Use Reformulation Rule For Type Shifting
useReformulationRuleForTypeShifting
comment: (useReformulationRuleForTypeShifting RULE) indicates that RULE will be used by the TypeShiftingRLModule.

(makesMoreVulnerableThan_Object THREAT-OBJ1 THREAT-OBJ2 OBJECT HARM-TYPE) means that THREAT-OBJ1 increases the vulnerability of OBJECT to results of type HARM-TYPE more than THREAT-OBJ2 does. OBJECT is presumably vulnerable to both THREAT-OBJ1 and THREAT-OBJ2. Note also that this is an instance level predicate, although the last argument is a type of situation. For restrictions on HARM-TYPE see vulnerableTo.
label: Makes More Vulnerable Than Object
makesMoreVulnerableThan-Object

comment: If PLACE isa TYPE, has latitude LAT and longitude LON, then (featureOfTypeLocatedInBoundingBoxWithCoordinates PLACE LAT-MAX LON-MIN LAT-MIN LON-MAX) is true precisely if (LAT-MAX > LAT > LAT-MIN) and (LON-MAX > LON > LON-MIN).
label: Feature Of Type Located In Bounding Box With Coordinates
featureOfTypeLocatedInBoundingBoxWithCoordinates

comment: A ternary RelativeLocationalPredicate that relates a SpatialThing to a CartesianCoordinateSystem to a ScalarInterval. (positionAlongXAxisInCoordinateSystem OBJECT SYSTEM POSITION) means that the position of OBJECT along the x axis of SYSTEM (see xAxisPredicateOfSystem) is POSITION.
label: Position Along X Axis In Coordinate System
positionAlongXAxisInCoordinateSystem

comment: This is the type-constrained version of thereExistsRolePlayer. (thereExistsRolePlayerOfType SIT-TYPE SUBSIT-TYPE ROLE TYPE) means that in any instance of SUBSIT-TYPE that is a subSituations of SIT-TYPE, there is an instance of TYPE that plays ROLE.
label: There Exists Role Player Of Type
thereExistsRolePlayerOfType

comment: (packetTypeFirewallTarget PACKET-TYPE-BY-DIRECTION PACKET-TYPE-BY-PORT FW TARGET) means that packets of type PACKET-TYPE-BY-PORT and PACKET-TYPE-BY-DIRECTION are assigned the attribute TARGET by a firewall program running on FW. For example, (packetTypeFirewallTarget (OutgoingWRTLANFn #$CycorpLAN) Packet_Internet #$Helmet-Cyc-Com Deny_FirewallTarget) means that helmet drops all IP packets that are outgoing with respect to the Cycorp LAN. Again, for example, (packetTypeFirewallTarget (DestinationIPFn "208.209.34.175") (DestinationPortFn TransmissionControlProtocol 80) #$Helmet-Cyc-Com Accept_FirewallTarget) means that helmet does not filter TCP packets bound for port 80 on 208.209.34.175.
label: Packet Type Firewall Target
packetTypeFirewallTarget

comment: (sententialPhraseForVerbWithFrame_Generic VERB FRAME PHRASE) means that PHRASE is NLSentence which exemplifies VERB being used with the SubcategorizationFrame FRAME. PHRASE is generic and includes keywords for grammatical role fillers.
label: Sentential Phrase For Verb With Frame Generic
sententialPhraseForVerbWithFrame-Generic

comment: A ternary instance of InterArgIsaPredicate (q.v.). (interArgIsa5_4 RELN INDEPENDENT-ARG-COL DEPENDENT-ARG-COL) means that, when an instance of INDEPENDENT-ARG-COL appears as the fifth argument to RELN, a necessary condition for semantic well-formedness is that the fourth argument must be an instance of DEPENDENT-ARG-COL. That is, if INST is an instance of INDEPENDENT-ARG-COL, then (RELN ARG1 ARG2 ARG3 ARG4 INST ... ARGN) is semantically well-formed only if ARG4 is an instance of DEPENDENT-ARG-COL. For an explanation of semantic well-formedness, see CycLExpression_Assertible and its direct specializations.
label: Inter Arg Isa 5 4
interArgIsa5-4

comment: (levelOfExposureToSubstanceType EVENT TANGIBLE STUFF LEVEL) says that the PartiallyTangible object TANGIBLE has been exposed to LEVEL degree of STUFF. For example (levelOfExposureToSubstanceType #$WorldWarII CityBlock005 RadioactiveStuff (HighAmountFn LevelOfExposure)) says that during WWII, city block 005 underwent a high level of exposure to some radioactive material.
label: Level Of Exposure To Substance Type
levelOfExposureToSubstanceType
Use Reformulation Rule For VPP Processing State Verbs
useReformulationRuleForVPPProcessing-StateVerbs
comment: (useReformulationRuleForVPPProcessing_NonStateVerbs RULE) indicates that RULE will be used by the VPPProcessingStateRLModule.

A generalization of followingValueOnScale (q.v.) that is used to compare the positions or "ranks" of quantities/attributes/properties that are on the same scale. More precisely, (followingOrEqualValueOnScale VALUE1 VALUE2 SCALE) means that VALUE1 and VALUE2 are both instances of the CollectionWithAnEventLikeOrder (q.v.) SCALE, and that VALUE2 is "greater than or equal to" (i.e. comes no earlier than) VALUE1 in the ordering scheme conventionally associated with SCALE.

Typically, VALUE1 and VALUE2 will either (i) both be instances of Quantity (q.v.) or (ii) both be instances of FirstOrderCollection (q.v.) such that they correspond to properties of individuals. In case (i), SCALE will be a TotallyOrderedQuantityType and, if VALUE1 and VALUE2 are not identical, (followingValue VALUE1 VALUE2) will also hold.

For example, all of these hold: 

  (followingOrEqualValueOnScale MildlyToxic MildlyToxic Toxicity)

  (followingOrEqualValueOnScale
    Corporal_Rank Sergeant_Rank USArmyRank) 

  (followingOrEqualValueOnScale 
    TwoDimensionalThing
    PolyDimensionalThing
    SpatialThingTypeByDimensionality)  .
label: Following Or Equal Value On Scale
followingOrEqualValueOnScale

comment: (consumptionCapacity PT PRODUCT-TYPE RATE) means that the Rate RATE is the greatest possible rate at which instances of the ProductType PRODUCT-TYPE could be consumed by the instance of PartiallyTangible PT. PT might, for example, be a Country or a Business.
label: consumption capacity
consumptionCapacity

comment: (inconsistentWithMts SENTENCE MT-1 MT-2) means that addition of SENTENCE to the union the microtheories MT-1 and MT-2 renders that union inconsistent. inconsistentWithMts is thus a rule macro predicate, shorthand for (inconsistentWithMt SENTENCE (MtUnionFn MT-1 MT-2)).
label: Inconsistent With Mts
inconsistentWithMts

comment: (importsFromThrough REGION1 PRODUCT-TYPE REGION2 PT) means that the GeographicalRegion REGION1 imports significant amounts of instances of the ProductType PRODUCT-TYPE from the GeographicalRegion REGION2 through the instance of PartiallyTangible PT on their way from REGION2. PT might, in the case of oil imports, for example, be a GeographicalRegion or a Pipeline.
label: Imports From Through
importsFromThrough

comment: (siblingsWithRespectToType THING1 THING2 TYPE) means that THING1 and THING2 share a common nearestIsaOfType TYPE.
label: Siblings With Respect To Type
siblingsWithRespectToType

comment: An instance of TernaryPredicate. glfComponentSemanticsWRTGraph is used to relate an instance of GLFGraphComponent to the object it denotes in the context of an instance of Graph_CW for which that component is part of the graph's structure. For example, (glfComponentSemanticsWRTGraph GLFNODE002 (CycQueryRunningFromFn VegetationConcealsDefenderFromLOSFlanksQuerySpec) GLFGRAPH002) says that in the graph GLFGRAPH002, GLFNODE002 represents the running of the query, VegetationConcealsDefenderFromLOSFlanksQuerySpec).
label: Glf Component Semantics WRT Graph
glfComponentSemanticsWRTGraph

comment: This predicate specifies the direction in which a given quantity changes in a given time period. (changesQuantityInDirection TIME THING SLOT DIRECTION) means that during TIME, THING's QuantitySlot SLOT changes in DIRECTION. TIME is a TemporalThing, and AMOUNT is a LevelOfChange. If DIRECTION is #$Positive, this denotes an increase (changesQuantityInDirection (YearFn 1980) SaudiArabia oilExport #$Positive) means that in 1980, Saudi Arabia's oil export increased. For predicates specifying amounts of change, see: changesQuantityByFraction, changesQuantityByAmount. See also quantityChangeFunction to describe qualitative aspects of a quantity change, e.g. a spike, net decreasing, curvilinear, or slow change.
label: Changes Quantity In Direction
changesQuantityInDirection

comment: A predicate relating instances of Firewall_Network with instances of Computer in the firewall's network. (filtersPacketType FIREWALL PACKTYPE COMPUTER) means that FIREWALL drops all packets of type PACKTYPE coming from outside the network bound for COMPUTER.
label: Filters Packet Type
filtersPacketType

comment: The corresponding predicate of ElectionForPositionInPolityFn.
label: Election For Position In Polity
electionForPositionInPolity

comment: (typesGreaterInValue COL1 COL2 COLL-TYPE) means that instances of COL1 are instances of instances of COLL-TYPE that are higher in the standard ordering of COLL-TYPE than the instance of COLL-TYPE of which COL2's instances are instances. In other words, every instance of COL1 is related to a higher value of COLL-TYPE that every instance of COL2. Example: (typesGreaterInValue Lawyer Janitor PersonTypeByEducationLevel) means that the education level of lawyers is greater than that of janitors (default true).
label: Types Greater In Value
typesGreaterInValue

comment: powerInOrganization specifies the amount of influence or sway that AGENT has in ORG. (powerInOrganization AGENT ORG GENERIC-VALUE) means that AGENT's level of influence in ORG is GENERIC-VALUE.
label: Power In Organization
powerInOrganization

comment: (mainConstituentAmount_Type OBJ-TYPE1 OBJ-TYPE2 AMOUNT) means that instances of OBJ-TYPE1 have amount AMOUNT of OBJ-TYPE2 as a main constituent.
label: Main Constituent Amount Type
mainConstituentAmount-Type

comment: An assertion of the form (allotmentWhollyReservesIndForInterval ALLOT INDIVIDUAL INTERVAL) is used to relate an instance of Allotment to an Individual and a TimeInterval. This refers to the particular interval which is being reserved and has the implication that there cannot be another Allotment that lays some claim to INDIVIDUAL during INTERVAL.
label: Allotment Wholly Reserves Ind For Interval
allotmentWhollyReservesIndForInterval

comment: (counterClockwise POINT-1 POINT-2 POINT-3) means that the straight line traversal originating at POINT-1, passing through POINT-2, and terminating at POINT-3 is in the counterclockwise direction.
label: counterclockwise
counterClockwise

comment: The predicate anatomicallyCapableOf indicates that an agent is anatomically able to play a certain role in a certain type of situation or event. (anatomicallyCapableOf AGENT SIT-TYPE ROLE) means that an individual EmbodiedAgent AGENT has the anatomical prerequisites (natural or prosthetic) needed to play ROLE in normal instances of SIT-TYPE. We mean 'anatomical' to be construed fairly broadly in this case. Strictly speaking, 'anatomical' may mean 'pertaining to the structures of organisms (e.g. the structures of plants or animals)'. In the case of this predicate, however, 'anatomical' means 'pertaining to the physical structures of embodied agents. Thus androids and even non-humanoid robots can be considered to have anatomical capabilities. Note that anatomicallyCapableOf is different inmeaning from physicallyCapableOf (q.v.). For instance, (anatomicallyCapableOf MarthaThePassengerPigeon Flying_FlappingWings doneBy), but if Martha were caged, then (not (physicallyCapableOf MarthaThePassengerPigeon Flying_FlappingWings doneBy)).
label: Anatomically Capable Of
anatomicallyCapableOf

comment: (relationToDuringRelationTo OBJECT BIN-PRED-1 INDIVIDUAL1 BIN-PRED-2 INDIVIDUAL2) means that the TimeInterval during which the proposition (BIN-PRED-1 OBJECT INDIVIDUAL1) holds at least partly overlaps the TimeInterval during which the proposition (BIN-PRED-2 OBJECT INDIVIDUAL2) holds. In other words, the two propositions hold during intersecting TimeIntervals (see temporallyIntersects). Since relationToDuringRelationTo is a query-only predicate used to compare the time indices of temporally-qualified assertions, BIN-PRED-1 and BIN-PRED-2 are restricted to TemporallyQualifiableRelations
label: Relation To During Relation To
relationToDuringRelationTo

comment: A sentence of the form (touchesAtDuring OBJ1 OBJ2 POINT EVENT) states that during the ContinuousPhysicalContactSituation EVENT, the two instances of PartiallyTangible OBJ1 and OBJ2 are in physical contact throughout EVENT and the Point POINT is subsumed by that region of contact .
label: Touches At During
touchesAtDuring

comment: A ternary complex action predicate. (doProgramCondition PROGRAMMER FILE CONDITION) means that PROGRAMMER appends code to the end of FILE which evaluates CONDITION and maps into the boolean space of the contextual programming language. For example, the conditional expressions of the "if" or "while" statements of many languages.
label: Do Program Condition
doProgramCondition
Do Initialize Local Variables
doInitializeLocalVariables
comment: A variable arity complex action predicate. (doInitializeLocalVariables PROGRAMMER FILE . VARIABLES) means that PROGRAMMER appends code that declares and initializes VARIABLES to the end of computer file FILE.

(doConnectRemotelyToProgramOnComputer AGENT PROGRAM COMPUTER) means that AGENT sets up a remote connection to the ServerProgram PROGRAM on the Computer COMPUTER (by sending packets to whatever port the program is listening on). See also doConnectRemotelyToProgramOnSystem.
label: Do Connect Remotely To Program On Computer
doConnectRemotelyToProgramOnComputer

comment: (increases_Generic TEMP-THING THING SLOT) means that the value of the predicate SLOT applied to THING (in the second argument position) is greater over some time period after the start of TEMP-THING. Compared with its value immediately before TEMP-THING, the value of SLOT applied to THING will be higher immediately following or some time after the start of TEMP-THING. This is the most generic of the SlotTrendPredicates relating to increasing of a given instance of QuantitySlot. The increase may be caused by TEMP-THING, but need not be. It may occur immediately, or over a period of time following TEMP-THING. For GAFs, or in the consequents of rules dealing with increased quantities, use the more specific predicates if possible. See #$NoteAboutQuantityChangePredicates for a map of related predicates.
label: Increases-Generic
increases-Generic

comment: (#$queingCost MARKET PRODUCT COST) identifies COST as the real monetary value of having to endure a shortage-induced delay in access to PRODUCT in MARKET. To offset COST individuals in the market may be tempted to enter a black market (see BlackMarket) to get access to PRODUCT.
label: queuing cost
queuingCost

comment: (titleOfPosition POSITION ORG STRING) means that people that have the position POSITION in ORG have the title STRING. For example, (titleOfPosition HeadOfState (GovernmentFn UnitedStatesOfAmerica) 'president').
label: Title Of Position
titleOfPosition

comment: An instance of StrictlyFunctionalPredicate. (organizationHasFacilityWithAddress ORGANIZATION FACILITY ADDRESS-TEXT) identifies FACILITY as the instance of ContactLocation that is a facility (see orgFacilities) of the instance of Organization ORGANIZATION with the address denoted by ADDRESS-TEXT.
label: Organization Has Facility With Address
organizationHasFacilityWithAddress

comment: (structureMapAnyMt ?Src ?Tgt ?Src-Desc ?Tgt-Desc) returns a structure-mapping of the formulae in ?Src-Mt pertaining to the source concept ?Src that are isomorphic with formulae in ?Tgt-Mt that pertain to the target domain concept ?Tgt. The mappings are condensed as formulae, so ?Src-Desc becomes bound to an and of all the matching formulae in the source domain, while ?Tgt-Desc becomes bound to an and of all the matching formulae in the target domain. See also structureMap, a version of this predicate in which the structure-mapping process is restricted to axioms available in specified microtheories only.
label: Structure Map Any Mt
structureMapAnyMt
Xsd:double
xsd:double
comment: xsd:double is an imported RDFS/XML term equivalent to the Cyc term SubLRealNumber

(projectedKETimePerPeriod CYCLIST PROJECT KE-TIME PERIOD) means that PERSON is expected to spend KE-TIME amount of time per PERIOD doing knowledge entry for PROJECT. For example, (#$projectedKETimePerWeek #$BillMathews #$TKBProject (HoursDuration 30 40) (WeeksDuration 1)) means that Bill Mathews is expected to spend 30 to 40 hours each week doing knowledge entry for the TKB project.
label: Projected KE Time Per Period
projectedKETimePerPeriod

comment: The thing ARG2 is chosen in the event ARG1, for the  expression ARG3 to hold.  It is possible that ARG3 never becomes  true, but it is the intent of the chooser(s)
label: Chosen For
chosenFor
Program Algorithm Outputs
programAlgorithmOutputs
comment: (programAlgorithmOutputs ALGORITHM . OUTPUTS) relates ALGORITHM to the list OUTPUTS of the relevant instances of #$IndexicalComputationalTerm that are outputs to the algorithmic process.

A quaternary predicate relating a logical schema, logical field, collection, and integer. (logicalSchemaFieldOfTypeWithMultiplicity SCHEMA FIELD TYPE N) means that:

1. FIELD is a logical field of SCHEMA (See logicalFields);

2. FIELD is of type TYPE (See fieldIsa);

3. FIELD is the Nth field in SCHEMA of type TYPE.

See also the function corresponding to the second argument of this predicate, LogicalFieldFn.
label: Logical Schema Field Of Type With Multiplicity
logicalSchemaFieldOfTypeWithMultiplicity

comment: (nearestTransitiveNeighbor PRED TERM NEAR-TERM) relates any transitive binary predicate PRED and a TERM to those other NEAR-TERMs that are the nearest in the following sense: (PRED TERM NEAR-TERM) holds and there is no other instance BETWEEN distinct from TERM and NEAR-TERM such that both (PRED TERM BETWEEN) and (PRED BETWEEN NEAR-TERM) hold. nearestTransitiveNeighbor generalizes the functionality of nearestGenls, nearestGenlMt and others to any transitive binary predicate. Note that this predicate is notAssertible, since it must be recomputed from the transitive hierarchy generated by PRED.
label: Nearest Transitive Neighbor
nearestTransitiveNeighbor

comment: An instance of TernaryPredicate used to represent a dispositional property of substance-types. (vaporPressureOfTypeAtTemperature STUFF PRESSURE TEMPERATURE) says that at the Temperature TEMPERATURE,the pressure of a sample of (GaseousFn STUFF) that is in equilibrium with a liquid or solid sample of STUFF will be PRESSURE. (To represent the actual pressure of a particular sample of gas, see barometricPressure).
label: Vapor Pressure Of Type At Temperature
vaporPressureOfTypeAtTemperature

comment: (nothingBetweenOfType REFERENT THING COL) means that there does not exist any instance of COL that is between THING and REFERENT.
label: Nothing Between Of Type
nothingBetweenOfType

comment: (numOfTypeDamagedInAttack ATTACK TYPE NUM) says that during ATTACK, NUM instances of TYPE were damaged.
label: Num Of Type Damaged In Attack
numOfTypeDamagedInAttack

comment: (eventErrorRateForType ERR-TYPE EVT-TYPE AGT-TYPE RATE) means that in normal circumstances in which EVT-TYPE is done by AGT-TYPE, the ratio of the number of errors of type ERR-TYPE to the number of events of type EVT-TYPE is RATE. For example, (eventErrorRateForType EngineMisFiring EngineFiring FordV-6Engine .0001) means that the ratio of engine misfirings to the total number of engine firings is 1 in a thousand, when the engine firing is done by a Ford V-6 engine.
label: Event Error Rate For Type
eventErrorRateForType

comment: (nthInteractionOfSession INTERACTION SESSION N) says that in the ComputerUserInteraction SESSION, INTERACTION is the Nth sub-event that is an instance of ComputerUserInteraction in its own right.
label: Nth Interaction Of Session
nthInteractionOfSession

comment: (relationExistsExistsSpec PRED COL1 COL2) means that there exists a subcollection of COL2, SUBCOL2, such that there exists an instance of COL1, INS1, such that (PRED INS1 SUBCOL2).
label: Relation Exists Exists Spec
relationExistsExistsSpec

comment: (interArgGenlIsa2_1 REL VAL COL) means that whenever a specialization of VAL is in the second argument place of REL, an instance of COL must be in the first place.
label: Inter Arg Genl Isa 2 1
interArgGenlIsa2-1

comment: (productionRateOfRegion REGION PRODUCT-TYPE RATE) means that PRODUCT-TYPE is produced within REGION at the rate of RATE.
label: regional production rate
productionRateOfRegion

comment: The predicate that corresponds to (see functionCorrespondsToPredicate) NthTermInOrgRoleFn, (agentNthTermInOrgRole AGENT N TERM ORG ROLE) means that TERM is the Nth instance of TermOfService in which AGENT served as/played the role of ROLE in the organization ORG.
label: Agent Nth Term In Org Role
agentNthTermInOrgRole

comment: a simplification predicate. (patchFixesSoftwareFaultOf PATCH FAULT SOFTWARE-OBJECT) holds just in case there exists a DATABASE and ID-STRING such that (#$patchFixesFaultOf PATCH FAULT DATABASE ID-STRING SOFTWARE-OBJECT).
label: Patch Fixes Software Fault Of
patchFixesSoftwareFaultOf
Backchain Discouraged
backchainDiscouraged
comment: (backchainDiscouraged PREDICATE) means that rules that conclude PREDICATE are most likely not going to have to be used in order to prove literals involving PREDICATE. In other words, when performing inferences about literals involving PREDICATE, rules that conclude PREDICATE should be heuristically disfavored. See also backchainRequired, backchainEncouraged, and backchainForbidden.

A loxodrome, also known as a rhumb line, is a curve which crosses the meridians for the axis of some surface of revolution (see meridianForAxisOfSurfaceOfRevolution) at any constant angular distance (in degrees) A such that -90 < A < 0 or 0 < A < 90. We rule out the case where A = 0 degrees, since this case corresponds to the meridians of the surface (for some axis of revolution), and we rule out the case where A = 90 degrees, since this case corresponds to the parallels of the surface (for some axis of revolution). In Cyc, (loxodromeForAxisOfSurfaceOfRevolution LOXODROME AXIS SURFACE) means the LOXODROME is such a curve with respect to the axis of revolution AXIS for the surface of revolution SURFACE.
label: rhumb line
loxodromeForAxisOfSurfaceOfRevolution

comment: (prepSemTrans PREP INT FRAME TRANS) means that the translation of word sense number INT of PREP in frame FRAME is TRANS.
label: Prep Sem Trans
prepSemTrans

comment: (patientMinimalYearAgeDuringMedicalEvent PAT EVT TIME-QUANTITY) means that the MedicalPatient PAT is at least TIME-QUANTITY old at the time of the start of the event EVT. Typically, the units are expressed in YearsDuration.
label: years or older
patientMinimalYearAgeDuringMedicalEvent

comment: (inheritRolePlayers_SitTypeToSubSitType_Unique SIT-TYPE SIT-TYPE-ROLE SUBSIT-TYPE SUBSIT-TYPE-ROLE) means that in any instance of SIT-TYPE whatever single entity plays SIT-TYPE-ROLE is identical to the entity that plays SUBSIT-TYPE-ROLE in the instance of SUBSIT-TYPE.
label: Inherit Role Players Sit Type To Sub Sit Type Unique
inheritRolePlayers-SitTypeToSubSitType-Unique
subPropertyOf: Inherit Role Players Sit Type To Sub Sit Type

comment: A TemporallyQualifiableRelation. An assertion of the form (agentEstimatedRemainingWorkForSpec AGENT QUANT SPEC) states that according to the IntelligentAgent AGENT, AGENT will need to work for the Time_Quantity QUANT, in order to complete his or her work relative to the realization of the NormativeSpecification SPEC.
label: Agent Estimated Remaining Work For Spec
agentEstimatedRemainingWorkForSpec

comment: (rateOfActionForChemicalType CHEMICAL-TYPE ORG-TYPE TIME-QUANTITY) means that the rate of action for CHEMICAL-TYPE in the body of ORG-TYPE is TIME-QUANTITY. The rate of action for a chemical substance is the time it takes to affect an organism.
label: Rate Of Action For Chemical Type
rateOfActionForChemicalType

comment: (mapsToTaxonomyRelnStartingAt TAXON KBPRED TAXPRED TERM1) means that assertions of the form (KBPRED TERM1 TERM2) will appear in TAXON as (TAXPRED TERM1 TERM2). For example, (mapsToTaxonomyRelnStartingAt #$FoodAndDrinkTaxonomy partTypes parts_Underspecified FoodComposite) means that TERMs such that (partTypes FoodComposite TERM) will appear in the food and drink taxonomy as (parts-Underspecified FoodComposite TERM).
label: Maps To Taxonomy Reln Starting At
mapsToTaxonomyRelnStartingAt

comment: Where FORMULA is a CycLFormula with a single open variable, (wouldBeEvidenceForIsa CAND-INST CAND-COL FORMULA) means that if the sentence that results from substituting CAND-INST for the variable in FORMULA were known to be true, it would constitute at least weak, prima facia evidence for believing (isa CAND-INST CAND-COL).
label: Would Be Evidence For Isa
wouldBeEvidenceForIsa

comment: (prefersToRelnA AGENT PREF-COL DISPREF-COL RELN) means that AGENT prefers to be in the relation RELN (expressed by a BinaryPredicate) to some element of the collection PREF-COL over some element of the collection DISPREF-COL.
label: Prefers To Reln A
prefersToRelnA

comment: (resultIsaArgIsaType FUNC N COL-TYPE) means that the NAT resulting from a use of FUNC is a member of the same collections that the term in arg N is a member of, where these collections are constrained to be members of the collection type COL-TYPE. For example: (resultIsaArgIsaType MotherFn 1 BiologicalTaxon) means that if CHILD is an instances of TAXON which is an instance of BiologicalTaxon, then (MotherFn CHILD) is also an instance of TAXON. But resultIsaArgIsa won't do because the mother won't be a member of *all* of the collections that her child will be a member of, e.g. MaleAnimal or Mule. In this case we need to make a resultIsaArgIsaType assertion to constrain the resulting NAT to be a member of a specific subset of the collections the child is a member of, in this case, those that are instances of BiologicalTaxon. Then, if (isa CHILD EquineAnimal), (isa (MotherFn CHILD) EquineAnimal) as well.
label: Result Isa Arg Isa Type
resultIsaArgIsaType

comment: (verbSemTransPartialTemplate COL FRAME TRANS) means that the partial translation of any verb denotation of a word denoting a specialization of COL, appearing with subcategorization frame FRAME, is TRANS.
label: Verb Sem Trans Partial Template
verbSemTransPartialTemplate

comment:
A MetaPredicate that is a generalization of transitiveViaArg (q.v.) in that it can take any binary predicate (transitive or not) as its second argument. (conservativeViaArg PRED RELN N) means that if both of these hold: 
  (PRED ... ARGN ... )

  (RELN ARGN NEW-ARGN),

then so does 

  (PRED ... NEW-ARGN ...)
(where the argument-sequence ... NEW-ARGN ... is just like ... ARGN ... except for having NEW-ARGN in place of ARGN).

Note that if RELN is a TransitiveBinaryPredicate, the more specialized transitiveViaArg can be used instead. See also conservativeViaArgInverse.
label: Conservative Via Arg
conservativeViaArg
subPropertyOf: Ke Relation Strengthens Via Arg Inverse

comment: (industryOfRegion LOCAL-INDUSTRY INDUSTRY-TYPE REGION) means that LOCAL-INDUSTRY is of type INDUSTRY-TYPE and 'belongs to' REGION -- that is, its income contributes to the Gross National Product of the nation containing REGION. If a private industry, it pays taxes to the national government of REGION. Not all of the industry's facilities are necessarily located in REGION. For instance, it may have factories in countries where labor is cheaper. See also IndustryOfRegionFn.
label: Industry Of Region
industryOfRegion

comment: A LogicalConnective that represents bi-directional implication in CycL. It takes two arguments, each of which must be an instance of #$ELSentence-Assertible. (equiv FORMULA-1 FORMULA-2) means that FORMULA-1 is true precisely when FORMULA-2 is true; in other words, FORMULA-1 is true if and only if FORMULA-2 is true. (An EL equiv formula is translated during canonicalization into an equivalent, less compact, conjunction of implies formulas.) See also the predicate sentenceEquiv.
label: Equiv
equiv

comment: (someAndOnlyTypePlaysRoleInSubSituationType SIT-TYPE TYPE SUBSIT-TYPE ROLE) means that for any instance of SIT-TYPE, there exists an instance of TYPE that plays the role ROLE in the sub-situation that instantiates SUBSIT-TYPE, and that only an instance of TYPE plays that role. Cf. the more general predicate onlyTypePlaysRoleInSubSituationType, which does not require an instance of TYPE to play ROLE in instances of SUBSIT-TYPE, but rather requires that whatever plays ROLE in SUBSIT-TYPE be of TYPE.
label: Some And Only Type Plays Role In Sub Situation Type
someAndOnlyTypePlaysRoleInSubSituationType
subPropertyOf: Only Type Plays Role In Sub Situation Type
Some Type Plays Role In Sub Situation Type

comment: (garnersVotes AGENT ELECTION NUMBER) means that the number of votes received by AGENT in ELECTION is NUMBER.
label: Garners Votes
garnersVotes

comment: (omitFromILP TERM) means that the CycLIndexedTerm TERM should not be included in ILP predicate determinations.
label: Omit From ILP
omitFromILP

comment: (producerOfResourceTypeInSystem AGENT RESOURCE-TYPE SYSTEM) implies that (componentInSystem_FunctionalRole SYSTEM AGENT), that, where AUTOCATALYSIS is the autocatalyticProcessImplementsSystem of SYSTEM, AGENT is capable of being the doneBy of makings of instances of RESOURCE-TYPE that are part of AUTOCATALYSIS, and that there exists a CONSUMER (which could be equivalent to AGENT but need not be) such that (consumerOfResourceTypeInSystem CONSUMER RESOURCE-TYPE SYSTEM).
label: resource producer
producerOfResourceTypeInSystem

comment:
(sentencesInducedByProgram_OverSubsetsOfPopulatedPreds PROG MT SENTENCE-SET)) means that, after the ILP program PROG iterates through the extent in microtheory MT of each of the 6 predicates in the sets of size 3 or less, PROG has sufficient evidence to induce the sentences in the set SENTENCE-SET.

See also sentencesInducedByProgram_OverSubsetsOfPopulatedPreds, which allows one to adjust the values that this predicate assumes will be 6 and 3 (the number of most-populous predicates found, and the maximumsize of the subsets passed to ILP.
label: Sentences Induced By Program In Mt
sentencesInducedByProgram-InMt

comment: (descriptionAscribesRelnToType DESCRIPTION RELN TYPE) means that the instance DESCRIPTION of Description_PCW is such that its description of DESCRIBED-THING (see thingDescribed) contains the claim that (relationInstanceExists RELN DESCRIBED-THING TYPE).
label: Description Ascribes Reln To Type
descriptionAscribesRelnToType

comment: A parallel for an axis of a surface of revolution is the intersection of the surface with any plane orthogonal to the axis. That is, if AXIS is an axis of revolution (see axisOfSurfaceOfRevolution) for the SurfaceOfRevolution SURFACE, then (parallelForAxisOfSurfaceOfRevolution PARALLEL AXIS SURFACE) means that there exists some Plane PLANE such that AXIS is orthogonal to PLANE and the intersection of PLANE and SURFACE is PARALLEL.
label: surface of revolution parallel
parallelForAxisOfSurfaceOfRevolution

comment:
A quaternary RuleMacroPredicate (q.v.) that can be used to state that a given binary predicate stands in a certain numerical relation with respect to two collections. (relationExistsMinAll BINPRED COL1 COL2 N) means that for any instance INST of COL2, there are at least N instances of (INST(1), ..., INST(N)) of COL1 such that (BINPRED INST(i) INST) holds (for 1 <= i <= N). This is equivalent to (and can thus be used in effect as shorthand for) the more complex form:

(implies (isa INST COL2) (thereExistAtLeast N ?INST-I (and (isa ?INST-I COL1) (BINPRED ?INST-I INST)))) .

For example, `(relationExistsMinAll physicalParts Hand Finger 1)' means that every finger is part of at least one hand. Cf. relationAllExistsMin, and see the shared #$NoteAboutUseOfRuleMacroPredicates.
label: Relation Exists Min All
relationExistsMinAll

comment: (keIrrelevantPrecisionSuggestion_Generalize TERM) says that TERM is never to be offered as by the precision suggestor as a possible generalization.
label: Ke Irrelevant Precision Suggestion Generalize
keIrrelevantPrecisionSuggestion-Generalize

comment: (availableForEvent AGENT OBJECT EVENT) means that AGENT has available OBJECT for the event EVENT. That is, if AGENT is capable of using OBJECT in EVENT, nothing prevents AGENT from choosing to use OBJECT in EVENT. Note that if OBJECT is availableForEvent to AGENT in EVENT, AGENT may still, for other reasons, be incapable of using OBJECT in EVENT.
label: Available For Event
availableForEvent

comment: (holdsAfter ?THING ?PRED ?OBJ ?VAL) means that (?PRED ?OBJ ?VAL) is true after the temporal extent of ?THING ends.
label: Holds After
holdsAfter

comment: (goalProvidesMotiveFor GOAL AGT ACT-TYPE ROLE) means that AGT's having the goal GOAL would provide her with a motive for acting in the specified way -- i.e., for playing ROLE in an instance of ACT-TYPE. Note that (goalProvidesMotiveFor GOAL AGT ...) does not entail that AGT actually has GOAL as a goal -- only that, if she had this goal, she would be credited (ordinarily) with having a motive for doing some instance of ACT-TYPE. goalProvidesMotiveFor is a specialization of providesMotiveFor which focuses on common motivational links between goals and action-types. For further discussion concerning the notion of 'motive' at work here, see the comment on providesMotiveFor.
label: Goal Provides Motive For
goalProvidesMotiveFor

comment: (n_WayJunctionInSystem X N SYS) means that X is an N-way junction in the PathSystem SYS, where N is a natural number greater than 2. This means that exactly N ends of links (or of loops) join at X, in the system SYS.
label: N Way Junction In System
n-WayJunctionInSystem

comment:
A ternary instance of InterArgIsaPredicate (q.v.). (interArgEqualsIsa3_2 RELN INDEPENDENT-ARG DEPENDENT-ARG-COL) means that, when INDEPENDENT-ARG appears as the third argument to RELN, a necessary condition for semantic well-formedness is that the second argument must be an instance of DEPENDENT-ARG-COL. That is, (RELN ARG1 ARG2 INDEPENDENT-ARG ...) is semantically well-formed only if ARG2 is an instance of DEPENDENT-ARG-COL.

For an explanation of semantic well-formedness, see CycLExpression_Assertible and its direct specializations. See interArgEqualsIsa for a similar but more general predicate that is quintary, allowing the user to specify the positions of the independent and dependent arguments.
label: Inter Arg Equals Isa 3 2
interArgEqualsIsa3-2

comment: (unifySchema ?Dag1 ?SchematicTFS ?Dag2) causes the typed-feature unification of the Lisp-level ?Dag1 (see #$dagOf) to be unified with the EL-Level Typed feature structure ?SchematicTFS to produce the Lisp-level typed-feature structure ?Dag2. Essentially a version of unify where the second argument is not a dag, but a more readable SubLList. The HL-level is responsible for converting ?SchematicTFS into a Dag for the unification to occur.
label: Unify Schema
unifySchema

comment: (satisfiesHeadSemanticConstraintsForNCR NODE RULE DENOT) means that wrt. the meaning DENOT (cf. proposedMeaning) NODE satisfies all of the semantic constraints (cf. NounCompoundRuleConstraint_Semantic) imposed by the NounCompoundRule RULE on a head.
label: Satisfies Head Semantic Constraints For NCR
satisfiesHeadSemanticConstraintsForNCR

comment:
A ternary predicate that relates a MultiDirectionalCommunication event to two agents that communicate with each other (bi-directionally) in that event. (interCommunicators COMM AGENT1 AGENT2) entails that both AGENT1 and AGENT2 are a communicatorOfInfo as well as an infoCommunicatedTo with respect to COMM; moreover, in the course of COMM some piece of information contributed by AGENT1 and intended for AGENT2 is in fact gathered by AGENT2, and vice versa (see infoContributed and infoGathered).

For example, interCommunicators holds when two agents are greeting (see ExchangeOfGreetings) or conversing with (see Conversation) each other.

Note that in some but not all cases, there will be two CommunicationAct_Single subevents of COMM such that AGENT1 is the senderOfInfo and AGENT2 the recipientOfInfo in one subevent, and vice versa for the other subevent.

Note also that the fact that two agents are both communicationParticipants in a given MultiDirectionalCommunication is not a sufficient condition for their being interCommunicators. For example, if you and I both take part in a group conversation among (say) six people, but we happen not to speak (or nonverbally communicate) to each other at all during the event, then we are not interCommunicators.
label: Inter Communicators
interCommunicators

comment: (interArgNotGenl1_2 PRED COL1 COL2) means that, when a spec of COL1 appears as the first argument to PRED, the second argument in that assertion is constrained to not be a spec of COL2 and vice versa.
label: Inter Arg Not Genl 1 2
interArgNotGenl1-2

comment: (agentHasOpportunity AGENT SITUATION-TYPE ROLE) says that the agent AGENT has the opportunity to play the role ROLE in an specialization of Situation.

agentHasOpportunity

comment: (closestEventOfTypePriorTo EVT1 EVT2 TYPE) means that EVT1 is the nearest event of TYPE prior to EVT2. In medical contexts it is assumed that both events involve the same patient.
