phoneticVariantOfSuffix

comment: (actsInCapacity_SupportFunction AGT ROLE EVT-TYPE) hold just in case AGT's role in events of type EVT-TYPE is of a supporting function (not as the main function).
label: supporting function
actsInCapacity-SupportFunction

comment: A predicate which asserts of sentences that they do not contradict currently known facts. (consistent SENTENCE) means that the CycLSentence_Assertible SENTENCE is consistent with assertions known in the current context. Consequently, (consistent SENTENCE) holds in a Microtheory MT just in case, for any assertion ASSERT that holds in MT, SENTENCE does not imply the negation of ASSERT. Note that this predicate is notAssertible. See also inconsistentWithMt.
label: consistent

comment: The predicate denotesOpposite is used to relate English words to concepts that are negatively related to their meanings. For instance, both #$Private-TheWord and #$Public-TheWord are semantically connected to ThePublic, but the two words are opposite in meaning. If (denotesOpposite #$Private-TheWord Adjective 0 ThePublic), we can conclude that the phrase 'not private' refers to ThePublic. Note that denotesOpposite is a placeholder predicate, signaling the need for further KE to represent the opposite concept.
label: Denotes Opposite
denotesOpposite

comment: (marketQuantityDemandAtConsumerIncomeLevel MARKET PRODUCT INCOME QUANTITY) identifies QUANTITY as the quantity of demanded goods or services of type PRODUCT for consumers at an income level of INCOME, an instance of MonetaryValue.
label: Market Quantity Demand At Consumer Income Level
marketQuantityDemandAtConsumerIncomeLevel

comment: (obstacleToFrom_Path OBS AGT PATH) means that OBS is an obstacle on the path PATH and provides AGT with some difficulty. OBS either blocks AGT from PATH completely, impedes AGT while AGT passes through it, or diverts AGT to some other path.
label: obstacle for agent on path
obstacleToFrom-Path
subPropertyOf: obstacle for agent moving into area

comment: An assertion of the form (birthRateDuring PLACE ORG-TYPE REAL DATE) states that measurements made of the population for the Date DATE indicate that for every 1000 people in the population of the GeographicalRegion PLACE, REAL number of people were born. For instance, an expression of the form (birthRateDuring Syria HomoSapiens 10.2 (YearFn 2005)) states that records indicate that during 2005, for every 1000 citizens of Syria, 10.2 children were born. This represents a measurement and estimate.
label: Birth Rate During
birthRateDuring

comment: (relationExistsSpecExistsSpec PRED COL1 COL2) means that there exists a subcollection of COL1, SUBCOL1 and a subcollection of COL2, SUBCOL2 such that (PRED SUBCOL1 SUBCOL2).
label: Relation Exists Spec Exists Spec
relationExistsSpecExistsSpec

comment: A ternary complex action predicate. (doOpenClassDefinition PROGRAMMER FILE CLASS) means that PROGRAMMER appends code to the end of FILE that signifies the beginning of a declaration of the datatype CLASS.
label: Do Open Class Definition
doOpenClassDefinition

comment: This predicate relates each of the object schema types for a schema integration to the set of relationship defining schemas that implicitly relate (See ImplicitRelationshipDefiningSchemaFn) some object defining schema of the given type. That is, (schemaIntegrationTypeForInputImplicitRDSSet INTEGRATION TYPE RDS-SET) means that in the schema integration INTEGRATION, each RelationshipDefiningSchema in the set RDS-SET implicitly relates some ObjectDefiningSchema of type TYPE (determined via schemaIsa). See also schemaIntegrationTypeForInputExplicitRDSSet.
label: Schema Integration Type For Input Implicit RDS Set
schemaIntegrationTypeForInputImplicitRDSSet
subPropertyOf: Schema Integration Type For Input RDS Set

comment: Static frictional forces from the interlocking of two surfaces work against any relative motion up until some threshold of motion which is characterized by the coefficient of static friction. The coefficient of static friction is typically larger than the coefficient of kinetic friction (see coefficientOfFriction_Kinetic). (coefficientOfFriction_Static OBJ1 OBJ2 NUM) means that NUM is the ratio of the static frictional resistance force (see FrictionVector) to the normal force which presses the surfaces of OBJ1 and OBJ2 together at the threshold of motion. See also coefficientOfFriction.
label: Coefficient Of Friction Static
coefficientOfFriction-Static

comment: A ternary instance of InterArgIsaPredicate (q.v.). (interArgIsa3_2 RELN INDEPENDENT-ARG-COL DEPENDENT-ARG-COL) means that, when an instance of INDEPENDENT-ARG-COL appears as the third argument to RELN, a necessary condition for semantic well-formedness is that the second argument must be an instance of DEPENDENT-ARG-COL. That is, if INST is an instance of INDEPENDENT-ARG-COL, then (RELN ARG1 ARG2 INST ... ARGN) is semantically well-formed only if ARG2 is an instance of DEPENDENT-ARG-COL. For an explanation of semantic well-formedness, see CycLExpression_Assertible and its direct specializations.
label: Inter Arg Isa 3 2
interArgIsa3-2

comment: (valveStenosisSeverityWithValve EVT VALVE VALVE-TYPE SEVERITY) means the information associated with the cardiac valve VALVE associated with medical event EVT indicates that the patient's valve of type VALVE-TYPE has severity SEVERITY
label: Valve Stenosis Severity With Valve
valveStenosisSeverityWithValve

comment: (linkBetweenInSystem LINK X Y SYS) means that in the PathSystem SYS, the Path_Simple LINK (a link in SYS, so that (linkInSystem LINK SYS) holds) has as its two end points X and Y (nodes in SYS, so that both (nodeInSystem X SYS) and (nodeInSystem Y SYS) hold). Since LINK connects the two end points X and Y when (linkBetweenInSystem LINK X Y SYS) holds, (linkBetweenInSystem LINK X Y SYS) implies (pathBetween LINK X Y). A link in a path system is a path whose end points are nodes in the system, and which has no other nodes along it (although it may have any number of non-node points along it). For each link LINK in SYS, there is a unique pair {X, Y} of different nodes in SYS such that (linkBetweenInSystem LINK X Y SYS) and (linkBetweenInSystem LINK Y X SYS) hold, and for any two nodes in SYS, there could be several different ('parallel') links between them. No point in SYS that is not a node can be an end point of a link. Only a node in SYS can be an 'intersection' point in SYS (see junctionInSystem), which implies that there is, in the system SYS, no point on a link LINK between X and Y that is an 'intersection' point of LINK and another link or a loop.
label: Link Between In System
linkBetweenInSystem

comment: (consulateBuildingOfCountryInCity COUNTRY CITY BUILDING) holds just in case BUILDING is the consulate building for COUNTRY and is located in CITY. This is the corresponding predicate to ConsulateBuildingFn.
label: Consulate Building Of Country In City
consulateBuildingOfCountryInCity

comment: The corresponding predicate of the function MaximalSubSituationDuringIntervalFn. It relates an instance of Situation to an instance of Situation and an instance of TimeInterval. An assertion of the form (isMaximalSubSituationDuringInterval SIT1 SIT2 INTERVAL) states that SIT1 bears the relation subSituations from SIT2 and is the largest sub-situation of SIT2 that INTERVAL temporallySubsumes.
label: Is Maximal Sub Situation During Interval
isMaximalSubSituationDuringInterval

comment: This is exactly the same as ratioOfCollectionToDifferentiatedCollection except it takes sets as its second and third argument .
label: Ratio Of Set To Differentiated Set
ratioOfSetToDifferentiatedSet

comment: A unary #$InferenceCompletenessPredicate. (collectionCompletelyEnumerableViaBackchain COL) means that the CycInferenceEngine can generate a list of all of (and only) the instances of COL by appeal to isa consequent rules. For example, in certain medical domain microtheories, MazeProcedure_SurgicalProcedure is collectionCompletelyEnumerableViaBackchain because backchaining on its single rule is sufficient to generate all the relevant instances in those microtheories.
label: Collection Completely Enumerable Via Backchain
collectionCompletelyEnumerableViaBackchain

comment: A sentence of the form (angularDistanceBetweenVectors VECT1 VECT2 ANGLE) means that the instances of SimpleVector VECT1 and VECT2 have the AngularDistance ANGLE between them when they are interpreted as having a common origin in the same CoordinateSystem.
label: Angular Distance Between Vectors
angularDistanceBetweenVectors

comment: A sentence of the form (evaluationTypeAcceptanceThresholdForAgent SENT-EVAL-TYPE N AGENT) means that, within a particular context, the Agent_Generic will 'accept' that any Sentence that has received N different evaluations of the value SENT-EVAL-TYPE (an instance of SentenceEvaluationOutput) has the property associated with that SentenceEvaluationOutput. For example, the sentence (evaluationTypeAcceptanceThresholdForAgent #$TrueCycLSentence 1000 Cyc) says that if, in a given context, 1000 people assert that a particular sentence is true, then Cyc will accept that it is true in that context.
label: Evaluation Type Acceptance Threshold For Agent
evaluationTypeAcceptanceThresholdForAgent

comment: (marketIsMaximallyEfficientInProductionOfTypeWRTTypeDuringPeriod MARKET PRODUCT-TYPE-1 PRODUCT-TYPE-2 PERIOD) means that during PERIOD, the instance MARKET of Market is maximally efficient/minimally inefficient in its production of PRODUCT-TYPE-1 with respect to the alternative product type PRODUCT-TYPE-2.
label: Market Is Maximally Efficient In Production Of Type WRT Type During Period
marketIsMaximallyEfficientInProductionOfTypeWRTTypeDuringPeriod

comment: This predicate takes a stab at defining a responsible agent's 'sphere of responsibility' (considered as a specialization of Situation) in a given Situation. Roughly speaking,(sphereOfResponsibilityOfAgentInSituation AGENT SIT SIT-TYPE) means that throughout the course of SIT, AGENT is responsible for making sure that instances of SIT-TYPE happen the way they are supposed to happen. One very specific facet of this meaning: where it is known that (inheritRolePlayers SUPER-EVENT-TYPE INDEP-EVENT-TYPE DEP-EVENT-TYPE ROLE directingAgent) - that is, where it is known that for Situations of type SUPER-EVENT-TYPE, anyone who plays ROLE in a subSituations of type INDEP-EVENT-TYPE also plays the rule directingAgent in any subSituations of type DEP-EVENT-TYPE - and where it is known that AGENT plays ROLE in EVENT such that EVENT is a subSituations of SUPER-EVENT and SUPER-EVENT is an instance of SUPER-EVENT-TYPE, AGENT has DEP-EVENT-TYPE. Or to put it a bit more loosely, anytime an IntelligentAgent inherits the role of directingAgent in a class of Situation as the result of a situational 'script', that agent has that class of Situation as his or her 'sphere of responsibility' in the Situation whose inherited scripting gives rise to the role inheritance.
label: Sphere Of Responsibility Of Agent In Situation
sphereOfResponsibilityOfAgentInSituation

comment: It is medically recommended that the organism with the condition ARG1 (note that it's a particular instance of a condition and not the condition type) *refrain* from playing the role ARG3 in instances of ARG2, in order to ameliorate the condition.
label: Medically Proscribed
medicallyProscribed

comment: (successorPositionTo HI-POSITION LOWER-POSITION ORGANIZATION) means that HI-POSITION is a position in ORGANIZATION which, if it becomes vacant, is filled by the person formerely holding LOWER-POSITION.
label: Successor Position To
successorPositionTo

comment:
A ternary RotationalOrientationPredicate that relates a HexalateralObject to a CartesianCoordinateSystem to an AngularDistance. (lateralOrientationInCoordinateSystem OBJ SYSTEM DIST) means that DIST is the angular distance that OBJ has "strayed" (so to speak) from its standard or original rotational orientation about its longitudinal (front-to-back) axis in SYSTEM. (See #$NoteOnStandardRotationalOrientation.)

In flight dynamics, the lateral orientation of an aircraft is known as its "roll".

See also normalOrientationInCoordinateSystem and lateralOrientationInCoordinateSystem.
label: Longitudinal Orientation In Coordinate System
longitudinalOrientationInCoordinateSystem

comment: (<font color="#ff0000">#$stockPrice-HFair</font> STOCK PRICE DATE EXCHANGE) means that PRICE is the theoretical value at which a company is 'fairly valued,' meaning that it would not be reasonable to assume that the shares will rise. Fair value at any given point is derived from a number of qualitative and quantitative aspects of the business.
label: fair price
stockPrice-Fair

comment: An sentence of the form (hangsFromDuring HANGING OBJ1 OBJ2) means that during the HangingFromSituation HANGING, the PartiallyTangible OBJ1 is suspended from the PartiallyTangible OBJ2 throughout HANGING.
label: Hangs From During
hangsFromDuring

comment:
This is a very general predicate used to state the angle between two spatial things that intersect. (angleBetween THING1 THING2 ANGLE) means that the AngularDistance between THING1 and THING2 is ANGLE. There are several points to note about the meaning of this predicate:

1. While it is necessary that THING1 and THING2 spatiallyIntersects in order for there to exist some ANGLE between them, it is not sufficient. Two things may intersect in such a complex fashion that it is impossible to determine a measurable angle between them.

2. The arg3 of this predicate is not functional. In many cases, the measured angle between two intersecting things may form more than one angle. For example, two intersecting straight lines, LINE1 and LINE2, form two angles, ANGLE and SUPP-ANGLE, which are supplementary to one another. (see supplementaryAngles) In such a case we posit that both (angleBetween LINE1 LINE2 ANGLE) and (angleBetween LINE1 LINE2 SUPP-ANGLE) are true. In addition, it may be that the measured angle depends on the orientation of the observer, or the context of the measurement. For example, measurement of the vertex angles of polygons often distinguishes between the interior angles and exterior angles.

3. In almost all cases, the best way to use this predicate is to write rules which state sufficient conditions for concluding angleBetween for special cases, such as for the angles of intersection between two lines. See the consequent rules on this predicate for examples of such.
label: Angle Between
angleBetween

comment: (cultureProscribes_Categorical CULTURE ACTTYPE ROLE) means that within CULTURE it is considered improper or immoral or wrong to play ROLE in instances of ACTTYPE. For example, most cultures consider it wrong to take a human life. This does not entail, however, that CULTURE has a (hypothetical) proscription against playing ROLE in instances of ACTTYPE with respect to every possible condition; i.e. there might exist exceptional situations in which playing ROLE in an ACTTYPE is not proscribed (and might even be prescribed) by CULTURE. One might be required to take human life, for example, in wartime. This predicate applies equally to moral rules, rules of conduct or etiquette, and customs. See also cultureProscribes_Hypothetical,culturePrescribes_Categorical, and culturePrescribes_Hypothetical.
label: Culture Proscribes Categorical
cultureProscribes-Categorical

comment: A ternary ArgIsaPredicate (q.v.). (argIsa RELN N COL) means that semantic well-formedness requires that anything given as the Nth argument to RELN must be an instance of COL. That is, (RELN ... ARGN ...) is semantically well-formed only if (isa ARGN COL) holds. For example, (argIsa mother 1 Animal) and (argIsa argIsa 3 Collection) both hold. For an explanation of semantic well-formedness, see CycLExpression_Assertible and its specializations. For similar but less flexible binary predicates, see arg1Isa et al. See also argGenl.
label: Arg Isa
argIsa

comment: This predicate represents the primitive relation of type level role inheritance for complex situation types. (inheritRolePlayers SIT-TYPE SUBSIT-TYPE-FROM SUBSIT-TYPE-TO ROLE-FROM ROLE-TO) means where SIT is a complex situation of type SIT-TYPE, any actor that plays the role ROLE-FROM in any instance of SUBSIT-TYPE-FROM that is a subSituations of SIT will also play the role ROLE-TO in any instance of SUBSIT-TYPE-TO that is a subSituations of SIT.
label: Inherit Role Players
inheritRolePlayers

comment: (importThroughAmountDuring REGION PRODUCT-TYPE PT THING AMOUNT) means that the ScalarInterval AMOUNT is a measure of the amount of instances of the ProductType PRODUCT-TYPE imported by the GeographicalRegion REGION through the instance of PartiallyTangible PT (on their way from their origin) during the temporal extent of the TemporalThing THING. PT might, in the case of oil imports, for instance, be a GeographicalRegion or a Pipeline. THING will often be a calendar time period; but it may also be, for instance, a particular Event. In the case of automobile imports, for example, AMOUNT might be an Integer indicating the number of cars imported. In the case of oil imports, AMOUNT might be a Volume (a number of barrels) indicating the total quantity of oil imported (by REGION through PT), or it might be an instance of MonetaryValue indicating the monetary value of all the oil imported. Alternatively, AMOUNT might be a Rate, characterizing the average rate of import of instances of PRODUCT-TYPE by REGION through PT during the temporal extent of THING. Oil imports, for example, might be expressed in terms of so many million barrels per day or in terms of so many dollars per day (again, indicating the monetary value of the oil).
label: Import Through Amount During
importThroughAmountDuring

comment: The corresponding predicate to the logical schema denoting function LogicalSchemaForKSWithNameFn
label: Default Boolean Strings For KS
defaultBooleanStringsForKS

comment: (headMedialString STRINGS1 WORD STRINGS2 POS TERM) means that the TERM is denoted with POS part of speech by the concatenation of STRING1, WORD, and STRING2. If TERM is a collection, the semantic meaning of TERM is (isa :noun TERM). If TERM is an individual object, the semantic meaning of TERM is (equals :noun TERM). See also multiWordSemTrans.
label: Head Medial String
headMedialString

comment: (numericFluentGT OBJ F(X) G(X)) states that F(OBJ) > G(OBJ)
label: Numeric Fluent GT
numericFluentGT

comment: A predicate used to relate an instance of Line_Planar to a qualitative specification of its slope at a given point on that line.
label: Line Has Slope At Point Qualitative
lineHasSlopeAtPoint-Qualitative

comment: (patchFixesFaultOf_ReportIndexed PATCH FAULT FAULT-REPORT LIST), where LIST is (TheList SOFTWARE-OBJECT ... SOFTWARE-OBJECT-N), means that PATCH fixes the fault FAULT of the version of SOFTWARE-OBJECT-N that is packaged with SOFTWARE-OBJECT N-1 that is packaged with ... SOFTWARE-OBJECT-1. (That is, SOFTWARE-OBJECT-N (the last member of LIST) is the "sub-program" and SOFTWARE-OBJECT-1 the "main program" of which SOFTWARE-OBJECT-N is a part. DATABASE and ID-STRING indicate the security database (and its reference no.) where the fault-information is recorded. For example: (patchFixesFaultOf_ReportIndexed Q252795_W2K_SP3_X86_En_TheSoftwarePatch BufferOverflowFault_CommandExecution (ComputerVulnerabilityReportFn BugtraqFaultDatabase "3215") MSWindows2000) means that the buffer overflow fault with MS Windows 2000 reported in Bugtraq entry number 3215 will not render a computer vulnerable if patch Q252795 has been applied to the computer in question. Sometimes the "patch" is actually an updated version of the program being patched.
label: Patch Fixes Fault Of Report Indexed
patchFixesFaultOf-ReportIndexed

comment: (standardVehicleOfUnitTypeCount ?UNITTYPE ?VEHICLETYPE ?NUMBER) means that under 'ordinary' or 'normal' circumstances we would expect to find an instance of ?UNITTYPE equipped with exactly ?NUMBER TransportationDevices of type ?VEHICLETYPE.
label: Standard Vehicle Of Unit Type Count
standardVehicleOfUnitTypeCount

comment: (hasAssociatedRangeCollection COLL ONTOLOGY PRED RANGE-COLL) means that RANGE-COLL is the corresponding collection used as an arg2Isa for the OWLProperty PRED in ONTOLOGY that has specs (or instances) of COLL as its range.
label: Has Associated Range Collection
hasAssociatedRangeCollection

comment: An instance of IRExpansionPredicate. (irExpansionSentencesFromRequiredRelations_Instance INST COL SENT) identifies SENT as a possible expansion to suggest for the Individual INST insofar as INST is an instance of COL. *ongoing*.
label: Ir Expansion Sentences From Required Relations Instance
irExpansionSentencesFromRequiredRelations-Instance
Number Played Role In Instances ID
numberPlayedRoleInInstances-ID
Minimize Collection Extent
minimizeCollectionExtent
comment: (minimizeCollectionExtent COLL) means that *negation-by-failure* should always be non-nil for queries of the form (isa ?X COLL). This predicate is also used by the UIA to generate drop down lists that can be added to.

label: Mt Visible
mtVisible
comment:
A unary EvaluatablePredicate that applies to a Microtheory. (mtVisible MT) means that the contents of MT are visible in the current query context. In general, 
(genlMt MT1 MT2)
entails 
(ist MT1 (mtVisible MT2),
but the converse does not hold. In particular, it fails when MT1 is a ProblemSolvingCntxt. For example, 
(ist EverythingPSC (mtVisible HumanSocialLifeMt))
holds (in BaseKB), but 
(genlMt EverythingPSC HumanSocialLifeMt)
does not hold (in BaseKB).

(negativelyDependsOn ?SET ?DEP-SLOT ?INDEP-SLOT) means that the values for ?DEP-SLOT are negatively dependent on the values for ?INDEP-SLOT, for elements of ?SET. In other words, if the value for ?INDEP-SLOT is high for an arbitrary element of ?SET, then the value for ?DEP-SLOT will be low (and vice versa: high if low). Unlike the more general negativelyCorrelatedWith, negativelyDependsOn means that there is some causal link from ?INDEP-SLOT affecting ?DEP-SLOT.
label: Negatively Depends On
negativelyDependsOn

comment: This predicate relates two temporally disjoint things (two instances of TemporalThing) to the (longest) instance of TimeInterval between them. (timeIntervalBetween BETWEEN EARLIER LATER) means that BETWEEN is the time interval that starts immediately after EARLIER ends and ends immediately before LATER begins. LATER, of course, must begin after EARLIER ends.
label: Time Interval Between
timeIntervalBetween

comment: The functionCorrespondingPredicate for EvaluationOfByOnFn. (evaluationOfByOn EVALUATION THING AGENT INT) identifies EVALUATION as the unique instance of Evaluating in which AGENT evaluates THING at the time denoted by INT (which is the number of seconds elapsed since January 1, 1970).
label: Evaluation Of By On
evaluationOfByOn

comment: A RuleMacroPredicate that supports estimation of size comparisons. Where TYPE1 and TYPE2 are specializations of SpatialThing_Localized, METRIC-PRED is a MeasurableQuantitySlot such as areaOfRegion, and COMP is a NumericComparisonPredicate such as greaterThan, (metricComparisonTypes_Definite TYPE1 TYPE2 METRIC-PRED COMP) means that for any instance INST1 of TYPE1 and any instance INST2 of TYPE2, if (METRIC-PRED INST1 QUANT1) is true and (METRIC-PRED INST2 QUANT2) is true, then the quantity QUANT1 bears the relation COMP to the quantity QUANT2.
label: Metric Comparison Types Definite
metricComparisonTypes-Definite

comment: (ncRuleAssignsPegInterpretation RULE PEG CYCL) means that the instance RULE of NounCompoundRule applies to the expression peg PEG so as to assign CYCL as CycL semantics for PEG.
label: Nc Rule Assigns Peg Interpretation
ncRuleAssignsPegInterpretation

comment: (demandRate PT PRODUCT-TYPE RATE) means that the Rate RATE is a measure of the demand for instances of the ProductType PRODUCT-TYPE by the instance of PartiallyTangible PT. In a general economic context, PT will often be an instance of (GroupFn IntelligentAgent).
label: demand rate
demandRate

comment: This predicate relates agents and events in which they play some role to the kind of purpose that it has for the agent. For instance, (purposeInEvent_GoalType WayneGretzky_Athlete EatingBreakfast001 SelfPreservationGoal) means that Wayne Gretzky eats breakfast001 with the explicit purpose of pursuing self preservation. See also purposeInEvent.
label: Purpose In Event Goal Type
purposeInEvent-GoalType
Prop Pending Verification
propPendingVerification
comment: CycFormula is to be enabled, i.e. become true, in the goal context.

(nearestCommonSpecMt MT-1 MT-2 NEAR-MT) means that NEAR-MT is a "nearest" microtheory of which both Microtheory MT-1 and Microtheory MT-2 are generalizations. That is, NEAR-MT is not identical to either MT-1 or MT-2, both (genlMt NEAR-MT MT-1) and (genlMt NEAR-MT MT-2) hold, and there is no reified Microtheory NEARER-MT distinct from MT-1, MT-2, and NEAR-MT such that (genlMt NEARER-MT MT-1), (genlMt NEARER-MT MT-2), and (genlMt NEAR-MT NEARER-MT) all hold. Note that nearestCommonSpecMt is notAssertible, since it must always be recomputed from the current state of the genlMt hierarchy. For comparison, see also nearestGenlMt and nearestCommonGenlMt.
label: Nearest Common Spec Mt
nearestCommonSpecMt

comment:
(predicateIsComposedOfThroughAlternateArgPositions COMP-PRED PRED-1 PRED-2) means that the binary predicate COMP-PRED is the composition of the binary predicates PRED-1 and PRED-2. If (predicateIsComposedOfThroughAlternateArgPositions COMP-PRED PRED-1 PRED-2), then (COMP-PRED X Z) if and only if there is something, Y, such that (PRED-1 X Y) and (PRED-2 Y Z).

Suppose, for example, that (predicateIsComposedOfThroughAlternateArgPositions mothersName mother nameString). Then it follows from (mother BarbaraBush GeorgeWBush) and (nameString BarbaraBush "Barbara Bush") that (mothersName GeorgeWBush "Barbara Bush"). The function corresponding to this predicate is BinaryCompositionPredicateFn_AlternateArgs.
label: Predicate Is Composed Of Through Alternate Arg Positions
predicateIsComposedOfThroughAlternateArgPositions

comment: Used to aid in exemplifying appropriate use of a constant. In assertions of the form (examples_Positive FORT EXAMPLE COMMENT), EXAMPLE is english text describing a single example which is relevant to the meaning of the #$HLReifiedDenotationalTerm, FORT. COMMENT is optional commentary about that example. If you choose not to include the commentary then use the null string as the value for the third argument. Some examples are classically prototypical. Others are just barely positive and serve to illustrate boundary cases for using FORT. See also examples_Negative, examples_Borderline.
label: Examples-Positive
examples-Positive

comment: This quaternary predicate is used to indicate a type of action that a particular agent is forbidden to play a particular role in under the terms of a particular agreement. (agreementForbids AGREEMENT AGENT ACTTYPE ROLE) means that AGREEMENT forbids AGENT to play ROLE in any instance of ACTTYPE. For example, if a peace accord ACCORD forbids its signatories to wage war against one another, and SIGNER is one such signatory, then (agreementForbids ACCORD SIGNER War performedBy) holds. Similarly, a business contract may forbid one agent to compete with another after s/he sells rights to a product, design, or practice to a second agent.
label: action forbidden by agreement
agreementForbids

comment:
(currentStageOfTypeInScriptedSitOfType SUB-SIT SUB-SIT-TYPE SIT SIT-TYPE) means that:
(1) SUB-SIT is the currently occurring situation which is a sub-situation of SIT;
(2) SIT is of the type SIT-TYPE;
(3) SUB-SIT is of the type SUB-SIT-TYPE; and
(3) SUB-SIT-TYPE is at least a candidate sub-situation type (see candidateSubSituationTypes) of SUB-SIT-TYPE.
label: Current Stage Of Type In Scripted Sit Of Type
currentStageOfTypeInScriptedSitOfType

comment: (tacticalTerrainFromPositionForUnitType TERRAIN TACTIC-TYPE LOCATIONAL-PRED UNIT-TYPE) means that TERRAIN is a TACTIC-TYPE type of terrain for instances of UNIT-TYPE when they are located LOCATIONAL-PRED in relation to TERRAIN. For example, (tacticalTerrainFromPositionForUnitType Hill-1234 ObservationFacilitatingTerrain on_Physical InfantryUnit_MilitarySpecialty) says that the individual hill called Hill-1234 facilitates observation for infantry units when they are on it. Similarly, that same hill might limit observation when the unit is near it.
label: tactical terrain from a position for a type of unit
tacticalTerrainFromPositionForUnitType
Complete Specification
completeSpecification
comment: An assertion of the form (completeSpecification SPEC represents that assertions using the predicates normativeSpecificationDescribesSituationType, normativeSpecificationDescribesRoleForInd, and normativeSpecificationDescribesRoleForType and the NormativeSpecification SPEC are all known. Those three predicates are used to represent the satisfaction conditions on SPEC This assertions states that there are no missing elements of the specification and that the KB contains knowledge of the sufficient conditions for a situation to satisfy the SPEC.

An instance of InterArgFormatPredicate (q.v.). (interArgFormat5_2 PRED COL FORMAT) means that FORMAT is a Format (q.v.) requirement for the second argument-place of PRED when PRED's fifth argument is an instance of COL. That is, with respect to a sentence of the form (PRED ARG1 ARG2 ARG3 ARG4 ARG5 ... ARGN) in which ARG5 is an instance of COL, PRED's arg2 position (i.e. the position occupied by the metavariable `ARG2' in the preceding sentence-form) is subject to FORMAT. See Format and its instances for further explanation.
label: Inter Arg Format 5 2
interArgFormat5-2

comment: (solutionOf ?SOLTYPE ?SOLVENTTYPE ?SOLUTETYPE) means that solutions of type ?SOLTYPE are created by combining instances of the solvent ?SOLVENTTYPE with instances of the solute ?SOLUTETYPE. This predicate does not assume ?SOLVENTTYPE and ?SOLUTETYPE are the only substances present, see also totalSolutesInAqueousSolution.
label: solution containing a particular solvent and solute
solutionOf

comment: (tenureInUnitPosition POSITION MMO AGENT DURATION) means that, in the context of the assertion, AGENT holds POSITION in MMO, and has held that position for DURATION. More specifically, if it holdsIn time interval TEMP that (tenureInUnitPosition POSITION MMO AGENT) and INT is any time interval of duration DURATION that is temporallyFinishedBy TEMP, then (POSITION MMO AGENT) holdsIn INT.
label: tenure in position
tenureInUnitPosition

comment: This predicate is used to identify collections whose proper specs are prima facie reasonable to treat as "nameable" -- i.e., one might reasonaby use a name when making generic claims about these specs qua classes of their instances. For example, one might use the word "cancer" as a name for the class of instances of Cancer conditions, say in "Cancer is a terrible disease." Thus (treatProperSpecsAsNameableCollections AilmentCondition) means that if a UIA user defines a new constant TERM as a spec of AilmentCondition, it is reasonable for Cyc to believe that (nameableCollection TERM).
label: Treat Proper Specs As Nameable Collections
treatProperSpecsAsNameableCollections

comment: This predicate relates buildings to their levels by number. (nthLevelOfBuilding BLDG N LEVEL) means that LEVEL is the Nth level of BLDG. More precisely: if N > 0, LEVEL is the Nth floor of BLDG that is at or above ground level (starting from the 1st floor at ground level); if N < 0, LEVEL is the Nth floor of BLDG that is below ground level (starting from the (-1)th floor immediately below ground level); if N = 0, (nthLevelOfBuilding BLDG N LEVEL) is undefined. Note that N denotes the _actual_ number of LEVEL relative to the ground (when calculated as just described), regardless of what numeral (or letter, etc.) might be used by the designers or occupants of the building to denote LEVEL. For example, some buildings with 13 or more stories, for superstitious reasons, have no floor designated as '13'; nevertheless, such buildings have a floor (probably called '14') whose nthLevelOfBuilding is 13. See also numberOfLevels and numberOfStories.
label: Nth Level Of Building
nthLevelOfBuilding

comment: (higherPriorityInFolder FOLDER RES1 RES2) means that the RES1 has a higher priority than RES2 with respect to the KEInteractionFolder FOLDER. Assertions of this form can be used to express constraints on the organization (i.e. order) of KEInteractionPages and KEInteractionFolders which are part of a given folder.
label: Higher Priority In Folder
higherPriorityInFolder

comment: (closestInSetToObject OBJ1 OBJ2 SET) means that OBJ2 is the element of SET such that the distanceBetween it and OBJ1 is smaller than for any other element of SET.
label: Closest In Set To Object
closestInSetToObject

comment: A ternary instance of InterArgIsaPredicate (q.v.). (interArgIsa4_3 RELN INDEPENDENT-ARG-COL DEPENDENT-ARG-COL) means that, when an instance of INDEPENDENT-ARG-COL appears as the fourth argument to RELN, a necessary condition for semantic well-formedness is that the third argument must be an instance of DEPENDENT-ARG-COL. That is, if INST is an instance of INDEPENDENT-ARG-COL, then (RELN ARG1 ARG2 ARG3 INST ... ARGN) is semantically well-formed only if ARG3 is an instance of DEPENDENT-ARG-COL. For an explanation of semantic well-formedness, see CycLExpression_Assertible and its direct specializations.
label: Inter Arg Isa 4 3
interArgIsa4-3

comment:
This predicate relates an instance of HoldingHostages, HOLD, and an instance of Animal, HOSTAGE, to the instance of HeldCaptive, CAP, where the following conditions hold:

   1. (hostages HOLD HOSTAGE) 
   2. (subEvents HOLD CAP)
   3. (captive CAP HOSTAGE)


If the above conditions do not hold the function is undefined for that argument pair. Note: this predicate is the corresponding predicate to HeldHostageFn .
label: Captivity Corresponds To Hostage Taking
captivityCorrespondsToHostageTaking

comment: (purposeOfScriptTypeInPlan SCRIPTTYPE PLANMT GOAL) means that within the Plan (i.e., the microtheoretic planning context) PLAN, events of the type SCRIPTTYPE are ordinarily associated with a purpose represented by GOAL. In many but not all contexts this entails that is an event of type SCRIPTTYPE is performed by someone, that agent will have GOAL as a goals. It is true generally that if (purposeOfScriptTypeInPlan SCRIPTTYPE PLANMT GOAL) and it is true in the PLANMT that (isa EVENT SCRIPTTYPE), it will be true in the PLANMT that(purposeOfEvent EVENT GOAL).
label: Purpose Of Script Type In Plan
purposeOfScriptTypeInPlan
Non Existent
nonExistent
comment: (nonExistent TERM) states the assumption that TERM does not exist. This predicate is primarily used for reasoning in hypothetical contexts about the ramifications of some existing term not actually existing.

An assertion of the form (setOfIndMightPlayRoleInSitType SET ROLE SIT-TYPE) is used to assert that there exists evidence that the SetOrCollection SET is such that all of its elements may be filling ROLE, an instance of BinaryRolePredicate, in an instance of SIT-TYPE, some sub-collection of Situation.
label: Set Of Ind Might Play Role In Sit Type
setOfIndMightPlayRoleInSitType

comment:
A specialization of followingOrEqualValueOnScale (q.v.) that is used to compare the positions or "ranks" of two quantities/attributes/properties that are on the same scale. More precisely, (followingValueOnScale VALUE1 VALUE2 SCALE) means that VALUE1 and VALUE2 are both instances of the CollectionWithAnEventLikeOrder SCALE, and that VALUE2 is "greater than" (i.e. comes later than) VALUE1 in the ordering scheme conventionally associated with SCALE.

Typically, VALUE1 and VALUE2 will either (i) both be instances of Quantity (q.v.) or (ii) both be instances of FirstOrderCollection (q.v.) such that they correspond to properties of individuals. In case (i), SCALE will be a TotallyOrderedQuantityType, and (followingValue VALUE1 VALUE2) will hold.

For example, both of these hold: 

  (followingValueOnScale MildlyToxic Toxic Toxicity)


  (followingValueOnScale Corporal_Rank Sergeant_Rank USArmyRank) .

See also the specialization of followingValueOnScale, succeedingValueOnScale.
label: Following Value On Scale
followingValueOnScale
subPropertyOf: Following Or Equal Value On Scale

comment: (agentWorkTimeAvailableForTask AGENT TIME-QUANTITY TASK) means that AGENT is available for TIME-QUANTITY amount of time for work to work on TASK.  This predicate should be temporally qualified.  Thus, if it is true that (agentTaskAvailableWorkHours JohnSmith TASK001 (HoursDuration 160)), it means that John Smith is available for 160 hours of work time to work on TASK001.
label: Agent Work Time Available For Task
agentWorkTimeAvailableForTask

comment:
If SPACE is a TopologicalSpace with base set BASE (see baseSetOfTopologicalSpace), THING is an element of BASE, and SYSTEM is a set of subsets of BASE, then SYSTEM is called a fundamental system of neighborhoods of THING, and we write in CycL 
(fundamentalSystemOfNeighborhoodsOfThing THING SYSTEM SPACE)
if and only if for each neighborhood, NEIGHBORHOOD1, of THING, (see neighborhoodOfThingInTopologicalSpace) there exists a neighborhood, NEIGHBORHOOD2, of THING, that is an element of SYSTEM and is a subset of NEIGHBORHOOD1.
label: Fundamental System Of Neighborhoods Of Thing
fundamentalSystemOfNeighborhoodsOfThing

comment: (suggestedSubEventTypesOnTour TOUR EVENTTYPE SUBEVENTTYPE PLACE) means that within the context of TOUR, a tour participant (see tourParticipants) in TOUR might be advised to consider performing an instance of SUBEVENTTYPE during the course of an event of type EVENTTYPE occuring at PLACE during the tour.
label: Suggested Sub Event Types On Tour
suggestedSubEventTypesOnTour

comment: (numberOfInstancesOfCollPerInstanceOfDateType DATE-TYPE DATE EVENT-TYPE NUM) holds of every NUM such that NUM is the number of instances of EVENT-TYPE that occur in DATE where DATE is an instance of DATE-TYPE.
label: Number Of Instances Of Coll Per Instance Of Date Type
numberOfInstancesOfCollPerInstanceOfDateType

comment: (priorValveInsufficiency EVENT VALVE INSUFF) means that within 6 months prior to EVENT, the most recent insufficiency recorded for VALVE of the patient treated in EVENT is INSUFF.
label: Prior Valve Insufficiency
priorValveInsufficiency

comment: (definitionInGlossary WORK GLOSSARY TERM DEFINITION) means that the GraphicalStructure GLOSSARY is a glossary contained within (see containsStructure_CW) the StructurallySpecificWork WORK and that among the subStructures of GLOSSARY are the TextString TERM, a term defined in GLOSSARY, and the GraphicalStructure DEFINITION, the definition of TERM.
label: Definition In Glossary
definitionInGlossary
Thing To Protect
thingToProtect
comment: SomethingExisting is to be protected in the goal context.

(exportRevenueFractionDuring REGION PRODUCT-TYPE THING NR) means that NR is the quotient of the monetary value of exports of the ProductType PRODUCT-TYPE by the GeographicalRegion REGION during the temporal extent of the TemporalThing THING (as dividend) and the monetary value of REGION's exports of all goods and services during the temporal extent of THING (as divisor). THING will often be a calendar time period; but it may also be, for instance, a particular Event. For example, to express the fact that Oman's oil exports accounted for 80 percent of the total value of its exports in 1997, we can say (exportRevenueFractionDuring Oman PetroleumProduct (YearFn 1997) (Percent 80)). See also exportAmountDuring.
label: Export Revenue Fraction During
exportRevenueFractionDuring
Evaluate At EL
evaluateAtEL
comment: (evaluateAtEL FUNCTION) means that the canonicalizer will translate each non-atomic term (see the collection CycLNonAtomicTerm) whose initial (or "0th" argument-place) term denotes FUNCTION into the value to which the non-atomic term evaluates. For example, if (evaluateAtEL PlusFn) holds in a Microtheory MT, then the non-atomic term `(PlusFn 2 3 4)' will canonicalize as `9' in that MT. Note that a non-atomic term containing a nested non-atomic term whose initial term denotes another instance of EvaluatableFunction (call that instance OTHER-FUNCTION) will not canonicalize in this way, unless (evaluateAtEL OTHER-FUNCTION) is also true in MT. For example, `(PlusFn 2 (DifferenceFn 3 4))' will not canonicalize as `1' in MT unless (evaluateAtEL DifferenceFn) is also true in MT.

This predicate relates a customary path such as a street to two objects that are generally across the path from each other. (oppositeOnPath_Generally OBJ1 OBJ2 PATH) means that some part of OBJ1 is directly across PATH from some part of OBJ2. In other words, OBJ1 and OBJ2 are onPath_Alongside opposite sides of PATH, and the two segments of PATH that OBJ1 and OBJ2 are respectively related to by alongsidePathSegment spatially intersect. More precisely: there is some vertical plane perpendicular to the vertical ''plane'' defined by the centerline of PATH (or, even more precisely, by the centerline of the portion of PATH common to the two segments of PATH mentioned above) that passes through both OBJ1 and OBJ2. For a specialization of this predicate that implies that the objects are more directly across the path from each other, see oppositeOnPath_Directly.
label: somewhere on opposite side of path
oppositeOnPath-Generally

comment: (moreSkilledThan AGENT1 AGENT2 SKILL) means that AGENT1 has greater skill at performing--i.e., bearing the relation doneBy to--#$SkilledActivity of type SKILL.
label: More Skilled Than
moreSkilledThan

comment:
A ternary RuleMacroPredicate that relates a Collection to a ScalarIntervalSlot to a ScalarInterval. (maximumValueForTypeWRTSlot COL SLOT MAX) means that every instance of COL stands in SLOT to a scalar interval less than or equal to MAX. That is, it is shorthand for the following rule: 
(implies
  (and
    (isa ?THING COL)
    (SLOT ?THING ?QUANT))
  (greaterThanOrEqualTo MAX ?QUANT))
See also minimumValueForTypeWRTSlot.
label: Maximum Value For Type WRT Slot
maximumValueForTypeWRTSlot

comment: anatomicalPartTypeRequired is an instance of ResourcePredicate. '(anatomicalPartTypeRequired ACT-TYPE PART-TYPE ROLE)' means that the successful player of ROLE in an act of ACT-TYPE must have at least one physical part of type PART-TYPE.
label: Anatomical Part Type Required
anatomicalPartTypeRequired

comment: (massNounSemTrans NOUN INT FRAME TRANS) means that the translation of word sense number INT of mass noun NOUN in frame FRAME is TRANS.
label: Mass Noun Sem Trans
massNounSemTrans

comment: For example, (objectsPerArea PT Mine 4 (SquareMeter 1)) means that PT has 4 mines per square meter.
label: Objects Per Area
objectsPerArea

comment: `Change' here means change in cardinality. (wantsToRelnChange AGT COL PRED GVP) means that AGT desires to be in the relation PRED with the amount suffested by GVP; more [highAmountOf] or fewer [lowAmountOf] instances of the collection COL. PRED is a BinaryPredicate.
label: Wants To Reln Change
wantsToRelnChange

comment: The functionCorrespondingPredicate of PreparingToPlayRoleInSituationFn (typePreparesForRoleInSituation PREPARATION-TYPE ROLE SITUATION) identifies PREPARATION-TYPE as the collection of events in which an intelligent agent prepares to play the role ROLE in the situation SITUATION. For example, (typePreparesForRoleInSituation TrainingForTheBigRaceOnJanuary10 competingAgents TheBigRaceOnJanuary10) says that TrainingForTheBigRaceOnJanuary10 is the collection of all events in which someone prepares to compete in the big race. See also typePreparesForRoleInType.
label: Type Prepares For Role In Type
typePreparesForRoleInType

comment: (logicalFieldValueWithFieldName LS NAME LFI) means that LFI is the logical field indexical in LS that corresponds to to the physical field with NAME.
label: Logical Field Value With Field Name
logicalFieldValueWithFieldName

comment: (etymologicalVariantOfSuffix SUFFIX STRING BASE-TYPE) means that STRING is the suffixString of the LexicalSuffix SUFFIX whenever it is combined with a BaseWordForm having etymological feature BASE-TYPE. Example: (etymologicalVariantOfSuffix Er_Agent_TheSuffix "or" NeoClassicalBaseWordForm)
label: Etymological Variant Of Suffix
etymologicalVariantOfSuffix

comment: (durationAtIntensityLevel COND DIS-LEV TIME) means that the agent experiencing (bodilyDoer) COND has experienced the level of discomfort DIS-LEV for the time period TIME.
Mx4rwLSVCpwpEbGdrcN5Y29ycA: durations of a condition at a particular intensity level
label: duration of a condition at a particular intensity level
durationAtIntensityLevel

comment:
(closestEventOfTypePriorToWithValueForOf EVT1 EVT2 TYPE PROPERTY VALUE) means that EVT1 is the nearest event of TYPE prior to EVT2 that has VALUE for property. This entails that 
    
       (PROPERTY EVT1 VALUE)
In medical contexts it is assumed that both events involve the same patient.
label: Closest Event Of Type Prior To With Value For Of
closestEventOfTypePriorToWithValueForOf

comment: (compatibleWithIn PROD1 PROD2 SCRIPT) states that instances of PROD1 are compatible with instances of PROD2 when used in scripts of type SCRIPT. The roles that each object must play are stated as their primaryFunction assertions involving SCRIPT
label: Compatible With In
compatibleWithIn

comment: (most_GenQuantWithQuantityHaveQuant SETORCOL QUANT1 QUANT2) is true if and only if most elements of SETORCOL with the Quantity QUANT1 have the Quantity QUANT2. For instance, it might be true that all persons that are experiencing a low level of burning sensation are also experiencing a low level of pain. We can express this dependency in the following way: (most_GenQuantWithQuantityHaveQuant Person (LowAmountFn LevelOfBurningSensation) (LowAmountFn LevelOfPain)).
label: Most Gen Quant With Quantity Have Quant
most-GenQuantWithQuantityHaveQuant

comment: (specPredsIrrelevantToTermSummaryPredWRTInstancesInArg PRED TERM-SUMMARY-PRED TYPE N) means that if a thing THING is an instance of TYPE, then any assertions in which a specialization of PRED occurs in arg 0 and THING occurs as arg N should not appear in the fact sheet for THING under the category associated with TERM-SUMMARY-PRED.
label: Spec Preds Irrelevant To Term Summary Pred WRT Instances In Arg
specPredsIrrelevantToTermSummaryPredWRTInstancesInArg

comment: (intervalAfterOfDuration INT TEMP-OBJ QUANT) means that INT is the TimeInterval of duration QUANT (an instance of Time_Quantity) that immediately follows (see the predicate contiguousAfter) the TemporalThing TEMP-OBJ.
label: Interval After Of Duration
intervalAfterOfDuration

comment: (dateRangeForMedicationStart MED DATE1 DATE2) means that if MED is an instance of MedicationPrescribedOrTaken, then MED has min-Date DATE1 and max-Date DATE2 as the bounds of its MedicationStartTime.
label: Date Range For Medication Start
dateRangeForMedicationStart

comment: (requiredRolesForSubSituationType SIT-TYPE SUBSIT-TYPE ROLE) means that if an instance of SUBSIT-TYPE is a subSituations of an instantiation of SITTYPE, there must be some SomethingExisting that plays the role ROLE in the instance of SUBSIT-TYPE.
label: Required Roles For Sub Situation Type
requiredRolesForSubSituationType

comment: An instance of RelativeLocationalPredicate. (between_Entirely THIS THAT MID) means that MID fills the space separating THIS and THAT, and is directly between them.
label: Between-Entirely
between-Entirely

comment: A #$CustomaryPathCycLConstant used for stating that a given path connects two things. (pathConnects PATH HERE THERE) means that PATH connects HERE and THERE. Often PATH is a physical path or connection along which objects or information may travel between HERE and THERE. Note that PATH might extend beyond HERE or THERE (cf. pathBetween). If PATH is bidirectional, then (pathConnects PATH THERE HERE) holds as well; but if PATH is unidirectional (see DirectedCustomaryPath), this does not hold; cf. the more general pathConnects_Commutative.
label: path connection
pathConnects

comment: A predicate relating an individual thing, such as a ModernMilitaryUnit_Deployable or a piece of equipment, to military functions it can serve, beyond its primary function. For example, (#$auxillaryFunction-Military MORTARUNIT01 #$Reconnaissance-MilitaryFundamental performedBy) means that the individual unit MORTARUNIT001 has some reconnaissance capabilities, though that is not its primary function. Reconnaissance is a possible use, but not the most probable use, of the unit when it appears in military operations.
label: auxiliary military function
auxiliaryFunction-Military

comment: (launchFromERHasStationCompromisedWRTCapability OP FACILITY FUNC-TYPE) means that the rocket launch operation OP involves a range station FACILITY whose functionality, FUNC-TYPE is compromised in a manner that impacts the implementation of OP.
label: Launch From ER Has Station Compromised WRT Capability
launchFromERHasStationCompromisedWRTCapability

comment: A QueryDedicatedPredicate used for querying whether for any roles such that all instances of specified event type are known to have some instance of a specified actor type playing the role in question.
label: Query Rule Macro Roles In Event Type
queryRuleMacroRolesInEventType

comment: (satisfiesHeadSemanticConstraintsForNCR NODE RULE DENOT) means that wrt. the meaning DENOT (cf. proposedMeaning) NODE satisfies all of the semantic constraints (cf. NounCompoundRuleConstraint_Semantic) imposed by the NounCompoundRule RULE on a modifier.
label: Satisfies Modifier Semantic Constraints For NCR
satisfiesModifierSemanticConstraintsForNCR

comment: (identicalInQuantity THING1 THING2 QUANT-TYPE) means that the two things THING1 and THING2 have the same values of the quantity type QUANT-TYPE. Here 'the same' means complete identity or very close resemblance -- what this means, and what the standard of closeness or identity is, depends on the context, but identicalInQuantity and differentInQuantity cannot both be correctly asserted of the same two things. See also resemblesInQuantity.
label: Identical In Quantity
identicalInQuantity

comment: (partTypeCount OBJ-TYPE PART-TYPE INT) means that INT is the number of parts of type PART-TYPE that every instance of OBJ-TYPE has. For example (partTypeCount Book_CW Chapter_PCW 15) says that every book has fifteen chapters. To talk about physical parts, use the more specific physicalPartTypeCount.
label: Part Type Count
partTypeCount

comment: (adjectiveOfGenericValue SLOT VALUE WU) means that the regularDegree form of WU can be used to modify a noun NOUN to form a phrase meaning 'NOUN whose SLOT value is VALUE compared to other NOUNs'.
label: Adjective Of Generic Value
adjectiveOfGenericValue

comment: (partnersInCooperation AGT1 AGT2 COOP) means that AGT1 and AGT2 are IntelligentAgents who cooperate with each other in the CooperationEvent COOP. Note that there could be more than two agents who cooperate in COOP, but there are at least two. Accordingly, AGT1 and AGT2 must be distinct agents when (partnersInCooperation AGT1 AGT2 COOP) holds. See also cooperatingParticipants.
label: Partners In Cooperation
partnersInCooperation

comment: The agent ARG1 prefers ARG3 over ARG4 on its ARG2 slot.
label: Preferred Entry
preferredEntry

comment: This predicate can be used to assert that a given animal agent has the ability to play a certain role in a certain type of SkilledActivityType (q.v.). (skillCapableOf ANIMAL ACTTYPE ROLE) means that ANIMAL has the necessary skills to act in ROLE in normal instances of ACTTYPE. For example, that #$Gumby can swim is expressed by (skillCapableOf #$Gumby Swimming_Generic performedBy). skillCapableOf entails that ANIMAL satisfies any anatomical or intellectual prerequisites for possessing or exercising the skill; but it is neutral as to whether ANIMAL has the necessary resources of time, money, opportunity, etc., to use the skill in any particular instance of ACTTYPE.
label: could
skillCapableOf

comment: (traversalInSystem TRAV A B SYS) means that TRAV is a Traversal from A to B in the PathSystem SYS. Let TRAV = (TraversalFn (TheList X(1) PATH(1) ... X(n) PATH(n) X(n+1))). To say that TRAV is a Traversal from A to B in SYS we mean that (i) TRAV is a Traversal in SYS, i.e., (traversalInSystem TRAV SYS) holds, and (ii) A = X(1) and B = X(n+1) (and thus both A and B are points in SYS and both (traversalFrom TRAV A) and (traversalTo TRAV B) hold). So (traversalInSystem TRAV A B SYS) is actually an abbreviation of (and (traversalInSystem TRAV SYS) (pointInSystem A SYS) (pointInSystem B SYS) (traversalFrom TRAV A) (traversalTo TRAV B)).
label: Traversal From To In System
traversalFromToInSystem

comment: (formulaTemplateExample TEMPLATE TOPIC FORMULA) means that, when dealing with TOPIC, FORMULA is a good example of a formula that can be made using TEMPLATE.
label: Formula Template Example
formulaTemplateExample

comment: ARG1 is interested in having the relationship ARG3 to some instance of the class of things, ARG2.
label: Interest In Type
interestInType

comment: (productionRate PRODUCER PRODUCT-TYPE RATE) means that the instance of SomethingExisting PRODUCER produces instances of the ProductType PRODUCT-TYPE at the Rate RATE. PRODUCER might, for example, be a Country, a Business, an Island, or a Person; and RATE might be a number per unit of time, or a volume per unit of time, or a MonetaryRate.
label: production rate
productionRate

comment: (agentBetterThanAtType GROUP1 GROUP2 EVENT-TYPE) means that GROUP1 is considered better than GROUP2 at instances of EVENT-TYPE. For example, (agentBetterThanAtType DallasCowboys WashingtonRedskins PenetratingADefense) means that the DallasCowboys are considered better at instances of PenetratingADefense than the WashingtonRedskins are.
label: Agent Better Than At Type
agentBetterThanAtType

comment: A ternary complex action predicate. (doOutputProgramExpression PROGRAMMER FILE EXPRESSION) means that PROGRAMMER appends EXPRESSION to the end of computer file FILE.
label: Do Output Program Expression
doOutputProgramExpression

comment: (isAContraryFactorFor FACTOR AGENT ACT_TYPE) means that in the given circumstances FACTOR would cause AGENT's likelihood of success in doing actions that are tokens of ACT_TYPE to be lower, i.e., the conditional probability of AGENT's succeeding at ACT_TYPE given FACTOR is less than it would be if FACTOR did not obtain. In other words, FACTOR brings it about that the derivedProbability of the proposition expressed by 'A would be successful at ACT_TYPE_TOKEN if she tried' is decreased. Note that 'being a contrary factor' in this sense is relative to the given circumstances: in the present, ordinary circumstances not having coffee readily available might be a contrary factor for Julia to make a successful presentation, but things might well be different in a state of affairs where Julia has slept for 3 straight days and is fully rested.

comment:
(cycLQuerySpecificationPertinentToDegree Q-SPEC DEGREE SET) means that Q-SPEC is an instance of CycLQuerySpecification that is, to the degree of relevance DEGREE, pertinent to the instance of information gathering InformationGathering), as a consequence of the pertinence of the terms in the Set_Mathematical SET.

Q-SPEC may have as an InferenceSentenceParameter a fully-bound query sentence, or it may be a query specification which has open variables. If Q-SPEC has open variables, it may be that some appropriate restriction of those variables will yield a more obviously pertinent query. For example, if someone is studying a crime denoted by "Crime008", a CycL query specification with this inference sentence parameter will be pertinent: 

(likelySuspects ?ACT ?AGENT)

Further, a restriction of the open variables in that CycL query specification will yield a more obviously pertinent sentence: 

(likelySuspects Crime008 ?AGENT)

In such a case, it will be true that a CycL query specification with the latter inference sentence parameter will be pertinent to a higher degree of relevance than a CycL query specification with the former inference sentence parameter.

See also cycLQuerySpecificationPertinentToDegree_Numeric.

NOTE: This predicate should only be used in microtheories which specify the appropriate qualifications of assertions made with it: e.g., for whom the query is pertinent, on what task, at what time and place, etc.
label: Cyc L Query Specification Pertinent To Degree
cycLQuerySpecificationPertinentToDegree

Equivalently, where INST1 and INST2 are respective instances of COL1 and COL2, (typesSimilarWRTTypeViaBinRel_Inverse COL1 COL2 COMCOL BINPRED) implies (similarWRTTypeViaBinRel_Inverse INST1 INST2 COMCOL BINPRED).

This predicate is similar to makesVulnerableToDegree except that, unlike makesVulnerableToDegree, it expresses a relative increase in OBJECT's vulnerability rather than an absolute degree of vulnerability. It also resembles vulnerableIn, but there is an important difference that must be observed, namely that when using increasesVulnerabilityIn one assumes that certain conditions coming into effect increase vulnerability. Therefore, it should not be used to declare vulnerabilities outright; Cyc should have to conclude that a situation increases an object's vulnerability to some result.

This predicate relates agents to the kinds of things they like to do. (likesRoleInEventType AGENT ROLE EVENTTYPE) means that AGENT enjoys playing ROLE in events of the type EVENTTYPE. This entails that AGENT actually _has_ played -- and enjoyed playing -- ROLE in one or more instances of EVENTTYPE, and that on most (if not all) such occasions she enjoyed herself. Typically, AGENT will have played ROLE in a number of instances of EVENTTYPE. For example, (likesRoleInEventType Joe performedBy Running) means that Joe likes to run. Cf. dislikesRoleInEventType.

comment: (willBe_Metric TYPE NUM PROP) means that it will be the case NUM `steps' forward that PROP, where the interpretation of `step' is determined by TYPE. For example, (willBe_Metric CalendarDay 2 `Fritz goes to California') means that Fritz will go to California the day after tomorrow, (willBe_Metric CalendarYear 1 `Cyc goes public') means that Cyc will go public next year, and (willBe_Metric Friday 1 `Charles visits his dentist') means that Charles will visit his dentist the following Friday (the first Friday in the future, w.r.t. today). Note that when asserting (willBe_Metric TYPE NUM PROP) with a time index (see mtTimeIndex) t, one should make sure that t is subsumed by an instance of TYPE if TYPE is a member of CalendarCoveringType. In general, a rule of thumb is to have t be subsumed by (TimeInterval_Incl_Excl_Fn X Y), where Y is the first member of TYPE in the future of t, and X is the first member of TYPE in the past of Y. (See other metric tense predicates was_Metric, willBe_Metric_CalendarTime and was_Metric_CalendarTime, and plain tense operators willBe and was etc.)
label: Will Be Metric
willBe-Metric

comment: The predicate authorityCapableOf is used to assert that a particular agent has the authority to participate in a certain kind of situation in the capacity of a particular role, because of said agent's intrinsic properties. (authorityCapableOf AGENT SITTYPE ROLE) means that AGENT is authorized by the appropriate agency of authorization to play the role ROLE in situations of type SITTYPE. For example, it is true in Orange County that (authorityCapableOf LanceIto Trial_Criminal judicialAgents). Note that even though an agent may be authorityCapableOf playing a certain role in a certain kind of situation, this does not necessarily imply that the agent will be physically or mentally capable of playing that role in every instance of the situation type, or even that the agent is physically or mentally capable in general of playing that role in situations of that type.
label: Authority Capable Of
authorityCapableOf

comment: (resultTemporallySubsumedByArg FUNC) holds just in case, for anything, ARG, such that ARG is an admitted argument to FUNC, the result of applying FUNC to ARG is such that (temporallySubsumes ARG (FUNC ARG)). (nearestCommonGenlPreds PRED-1 PRED-2 NEAR-PRED) means that NEAR-PRED is a "nearest" predicate of which both PRED-1 and PRED-2 are specializations. That is, both (genlPreds PRED-1 NEAR-PRED) and (genlPreds PRED-2 NEAR-PRED) hold, and there is no reified Predicate NEARER-PRED distinct from NEAR-PRED such that (genlPreds PRED-1 NEARER-PRED), (genlPreds PRED-2 NEARER-PRED), and (genlPreds NEARER-PRED NEAR-PRED) all hold. Note that this predicate is non-assertible (see notAssertible), since its extension at any given time depends upon (and so must be computed from) the current state of the genlPreds hierarchy in the Cyc Knowledge Base.

comment: An assertion of the form (allotmentReservesPercentageOfIndForInterval ALLOT PERCENT INDIVIDUAL INTERVAL) states that the Allotment ALLOT represents a reservation of PERCENT percent of the Individual INDIVIDUAL's time during the TimeInterval INTERVAL. Every individual assertion using this predicate in a given context is assumed to represent a different reservation. Therefore, for the same ALLOT and INDIVIDUAL, even if there are two assertions where the TimeInterval of one bears the relation temporalBoundsContain to the TimeInterval of the second assertion, then ALLOT is assumed to have reserved the sum of the two reserved portions. This is a core predicate for describing what an Allotment reserves, see also allotmentReservesPercentageOfIndForInterval. This predicate assumes that for any set of values for ALLOT, INDIVIDUAL, and INTERVAL, there can be at most one value of PERCENT.

comment: interArgResultIsa_Asserted is a quaternary instance of MetaRelation. It is used to state that a certain complex and partly isa -based relationship holds between a given argument to a given function and the corresponding value that is returned when the function is applied to the argument. (interArgResultIsa_Asserted FUNC N INDEPENDENT-ARG-COL DEPENDENT-ARG-COL) means that, when a term that is asserted to be an instance of INDEPENDENT-ARG-COL appears as the Nth argument to FUNC, then (regardless of what the other arguments to FUNC might be) the value (if any) of that function for those arguments is an instance of DEPENDENT-ARG-COL. That is: if INST is asserted to be an instance of INDEPENDENT-ARG-COL and (FUNC ARG(1) ... ARG(N-1) INST ...) = VALUE, then VALUE is an instance of DEPENDENT-ARG-COL. Note that, unlike interArgResultIsa assertions, interArgResultIsa_Asserted assertions will not support assertions of the form (isa VALUE DEPENDENT-ARG-COL) unless it is asserted in the Cyc KB that (isa INST INDEPENDENT-ARG-COL).
label: Inter Arg Result Isa Asserted
