comment: (testCorrespondsToSourceQuestionNumber TEST SOURCE NUMBER) says that the #$KBContentTest-FullySpecified TEST corresponds to question number NUMBER from the AspatialInformationStore SOURCE.
label: Test Corresponds To Source Question Number
testCorrespondsToSourceQuestionNumber

comment: This predicate is used to describe an imbalance that may contribute to one agent's actual or strategic military advantage over another. (asymmetricMenaceWRT AGT1 AGT2 TYPE) means that AGT1 has an asymmetric advantage over AGT2 with respect to weapons of the type designated by TYPE, i.e., the first agent has weapons of that type, and the second agent has neither corresponding weapons of that type, nor defense systems designed to defend against such weapons. Thus, the Cyc assertion (asymmetricMenaceWRT UnitedStatesOfAmerica Japan NuclearWeapon) means that the United States has nuclear weapons, while Japan has neither nuclear weapons nor anti-nuclear weapons. By implication, if the United States were to use nuclear weapons to attack Japan, Japan would be at a decided disadvantage.
label: Asymmetric Menace WRT
asymmetricMenaceWRT

comment: (actionExpressesFeelingToward ACTION FEELING OBJECT) means that the doer (doneBy) of ACTION expresses FEELING about OBJECT by doing ACTION. Example uses include 'protesters burned a flag to express their hatred of the government', or 'Joe donned a Zoot suit to express his nostalgia for the 1920's.' See also actionExpressesFeeling, feelsTowardsObjectToDegree, feelsTowardsEvent. Note that this predicate describes feelings expressed about OBJECT and does not necessarily entail communicating feelings to OBJECT. To represent the communication of emotions to others see CommunicationAct_Single, NonVerbalCommunicating.
label: Action Expresses Feeling Toward
actionExpressesFeelingToward

comment: (predicateIntersection PRED GENLPRED1 GENLPRED2) means that (PRED ARG1 ...) holds iff (and (GENLPRED1 ARG1 ...) (GENLPRED2 ARG1 ...)). That is, if both GENLPRED1 and GENLPRED2 hold for a given sequence of arguments, then PRED holds for those arguments; and vice versa. If either GENLPRED1 or GENLPRED2 has fixed arity, then PRED has (the same) fixed arity; but if both have variable arity, so does PRED.
label: Predicate Intersection
predicateIntersection

comment: (useOfTypeInTypeForRole USE-TYPE OBJ-TYPE ACT-TYPE ROLE) means the specialization of PurposefulAction USE-TYPE is the type of action in which some instance of Agent_PartiallyTangible uses some instance of the specialization of SomethingExisting OBJ-TYPE in an instance ACT-TYPE of PurposefulAction in the instance ROLE of Role. Cf. this predicate's corresponding function, UsingAForFn.
label: Use Of Type In Type For Role
useOfTypeInTypeForRole

comment:
A ternary instance of InterArgIsaPredicate (q.v.). (interArgEqualsIsa4_3 RELN INDEPENDENT-ARG DEPENDENT-ARG-COL) means that, when INDEPENDENT-ARG appears as the fourth argument to RELN, a necessary condition for semantic well-formedness is that the third argument must be an instance of DEPENDENT-ARG-COL. That is, (RELN ARG1 ARG2 ARG3 INDEPENDENT-ARG ...) is semantically well-formed only if ARG3 is an instance of DEPENDENT-ARG-COL.

For an explanation of semantic well-formedness, see CycLExpression_Assertible and its direct specializations. See interArgEqualsIsa for a similar but more general predicate that is quintary, allowing the user to specify the positions of the independent and dependent arguments.
label: Inter Arg Equals Isa 4 3
interArgEqualsIsa4-3

comment: (levelOfEfficiencyWithRespectTo SYSTEM LEVEL EVTTYPE) says that SYSTEM has a LEVEL level of efficiency with respect to EVTTYPE, a kind of activity. For example, (levelOfEfficiency MySprinklerSystem (VeryLowAmountFn Efficiency) WateringALawn) says that my sprinkler system is inefficient with respect to lawn-watering activities. Note, however, that MySprinklerSystem might be fairly efficient with respect to other activities, such as spraying pedestrians from a distance.
label: Level Of Efficiency With Respect To
levelOfEfficiencyWithRespectTo

comment: (cellValueForSentenceInTableType TABLE-TYPE FOCAL-THING SENTENCE INTEGER CELL-VALUE) means that for tables about FOCAL-THING in rows representing the information encoded in SENTENCE instances of TABLE-TYPE have the value CELL-VALUE in the cell identified with the column numbered INTEGER (assuming a column numbering scheme in which the left-most column is numbered 1, the columns just to its right is numbered 2, and so on).
label: Cell Value For Sentence In Table Type
cellValueForSentenceInTableType
Locked Situation
lockedSituation
comment: (lockedSituation LOCK) means that the Lock LOCK is locked.

label: Do Declare Function Parameters
doDeclareFunctionParameters
comment: A variable arity complex action predicate. (doDeclareFunctionParameters PROGRAMMER FILE . ARGS) means that PROGRAMMER appends to the end of FILE code that declares ARGS as part of a function declaration.

An assertion of the form (budgetExpendituresDuring GEO DATE AMOUNT) states that the GeopoliticalEntity GEO spent the MonetaryValue AMOUNT during the Date DATE. For example, an assertion of the form (budgetExpendituresDuring Syria (YearFn 2003) (Dollar-UnitedStates 10000000000)) states that Syria spent $10 billion from its budget in 2003.
label: Budget Expenditures During
budgetExpendituresDuring

comment: (senseExtensionForWord WORD POS DENOTE) means that DENOTE should be recognized as an extended sense of WORD when it is used as POS.
label: Sense Extension For Word
senseExtensionForWord

comment: (featureOfTypeWithinDistanceFromPlace FEATURE TYPE DISTANCE PLACE) means that FEATURE isa TYPE and is roughly within a 4*(DISTANCE)^2 square box centered at PLACE. This predicate is implemented by finding the latitude and longitude of PLACE and constructing a 'bounding box' around it with sides of length 2*DISTANCE. Note that the 'roughness' of this box is greater away from the EarthsEquator, since the distanceBetween LatitudeLines decreasesCausally farFrom the EarthsEquator.
label: Feature Of Type Within Distance From Place
featureOfTypeWithinDistanceFromPlace

comment: (vulnerableIn SITUATION OBJECT RESULT-TYPE) means that when in situation SITUATION, existing object OBJECT is vulnerable to hardships of type RESULT-TYPE. The purpose of vulnerableIn is to represent vulnerabilities that stem from being in a particular situation, and presumably from playing some sort of role in that situation. It is the situation taken as a whole, including the important background conditions, that pose the vulnerability, not some object exclusively. Given this sense of vulnerability, and so as to distinguish this predicate from vulnerableTo and the like, we characterize RESULT-TYPE from OBJECT's perspective. RESULT-TYPE should therefore be a 'passive' term.
label: Vulnerable In
vulnerableIn
Use Reformulation Rule For Predicate Strengthening
useReformulationRuleForPredicateStrengthening
comment: (useReformulationRuleForPredicateStrengthening RULE) indicates that RULE is to be used for the purpose of replacing predicates in the input formula with more specialized ones (in the sense of typedGenlPreds).
(infectionRateOfIn DISEASE PLACE NUMBER) means that the number of people in (the territory of) PLACE who are infected with DISEASE is NUMBER (a fraction between 0 and 1).
label: Infection Rate Of In
infectionRateOfIn

comment: `(changeOfDesignatedSecondaryResidenceForYear CHANGE RES1 RES2 YEAR)' means that CHANGE is a ChangingOfDesignatedSecondaryResidence from RES1 to RES2 for YEAR. Specifically, before the change, RES1 was the designatedSecondaryResidence of the performedBy of CHANGE for YEAR while RES2 was not, and after the change the situation is reversed.
label: Change Of Designated Secondary Residence For Year
changeOfDesignatedSecondaryResidenceForYear
Xsd:any URI
xsd:anyURI
comment: xsd:anyURI is an imported RDFS/XML term equivalent to the Cyc term UniformResourceLocator

A sentence of the form (strategyGivesHypothesisScore STRAT HYP SCORE) means that the ScoringSoftwareStrategy STRAT assigns the HypotheticalContext HYP a numeric score of SCORE within the context in which the sentence is asserted. The value of SCORE that STRAT assigns to HYP can differ across context and can differ when STRAT's optimized form (see optimizedStrategyForm) differs.
label: Strategy Gives Hypothesis Score
strategyGivesHypothesisScore

comment: A QueryDedicatedPredicate that is used to query for explanations for causal relations' obtaining between event types.
label: Query For Outcome Explanation
queryForOutcomeExplanation

comment: An instance of InterArgFormatPredicate (q.v.). (interArgFormat4_2 PRED COL FORMAT) means that FORMAT is a Format (q.v.) requirement for the second argument-place of PRED when PRED's fourth argument is an instance of COL. That is, with respect to a sentence of the form (PRED ARG1 ARG2 ARG3 ARG4 ... ARGN) in which ARG4 is an instance of COL, PRED's arg2 position (i.e. the position occupied by the metavariable `ARG2' in the preceding sentence-form) is subject to FORMAT. See Format and its instances for further explanation.
label: Inter Arg Format 4 2
interArgFormat4-2

comment: The effect of exploitFaultOfProgramOnSystem.
label: Fault Of Program On System Exploited By
faultOfProgramOnSystemExploitedBy

comment: (possessiveSemTrans CONTRACTION INT FRAME TRANS) means that the translation of word sense number INT of CONTRACTION in frame FRAME is TRANS.
label: Possessive Sem Trans
possessiveSemTrans

comment: (sourceImplicitFieldTypeDerivedFromRelationArg SOURCE PRED INT) means that the structured information source SOURCE encodes the relation PRED to a series of arguments, where the INTth argument of PRED is implicit in SOURCE (i.e., not the value of any field in SOURCE. Implicit values may be fixed or variable; see the spec-preds sourceFixesRelationArg and sourceVariesRelationArg.
label: Source Implicit Field Type Derived From Relation Arg
sourceImplicitFieldTypeDerivedFromRelationArg

comment:
This predicate is a directive for the CycSalientDescriptor. (uninterestingQueryForRelnWithTermInArg RELN TYPE ARG) means that for any query on RELN where TERM stands in argument place ARG of RELN, (RELN TERM VARIABLE) is an uninteresting question.

For example, (uninterestingQueryForRelnWithTermInArg eventOccursAt #$InterestAccruingEvent001 1) means that if (eventOccursAt #$InterestAccruingEvent001 WHERE) is an uninteresting question for the CycSalientDescriptor to ask.
label: Uninteresting Query For Reln With Term In Arg
uninterestingQueryForRelnWithTermInArg

comment:
A very general instance of TernaryOrderingPredicate that identifies an ordering among two instances of AbstractStructure in some larger structure. 
   (structurePriorToStructureInStructure AS-1 AS-2 STRUCTURE)
means that AS-1 occurs prior to AS-2 within the context STRUCTURE, itself an instance of AbstractStructure. "occurs prior to" in this context means that AS-1 comes before AS-2 as understood by the conventions (interpreted loosely, to include man-made conventions as well as natural ones, such as the processes by which information in DNA is interpreted) used in interpreting STRUCTURE. So if AS-1 and AS-2 are abstract character strings (c.f., CharacterString) of English and STRUCTURE is a document formatted in the typical way that English documents are formatted, then any physical instantiation PRINTOUT of STRUCTURE will be such that an instantiation of (instantiationOfAIS) AIS-1 will appear to the left of or higher than or on an earlier page than an instantiation of AIS-2 on PRINTOUT.
label: Structure Prior To Structure In Structure
structurePriorToStructureInStructure

comment: An expression of the form (assertionNthArgBindingDerivedFromString ASSERT N STRING) relates an instance of CycLAssertion to an instance of SubLString. The SubLString was instrumental in providing the binding value for the Nth argument in the CycLAssertion.
label: Assertion Nth Arg Binding Derived From String
assertionNthArgBindingDerivedFromString

comment: (rankInCompetition AGENT COMP RANK) states that AGENT came in RANK place in competition COMP.
label: Rank In Competition
rankInCompetition

comment:
(ratioOfCollectionToDifferentiatedCollection MOD COLL DIFFERENTIATOR-COLL NUM) holds just in case the ratio/percent/number of instances of COLL that also are instances of DIFFERENTIATOR-COLL is NUM. MOD tells the inference engine what format to return the answer -- either a ratio, percent, or non-negative integer. DIFFERENTIATOR-COLL is a collection that specifies the additional condition -- usually constructed via some subcollection function. For example, If we wanted to ask what is the percentage of bombings performed by Hamas that are terrorist suicide bombings we would use the following formula: 
(ratioOfCollectionToDifferentiatedCollection Percent
 (CollectionSubsetFn TerroristAttack 
  (TheSetOf ?ACT
    (and
    (performedBy ?ACT #$TerroristOrganization-Hamas)
    (isa ?ACT Bombing))))
      TerroristSuicideBombing  ?NUM)

.
label: Ratio Of Collection To Differentiated Collection
ratioOfCollectionToDifferentiatedCollection

comment: (kePredArgWeakSuggestionPreds PRED N BINPRED) means that if the relation expression (PRED . ARGS) is known, and ARGN appears as the Nth argument in (PRED . ARGS) it is weakly suggested that Cyc know there exists a THING such that (BINPRED ARGN THING).
label: Ke Pred Arg Weak Suggestion Preds
kePredArgWeakSuggestionPreds

comment: An assertion of the form (literalHasRealNumberInArg LIT NUMBER N) states that the RealNumber NUMBER is the value of the Nth argument in the (CycLObjectTypeFn CycLAtomicSentence) LIT.
label: Literal Has Real Number In Arg
literalHasRealNumberInArg

comment: powerInRegion_Generic specifies the degree of power or influence that some IntelligentAgent has in some GeographicalRegion. (powerInRegion_Generic AGENT REGION GENERIC-VALUE) means that AGENT's level of power or influence in REGION is GENERIC-VALUE. To specify the exact type of power involved, see powerInRegion_Economic, powerInRegion_Military, powerInRegion_Geopolitical.
label: Power In Region Generic
powerInRegion-Generic

comment: (moreVulnerableToBecause AGENT EVTTYPE ROLE PROP) means that there is an increased chance of AGENT's playing the role ROLE in a situation of type EVTTYPE because PROP is true (increasedChanceForRoleBecause AGENT EVTTYPE ROLE PROP) and AGENT has the goals (not (ROLE EVTTYPE AGENT)).
label: More Vulnerable To Because
moreVulnerableToBecause

comment: (physicalPartTypeCount OBJ-TYPE PART-TYPE INT) means that INT is the number of parts of type PART-TYPE that elements of the set OBJ-TYPE have. See also hasPhysicalPartCount.
label: Physical Part Type Count
physicalPartTypeCount

comment: (kEInteractionFolderOfUserForTask AGENT ALLOTMENT FOLDER) means that FOLDER is the KEInteractionFolder associated with the IntelligentAgent AGENT, for the task ALLOTMENT.
label: KE Interaction Folder Of User For Task
kEInteractionFolderOfUserForTask

comment: (correspondenceBetween CORR BASE-ITEM TARGET-ITEM) represents the hypothesis that BASE-ITEM matches TARGET-ITEM. BASE-ITEM and TARGET-ITEM can be entities, functors, or expressions of AnalogyCases. Mappings include a set of structurally consistent correspondences. For example, comparing WW-II to the Gulf war may produce a correspondence between Germany and Iraq.
label: Correspondence Between
correspondenceBetween

comment: (caloricContentOfFood EDIBLESTUFF MASS CAL) means that MASS of EDIBLESTUFF, if burned, releases CAL of energy. CAL will generally be stated using the unit function Kilocalorie. For example, (caloricContent PeachPie001 (Gram 1) (Kilocalorie 7)) means that PeachPie001 has 7 Calories per gram. Unlike caloricContent, caloricContentOfFood allows qualitative values like (HighAmountFn EnergyQuantity) in addition to quantitative values like (Kilocalorie 400). A qualitative value indicates the substance's caloric content relative to some relevant specialization of EdibleStuff, but usually the collection EdibleStuff itself.
label: Caloric Content Of Food
caloricContentOfFood

comment: (supplyFromAmount PT1 COL PT2 AMOUNT) means that the ScalarInterval AMOUNT is a measure of the amount of instances of the Collection COL with which the instance of PartiallyTangible PT1 is supplied from the instance of PartiallyTangible PT2. Like the predicate suppliedWith (q.v.), supplyFromAmount is very general. In various assertions PT1 might, for instance, be a Cell, a Person, a Business, or a GeographicalRegion; and likewise for PT2. The range of possible supplies is similarly broad.
label: Supply From Amount
supplyFromAmount

comment: (physicianInRoleForOperationHasName EVENT ROLE NAME-STRING) means that NAME-STRING is the name of the physician who plays ROLE in EVENT.
label: Physician In Role For Operation Has Name
physicianInRoleForOperationHasName

comment: A ternary VulnerabilityPredicate. (vulnerableTo_RoleInType OBJ TYPE ROLE) says that OBJ is vulnerable to playing ROLE in some instance of TYPE. The notion of 'vulnerability' here is to be cashed out in terms of an agent's interests or desires being thwarted if some instance INS of TYPE in which (ROLE INS TYPE) were to become true. That agent need not be identical to OBJ, though often will be.
label: vulnerability in situation
vulnerableTo-RoleInType

comment:
(benefitsForRolePlayerInSitTypeWRTAgentType AGENT-TYPE ROLE SIT-TYPE BENEFIT-SENTENCE)
holds just in case instances of AGENT-TYPE playing ROLE in instances of SIT-TYPE will gain the benefit described by BENEFIT-SENTENCE.
label: Benefits For Role Player In Sit Type WRT Agent Type
benefitsForRolePlayerInSitTypeWRTAgentType

comment: (assertionDirectionForProjectBuilds ASSERTION ASSERTION-DIRECTION PROJECT) means that the project PROJECT requires its builds (see #$SoftwareBuild) to be such that the assertion (c.f., CycLAssertion) have an assertion-direction (c.f., CycLAssertionDirection) of ASSERTION-DIRECTION.
label: Assertion Direction For Project Builds
assertionDirectionForProjectBuilds

comment: (totalReserves COUNTRY PRODUCT-TYPE AMOUNT) expresses the total reserves of a organization such as a GeopoliticalEntity for PRODUCT-TYPE. A useful example is (totalReserves COUNTRY Petroleum_CrudeOil VOLUME). The amount of oil held in reserve has an impact on the economy of the region. This predicate refers to the amount of PRODUCT-TYPE that is proven to exist at some time. It is often the case that estimates exceed the proven reserves, and often new sources are found so the reserves increase.
label: Total Reserves
totalReserves

comment: (#$toIndividualGLFLiteArc NODE1 NODE2 SYSTEM ARC) means that ARC is the SOEToIndividualArc that links NODE1 to NODE2 in SYSTEM, and that ARC has (InverseBinaryPredicateFn isa) as its semantics.
label: To Individual GLF Arc
toIndividualGLFArc

comment: (terrainAdvantage_DimensionDegree LOC TAC-DIM ADV-AMT) means that the location LOC has the tactical potential to provide some advantage along the tactical dimension TAC-DIM, to the degree ADV-AMT. TAC-DIM must be some recognized tactical aspect of a military situation, such as a dimension of the UnitedStatesArmy's OCOKA terrain analysis or METT-T situation analysis. For example, (terrainAdvantage_SideDegree Hill28 ObservationFacilitatingTerrain (HighAmountFn TacticalAdvantage)) means that Hill28 has the potential to facilitate observation, and so offer a high degree of TacticalAdvantage. Note that TacticalAdvantages depend not just on terrain characteristics, but also on force and situation characteristics, and therefore belong to agents in fairly specific classes of real or potential military operations. For this reason, assertions stating the terrainAdvantage-DimensionDegree for some piece of terrain should be made only within appropriately scenario-specific contexts.
label: Terrain Advantage Dimension Degree
terrainAdvantage-DimensionDegree

comment: (hasQuantityWithRespectTo THING VAL RES) means that the instance of the collection Thing, THING, has the quantity VAL, an instance of the collection Quantity with respect to RES, an instance of the collection Thing. For instance, (hasQuantityWithRespectTo Juggling Difficult Bob) means that juggling is difficult at least with respect to Bob.
label: Has Quantity With Respect To
hasQuantityWithRespectTo

comment: (closerTo OBJ NEAR FAR) iff OBJ is closer to NEAR than to FAR. For example, (closerTo Sun PlanetMercury PlanetVenus).
label: Closer To
closerTo
Area To Control
areaToControl
comment: a MilitarilySignificantArea is to be controlled in the goal context.

(differWRTSet THING1 THING2 SET) means that THING1 belongs to SET, while THING2 does not. SET will often be an expression of the form (TheSetOf VAR FORMULA). In such cases, the meaning of the overall expression is that THING1 satisfies FORMULA (belongs to the set of things which satisfy FORMULA), while THING2 does not. This fact should be a salient difference between THING1 and THING2, i.e. a relevant point of comparison.
label: Differ WRT Set
differWRTSet

comment: (partsPartition_Binary WHOLE PART-1 PART-2) says that PART-1 and ?PART-2 form a partition of WHOLE. In other words, PART-1 and PART-2 have no parts in common, and together, PART-1 and PART-2 form WHOLE in its entirety.
label: Parts Partition Binary
partsPartition-Binary

comment:
epistemicRule is a specialization of nonAbducibleRule (q.v.). It is used to indicate that a rule's antecendent states merely epistemic (not physical or metaphysical) and hence non-explanatory sufficient conditions for the truth of its consequent. For example, 

  (epistemicRule
    (implies
      (and
        (isa ?EVENT SchedulingASocialDinnerAtRestaurant)
        (performedBy ?EVENT ?USER)
        (socialParticipants ?EVENT ?INVITEE))
      (likesAsFriend ?USER ?INVITEE)))

means that the fact that one person successfully invites another to a social dinner at a restaurant provides a good reason to believe that the inviter likes the invitee as a friend, but it does not explain the fact that the two people are friends.
label: Epistemic Rule
epistemicRule

comment: (halfReactionCoefficients SUBST1 SUBST2 COEFFICIENT1 COEFFICIENT2 CHARGE) means that the half reaction representing the reduction of SUBST1 into SUBST2 can be represented as a balanced half reaction as "COEFFICIENT1 SUBST1 + CHARGE e- -> COEFFICIENT2 SUBST2". See halfReaction for more details.
label: half-reaction reduction equation
halfReactionCoefficients

comment: An instance of both FunctionalPredicate and QuaternaryPredicate. (lethalConcentrationForOrganismType SUBSTANCE-TYPE PERCENTAGE ORGANISM CONCENTRATION) means that exposure to CONCENTRATION of SUBSTANCE-TYPE will kill PERCENTAGE of ORGANISM-TYPE.
label: lethal concentration
lethalConcentrationForOrganismType

comment: An instance of RuleMacroPredicate, (agreementAuthorizationIsaCondition AUTHORITY PRED COLL) means that any instance INS of Agreement authorized by AUTHORITY and any thing THING such that (PRED INS THING), (isa THING COLL) must hold. Otherwise, AUTHORITY cannot authorize INS.
label: Agreement Authorization Isa Condition
agreementAuthorizationIsaCondition

comment: (potentialCollaboratorConcept COL-OP USER CONCEPT) means that Cyc has detected a potential collaboration opportunity, COL-OP, between the CAE user USER, working on topic CONCEPT and other CAE users.
label: Potential Collaborator Concept
potentialCollaboratorConcept

comment: (grammaticalRoleWRTRelationMention RM EM ROLE) means that EM, an instance of #$EntityMentionHypothesis, fills the grammatical role ROLE wrt. the #$RelationMentionHypothesis RM. So, for example, given a sentence like "the cat is on the mat", we can use (grammaticalRoleWRTRelationMention RM1 EM1 SubjectRoleMarker) to indicate that the #$EntityMentionHypothesis corresponding to this occurnace of "the cat"(EM1) fills the subject role in the #$RelationMentionHypothesis (RM1) associated with this sentence.
label: Grammatical Role WRT Relation Mention
grammaticalRoleWRTRelationMention

comment: (clinicalFormMostCommonInOrgType_Infection INF-GEN-TYPE ORG-TYPE INF-SPEC-TYPE) means that if an infection INF is known to be an instance of INF-GEN-TYPE, and an instance of ORG-TYPE is known to be the bodilyDoer of INF, it is extremely likely, absent information to support the conclusion (not (isa INF INF-SPEC-TYPE)), that (isa INF INF-SPEC-TYPE).
label: Clinical Form Most Common In Org Type Infection
clinicalFormMostCommonInOrgType-Infection

comment: (maxRangeForSightUnderAmbientCondition SIGHTTYPE CONDITION DISTANCE) means that the maximum effective range for SIGHTTYPE under the ambient conditon CONDITION is DISTANCE.
label: Max Range For Sight Under Ambient Condition
maxRangeForSightUnderAmbientCondition

comment: (fieldValueIsTransformedViaInSKS SKS NAME TRANSFORMATION) means that the value of the logical field indexical corresponding to NAME should undergo TRANSFORMATION before being output to the document.
label: Field Value Is Transformed Via In SKS
fieldValueIsTransformedViaInSKS

comment: (exposureLimitOverTime SUBSTANCE LIMIT EXP-DURATION EXP-PARAMETER OVER-DURATION OVER-PARAMETER) means that LIMIT is the limit of SUBSTANCE a normal, healthy adult may be exposed to in the duration of EXP-DURATION for the parameter EXP-PARAMETER over the period of OVER-DURATION for OVER-PARAMETER. Essentially, (exposureLimitOverTime ?SUBSTANCE (PartsPerMillion 400) (HoursDuration 8) Weekday (HoursDuration 40) CalendarWorkWeek) means that a healthy human adult should not be exposed to more than 400 ppm of SUBSTANCE during an 8 hour work day for any given 40 hour work week. Substances may have more than one exposure limit.
Mx4rwLSVCpwpEbGdrcN5Y29ycA: exposure limits over a period of time
label: exposure limit over a period of time
exposureLimitOverTime

comment: The predicate includesWithProductType is used to specify extra goods or services that a particular seller includes with a specific product. (includesWithProductType SELLER MAINTYPE EXTRATYPE) means that the CommercialOrganization SELLER provides an item of the ProductType EXTRATYPE free of charge to its customers who purchase a product of ProductType MAINTYPE. For example, to say that Ernie's Garage provides towing free with a car repair, we could say (includesWithProductType ErniesGarage (RepairingFn Automobile) TowingAnAutomobile).
label: including
includesWithProductType

comment: (multiWordStringTemplate LIST WORD POS TEMPLATE) says that TEMPLATE captures the meaning of one of the phrases for which WORD with part of speech POS, is the head, and the string given in LIST is the modifying phrase. This predicate is used in conjunction with multiWordStringDenotesArgInReln to provide denotations for words whose meaning is best expressed in CycL using relations. For example, sentences in which the nbar "biological mother(s)" occur (e.g., "everyone has one biological mother") are best expressed in CycL using the relation biologicalMother (e.g., (relationAllExistsUnique biologicalMother Person FemaleAnimal)). However, since biologicalMother is an inappropriate denotation for the phrase "biological mother," instead of asserting (multiWordString ("biological") #$Mother-TheWord CountNoun biologicalMother), we infer from (multiWordStringDenotesArgInReln ("biological") #$Mother-TheWord CountNoun biologicalMother) that the meaning of the phrase "biological mother(s)" is best expressed through a template: (SubcollectionOfWithRelationToTypeFn FemaleAnimal biologicalMother Animal). Thus the inferred assertion, (multiWordStringTemplate ("biological") #$Mother-TheWord CountNoun (SubcollectionOfWithRelationToTypeFn FemaleAnimal biologicalMother Animal)) allows us to parse "biological mother(s)" into this form, without requiring us to add unnecessary collections to the KB.
label: Multi Word String Template
multiWordStringTemplate

comment: (no_GenQuantRelnFrom RELN THING COL) is true iff there is no INST such that INST is an element of COL and (RELN THING INST) holds.
label: No Gen Quant Reln From
no-GenQuantRelnFrom
Failed Goal
failedGoal
comment: (failedGoal GOAL-SENTENCE) means that, in the current planner-state, the planner has tried to find plans for GOAL-SENTENCE and failed. For example: (failedGoal (doGetLoginInformationForAccount AGENT ACCOUNT)) means that, in the current state of the planning domain, the planner has already tried and failed to solve (doGetLoginInformationForAccount AGENT ACCOUNT).

(objectEmitsObjectInEmission EVENT EMITTER EMITTED) can hold for an Emission iff (emitter EVENT EMITTER) and (objectEmitted EVENT EMITTED) hold as well. If there are multiple emitters and objectEmitteds during an Emission, it may take some detective work to link up particular pairs; but if there's only 1 of each, the relationship can easily be determined.
label: Object Emits Object In Emission
objectEmitsObjectInEmission
subPropertyOf: Object Acts On Object In Event

comment: (deprecatedSalientDescriptorRule RULE) means that RULE should not be used to generate Salient Descriptor interview questions.
label: Deprecated Salient Descriptor Rule Assertion
deprecatedSalientDescriptorRuleAssertion

comment: (kePredArgStrongSuggestionInverse PRED N BINPRED) means that if a CycLFormula of the form (PRED ARG1 ... ARGK) is known, and ARGN (where N is greaterThanOrEqualTo 1 and lessThanOrEqualTo K) appears as the Nth argument in (PRED ARG1 ... ARGK), it is strongly suggested that there exists a THING such that (BINPRED THING ARGN) is known in the Knowledge Base.
label: Ke Pred Arg Strong Suggestion Inverse
kePredArgStrongSuggestionInverse
Irrelevant Assertion
irrelevantAssertion
comment: A CycInferenceHeuristicRelevancePredicate. (irrelevantAssertion ASSERTION) states that the CycLAssertion ASSERTION should be heuristically considered very unlikely to be relevant to inferences in the current Microtheory. See also other instances of CycInferenceHeuristicRelevancePredicate.
Arg3 is the smallest dollar amount of arg2 that may be purchased under the terms of the agreement arg1.  Any smaller purchase is not governed by the terms of arg1.
label: Min Contract Amount
minContractAmount

comment: (rangeForSightUnderIlluminationCondition SIGHTTYPE CONDITION RNAGE) means that the maximum effective range for SIGHTTYPE under the lighting conditon CONDITION (an instance of OutdoorLocationTypeByIlluminationSource) is RNAGE.
label: Range For Sight Under Illumination Condition
rangeForSightUnderIlluminationCondition
subPropertyOf: Max Range For Sight Under Ambient Condition

comment: This event-predicate template expresses the relation between the object transported, the point of departure and the point of arrival in types of activity subsumed by TransportationEvent. Example: (transportedToFrom_EPFT (TransportViaFn AirTransportationDevice) THING LOC-TO LOC-FROM) is true iff THING is (being) transported by air from place LOC-FROM to place LOC-TO. The associateSlotInArg condition for arg2 implies that THING is distinct from the conveyor of transportation -- the package on the plane, e.g. or the pilot, but not the plane itself.
label: Transported To From EPFT
transportedToFrom-EPFT

comment: A quaternary complex action predicate. (doProgramOutputLineToStream PROGRAMMER FILE STRING STREAM) means that PROGRAMMER appends code the end of FILE which will, when executed, write STRING to STREAM, an instance of DataStream.
label: Do Program Output Line To Stream
doProgramOutputLineToStream

comment: A ternary instance of InterArgIsaPredicate (q.v.). (interArgIsa4_2 RELN INDEPENDENT-ARG-COL DEPENDENT-ARG-COL) means that, when an instance of INDEPENDENT-ARG-COL appears as the fourth argument to RELN, a necessary condition for semantic well-formedness is that the second argument must be an instance of DEPENDENT-ARG-COL. That is, if INST is an instance of INDEPENDENT-ARG-COL, then (RELN ARG1 ARG2 ARG3 INST ... ARGN) is semantically well-formed only if ARG2 is an instance of DEPENDENT-ARG-COL. For an explanation of semantic well-formedness, see CycLExpression_Assertible and its direct specializations.
label: Inter Arg Isa 4 2
interArgIsa4-2

comment: (doRemoteBufferOverflowAttack AGENT COMPUTER TARGET) means that AGENT performs a buffer overflow attack on TARGET using COMPUTER. It is "remote" in the sense that it exploits a program listening on a port on TARGET. Cf. doLocalBufferOverflowAttack.
label: Do Remote Buffer Overflow Attack
doRemoteBufferOverflowAttack

comment: (tourTransitUsesPath TOUR MOVETYPE PATH) means that TOUR is expected to include a TransportationEvent of type MOVETYPE that has PATH as it's motionPathway_Partial, according to the itinerary.
label: Tour Transit Uses Path
tourTransitUsesPath

comment: (typeInstancesStartAfterEndOfIn LATERTYPE EARLYTYPE MAINTYPE) means that in instances of MAINTYPE, an instance of EARLYTYPE will be followed by an instance of LATERTYPE. Note that this is consistent with no event of type EARLYTYPE occurring in the event of MAINTYPE and a different instance of LATERTYPE occurring prior to an instance of EARLYTYPE in an instance of MAINTYPE. This is closely related to startsAfterEndOfInSituationType but is not restricted to use in #$ScriptedEventTypes and allows for use of more general arguments than those in the range of #$SceneFn.
label: Type Instances Start After End Of In
typeInstancesStartAfterEndOfIn

comment: (nBarPresupposesOfDenotWithRemainder NBAR DENOT SENTENCES UNPRESUPPOSED) means that if NBAR is predicated of DENOT, then NBAR presupposes all sentences in SENTENCES except for those in UNPRESUPPOSED.
label: N Bar Presupposes Of Denot With Remainder
nBarPresupposesOfDenotWithRemainder

comment: The purpose of this predicate is to relate SystemRolePredicates (i.e., relations representing functional roles) to their corresponding ActorSlots (i.e., relations representing the roles that agents play in events). (entailsRoleInEventOfType SYS-SLOT EVENT-TYPE SYS-ACT-SLOT AGT-ACT-SLOT) means that if an agent plays the functional role SYS-SLOT in a particular functional system, and that system in turn plays the role SYS-ACT-SLOT in an event of type EVENT-TYPE, then the agent will play the role AGT-ACT-SLOT in that same event.
label: Entails Role In Event Of Type
entailsRoleInEventOfType

comment: A predicate that uniquely identifies an explicitly defined RelationshipDefiningSchema by a Predicate and a list of ObjectDefiningSchemas which correspond to the entities that participate in the relationship. (explicitRelationshipPredicateList RDS PREDICATE ODS-LIST) means that RDS is the logical schema that describes the relationship that holds between the entities described by the members of ODS-LIST. The relationship is expressed in the Cyc ontology as sentences using PREDICATE. The order of the ObjectDefiningSchemas in ODS-LIST determines the order in which the entities appear in PREDICATE sentences. In addition, there are several necessary conditions for RDSes to be well defined using this predicate. See also the corresponding function ExplicitRelationshipDefiningSchemaFn and the exceptions (exceptWhen meta assertions) on its generating rule.
label: Explicit Relationship Predicate List
explicitRelationshipPredicateList

comment: (scoreInAction AGENT ACT VAL) states that AGENT achieved a score of VAL in the action ACT.
label: Score In Action
scoreInAction

comment: A ternary instance of InterArgIsaPredicate (q.v.). (interArgIsa1_5 RELN INDEPENDENT-ARG-COL DEPENDENT-ARG-COL) means that, when an instance of INDEPENDENT-ARG-COL appears as the first argument to RELN, a necessary condition for semantic well-formedness is that the fifth argument must be an instance of DEPENDENT-ARG-COL. That is, if INST is an instance of INDEPENDENT-ARG-COL, then (RELN INST ARG2 ARG3 ARG4 ARG5 ... ARGN) is semantically well-formed only if ARG5 is an instance of DEPENDENT-ARG-COL. For an explanation of semantic well-formedness, see CycLExpression_Assertible and its direct specializations.
label: Inter Arg Isa 1 5
interArgIsa1-5

comment: (typesSimilarWRTPartType TYPE1 TYPE2 PART-TYPE) means that instances of TYPE1 and TYPE2 will be related to PART-TYPE via the relationship similarWRTPartType.
label: Types Similar WRT Part Type
typesSimilarWRTPartType

comment: (unclearSentence SENTENCE) means that the generation of CycLPropositionalSentence SENTENCE (which is usually the subject of a #$suggestedSentence assertion) is not a clearly formed natural-language sentence. Clearly formed, in this case, means that the sentence would be readily understood by anyone with no special training, but with a fluent grasp of the language. For example, "Cyndy Matuszek is viscidity." does not express an obvious concept in English, nor does the sentence "Abduced term fn cyc problem store fn 4412 agent 279 considers Libya an enemy."
label: Unclear Sentence
unclearSentence
Has Pathology Associated With Valve Type
hasPathologyAssociatedWithValveType

comment: A predicate used for indicating regular increases to an Agent_PartiallyTangible's account. (increaseToAccount AGENT ACCOUNT FREQ AMOUNT) means that the ScalarInterval AMOUNT is added to the Agent_PartiallyTangible AGENT's AccountType ACCOUNT at Frequency FREQ intervals. See incomeToAccount for cases where AMOUNT is an instance of MonetaryValue.
label: Increase To Account
increaseToAccount

comment: (predicateRuleEquivalent PRED PRED-FORMULA RULE-FORMULA) states that for a rule macro predicate PRED, each use of the predicate which unifies with PRED-FORMULA will result in the addition to the system of a rule of the form RULE-FORMULA. For example, one could implement genlInverse via : (predicateRuleEquivalent genlInverse (genlInverse ?SPEC-PRED ?GENL-PRED) (implies (?SPEC-PRED ?ARG1 ?ARG2) (?GENL-PRED ?ARG2 ?ARG1))).
label: Predicate Rule Equivalent
predicateRuleEquivalent

comment: (percentOfAttacksAgainstTypeWithInfoTranferTypeByPerp PERCENT TARGET-TYPE INFO-TRANFER-TYPE PERP) holds just in case the percentage of terrorist attacks against targets of type TARGET-TYPE by PERP that had associated information transfers of type INFO-TRANFER-TYPE is PERCENT.
label: Percent Of Attacks Against Type With Info Tranfer Type By Perp
percentOfAttacksAgainstTypeWithInfoTranferTypeByPerp

comment: (documentsRequiredOnTour TOUR PERSON CREDENTIAL) means that PERSON is required to have some instance of CREDENTIAL issued to him/her in order to participate in the instance of TravelTour TOUR.
label: Documents Required On Tour
documentsRequiredOnTour

comment: A ternary instance of InterArgIsaPredicate (q.v.). (interArgIsa5_2 RELN INDEPENDENT-ARG-COL DEPENDENT-ARG-COL) means that, when an instance of INDEPENDENT-ARG-COL appears as the fifth argument to RELN, a necessary condition for semantic well-formedness is that the second argument must be an instance of DEPENDENT-ARG-COL. That is, if INST is an instance of INDEPENDENT-ARG-COL, then (RELN ARG1 ARG2 ARG3 ARG4 INST ... ARGN) is semantically well-formed only if ARG2 is an instance of DEPENDENT-ARG-COL. For an explanation of semantic well-formedness, see CycLExpression_Assertible and its direct specializations.
label: Inter Arg Isa 5 2
interArgIsa5-2

comment:
This predicate relates human cultures to types of practices that are characteristic of and important to their participants. (culturePractices CULTURE ACTTYPE ROLE) means that most or many participants in CULTURE play ROLE in instances of ACTTYPE from time to time, and would (at least upon reflection) consider such activities important to or distinctive of CULTURE. These activities might be ones commonly engaged in on a regular basis (like praying thrice daily), or might be ones normally engaged in only in particular situations or on special occasions (like joining in group singing at parties); all that's essential is that many or most participants in the culture do them sometimes.

For a similar predicate that applies to practices distinctive of a culture but participated in by only a relatively small, specialized subcollection of its participants, see cultureSpecialPractices.

Note that when using this predicate it is important to avoid unjustified stereotypes of the culture in question and to refrain from relating the culture to practices that do not accurately characterize it.
label: Culture Practices
culturePractices

comment: (dataForValveOfEventRecordsOrificeArea VALVE EVENT AREA) means that according to the VALVE associated with EVENT (an instance of CardiacCatheterization or Echocardiogram) the focal valve has the orifice area AREA.
label: valve area
dataForValveOfEventRecordsOrificeArea

comment: (requiredTypeForSubSituationType_Many TYPE SITTYPE SUBSITTYPE) means that many instances of TYPE are constituents (cf. situationConstituents) in every instance of SUBSITTYPE in any instance of SITTYPE.
label: Required Type For Sub Situation Type Many
requiredTypeForSubSituationType-Many

comment: This predicate relates infection types, organism types and levels of risk. (riskOfInfectionFromTypeToType INFTYPE INFECTEDORGTYPE ENDANGEREDORGTYPE RISKLEVEL) means that if an organism of type INFECTEDORGTYPE carries the infection, INFTYPE, the likelihood that it will infect organisms of type ENDANGEREDORGTYPE if it comes into contact with such organisms is RISKLEVEL.
label: Risk Of Infection From Type To Type
riskOfInfectionFromTypeToType

comment: (genlsConstraintForNCR RULE INDEXICAL COL) means that RULE constrains its NounCompoundRuleIndexicalTerm_Direct term INDEXICAL to denote a subcollection of COL. In general, the means that there is a ncRuleConstraint linking RULE to (NCGenlsConstraintFn INDEXICAL TYPE) where TYPE is some spec of COL.
label: Genls Constraint For NCR
genlsConstraintForNCR

comment:
A ternary FacetBasisPredicate (q.v.) that relates a collection to a type-level binary predicate to a FacetingCollectionType such that the latter facets the collection on the basis of the predicate. (facetOfCollectionBasedOnBinaryPred COL BINPRED FACET) means that both (facets_Generic COL FACET) and (facetBasedOnTypeBinaryPred FACET BINPRED) hold.

See also the corresponding function FacetOfCollectionBasedOnTypeBinaryPredFn.
label: Facet Of Collection Based On Type Binary Pred
facetOfCollectionBasedOnTypeBinaryPred

comment: (tourNightLocation TOUR DAY REGION) means that TOUR spends the night in REGION on the CalendarDay DAY.
label: Tour Night Location
tourNightLocation

comment:
A ternary CotemporalPredicate that is used to state that an agent introduces a second agent to a third agent. (introducesTo PRESENTER PRESENTEE PRESENTED-TO) means that PRESENTER introduces PRESENTEE to PRESENTED-TO.

Note that the above does not entail that (introducesTo PRESENTER PRESENTED-TO PRESENTEE), though it strongly suggests it, since in most social circumstances two agents normally get introduced to each other at the same (or nearly the same) time.

It is assumed that, just prior to the introduction, PRESENTER is mutually acquainted with both of the other parties, and PRESENTED-TO is not acquainted with PRESENTEE. (PRESENTEE might conceivably be already acquainted with PRESENTED-TO, as the latter might already have been introduced to the former.) Just after the introduction, of course, PRESENTED-TO is acquainted with PRESENTEE.
label: Introduces To
introducesTo

comment: (keComparisonSentences TERM1 TERM2 SENTENCE1) means that SENTENCE1 has the following properties: it mentions TERM1, it remains true if TERM2 is substituted for TERM1, it contains no keIrrelevantTerms, and it is useful for comparing TERM1 and TERM2.
label: Ke Comparison Sentences
keComparisonSentences
To Do Sub Situation Type In Situation
toDo-SubSituationTypeInSituation
Vulnerability Bulletin DOD
vulnerabilityBulletin-DOD
comment: vulnerabilityBulletin_DOD is a unary predicate used to assert that a CycLAssertion expresses information contained in a vulnerability bulletin (IAVB) on the DOD CERT webpage at http://www.cert.mil/iava/index.htm.

(positionSanctionedByOrganization AGT POS ORG) says that the fact that (occupation AGT POS) is officially sanctioned by ORG. Typically, this will hold where AGT holds POS as an employee of ORG, but this need not be the case. For example (positionSanctionedByOrganization #$JohnPaulII Pope CollegeOfCardinals) holds by virtue of the process by which popes are selected, and not by virtue of the pope being an employee of the college (he's not).
label: Position Sanctioned By Organization
positionSanctionedByOrganization

comment: (istIncreasesSlotValue INDPROP DEPPROP SLOT) means that the value that SLOT takes in the arg2 position for DEPPROP will be greater if INDPROP is provable than it will be if INDPROP is not provable.
label: Ist Increases Slot Value
istIncreasesSlotValue

comment: An assertion of the form (mostRequestedInstanceOfCollForOrgDuring INDIVIDUAL COLLECTION ORGANIZATION INTERVAL) is used to express the most 'in demand' element of a collection of resources for a particular organization during a particular time interval. So, INDIVDIUAL would be the instance of the FirstOrderCollection COLLECTION that the Organization has some rights over (i.e., employees) during the ContinuousTimeInterval INTERVAL. So, the assertion (mostRequestedInstanceOfCollForOrgDuring #$Goolsbey #$CurrentCycorpEmployee Cycorp (MonthFn March (YearFn 2004))) would mean that #$Goolsbey is the most requested instance of #$CurrentCycorpEmployee by Cycorp for March, 2004.
label: Most Requested Instance Of Coll For Org During
mostRequestedInstanceOfCollForOrgDuring

comment: If INTEGRATION is an IntegratingASetOfKnowledgeSources, COLL is a Collection, and ODS is an ObjectDefiningSchema, then (schemaIntegrationTypeForTargetODS INTEGRATION COLL ODS) means that ODS is the target object defining schema of type COLL (see schemaIsa) in the schema integration event INTEGRATION.
label: Schema Integration Type For Target ODS
schemaIntegrationTypeForTargetODS

comment: (facilityOperatingTimes FACILTY DAY OPEN CLOSE) means that the Facility_Construct FACILITY is 'open' from TimeOfDay OPEN to TimeOfDay CLOSE on DAY.
label: Facility Operating Times
facilityOperatingTimes

comment: For the things on ARG1's ARG2 slot, the number of different entries on their ARG3 slot is ARG4 when compared to other instance of ARG5. For example, we might say (relativeVarietyOn SevenEleven001 sellsProductType insMarketedAs Medium RetailStore) to say that SevenEleven001 sells products that fall into a medium-large number of market categories, when compared with other RetailStores
label: Relative Variety On
relativeVarietyOn

comment: In ?mh of ?mapping, ?bisas is a set of ISA statements about items in the base that are different from the ISA statements about the corresponding target items in ?tisas
label: Role Difference Of
roleDifferenceOf

Mx4rwLSVCpwpEbGdrcN5Y29ycA: marching speeds of vehicle on terrain
label: marching speed of vehicle on terrain
marchSpeedOfVehicleTypeOnTerrain

comment: (softwareParameterSetToValueInSpecification SOFTWARE-PARAMETER VALUE PROGRAM-SPEC) mea ns that the value of SOFTWARE-PARAMETER [see softwareParameterValue] is set to the value VALUE at some point during any execution of PROGRAM-SPEC (an instance of ProgramSpecification). This normally means that the value changes, but it is possible that the value it is set to is its prior value.
label: Software Parameter Set To Value In Specification
softwareParameterSetToValueInSpecification

comment: The amount, in dollars, of arg2 purchased in arg1.
label: Amount Purchased
amountPurchased

comment: ARG1 has a relationship with ARG3, such that if ARG1 needs to consult a professional of type ARG2, by default they will go to ARG3 first.
label: Regular Personal Service Provider
regularPersonalServiceProvider

comment: An assertion of the form (argGenlsConstantModeForDetermination PRED N TYPE DET) means that relative to the InductiveLogicProgrammingDetermination DET, the Nth argument of the Predicate PRED should bea sub-collection of the Collection TYPE and that argument position has a constant mode (i.e., for the induction of rules, that argument must have a constant as its value and cannot take a variable). The sense of mode here is derived from Prolog_ComputerLanguage.
label: Arg Genls Constant Mode For Determination
argGenlsConstantModeForDetermination

comment: (queryHasPertinenceForThing QUERY THING DEGREE) means that QUERY (an instance of CycLQuerySpecification) has the pertinence DEGREE whenever THING has a non-zero pertinence.
label: Query Has Pertinence For Thing
queryHasPertinenceForThing

comment: (successfulForTaskMt TASK MT1 MT2 means that MT1 is a context in which TASK, as specified in the course of action MT2, is assumed to be successfully carried out.
label: successful task in context
successfulForTaskMt

comment: arg1 is both the performer and directingAgent of the instances of arg3 in which arg2 is the recipient. For example, we may say (directingPerformsFor SeniorSecretary001 JuniorSecretary001 AdministrativeSupervision). This implies that arg1 has some authority over arg2 particularly when arg1 is performing instances of arg3 where arg2 is the recipient.
label: Directing Performs For
directingPerformsFor

comment: sendDataOfTypeToSystem is an ActionPredicate relating instances of IntelligentAgent with subcollections of InformationStore and instances of ComputationalSystem. (sendDataOfTypeToSystem AGENT DATATYPE SYSTEM) means that AGENT remotely sends data of type DATATYPE to SYSTEM.
label: Send Data Of Type To System
sendDataOfTypeToSystem

comment:
A variable-arity MetaRelation used for stating that a given PartiallyCommutativeRelation (q.v.) is "commutative" with respect to two or more specified argument-places.

(commutativeInArgs RELN ARGNUM-1 ... ARGNUM-N) means that RELN is commutative in its ARGNUM-1th, ..., and ARGNUM-Nth arguments. Thus RELN admits unrestricted permutation among these arguments. More precisely: (i) if RELN is a Predicate that holds of a given argument-sequence SEQ, then RELN also holds of any other sequence SEQ-PERMUTE obtainable from SEQ by permuting some or all of SEQ's ARGNUM-1th, ..., and ARGNUM-Nth items (while leaving all of SEQ's other items unchanged). (ii) if RELN is a Function_Denotational that associates a given argument-sequence SEQ with the value VALUE, then RELN also associates any sequence SEQ-PERMUTE (as described above) with VALUE.

For example, (commutativeInArgs formsBorderBetween 2 3) has as a consequence that whenever a sentence of the form (formsBorderBetween BORDER REG1 REG2) holds, so does the corresponding sentence (formsBorderBetween BORDER REG2 REG1).

If RELN is commutative in at least two argument-places it is an AtLeastPartiallyCommutativeRelation. If RELN is commutative in all argument-places it is, more specifically, a CommutativeRelation. If RELN is commutative in at least two, but not all, argument-places it is, instead, a PartiallyCommutativeRelation.

Note that the fact that each argument-place of a given relation commutes with some other argument-place is not sufficient for its being fully commutative. For example, a partially-commutative quaternary relation might be such that its first and third places commute with each other and its second and fourth places commute with each other.
label: Commutative In Args
commutativeInArgs

comment:
(maxSubsetConsistentWithElement SET-OF-COLLS COLL SUBSET-OF-COLLS) means that every element of SET-OF-COLLS that is not disjoint with COLL is an element of SUBSET-OF-COLLS, and that SUBSET-OF-COLLS is a subset of SET-OF-COLLS.

For example, 

(maxSubsetConsistentWithElement (TheSet Monarch_HeadOfState FemaleAnimal War) FemaleAnimal (TheSet FemaleAnimal Monarch_HeadOfState))

means that:
1. (TheSet FemaleAnimal Monarch_HeadOfState) is a subset of (TheSet Monarch_HeadOfState FemaleAnimal War), and
2. every element of (TheSet Monarch_HeadOfState FemaleAnimal) is is not disjoint with FemaleAnimal.
label: Max Subset Consistent With Element
maxSubsetConsistentWithElement

comment: This predicate relates a physical schema with the list of its physical fields that have the following property.  A particular specified value of one of the fields -- some value for a physical field indexical, cannot be in more than one field.  This is typically the case when the field types are disjoint classes.
label: Mutually Exclusive Schema Field List WRT
mutuallyExclusiveSchemaFieldListWRT

comment: This predicate relates an agent to the use rights which that agent has over an object. (userRightsRelation AGENT OBJECT URA) means that AGENT enjoys the SituationTypeByUserRights URA over OBJECT. URA is a collection of situations in which someone has a particular user right over an object. If the userRightsRelation holds, there is a user rights situation whose constituents include AGENT and OBJECT and in which OBJECT is the object of the user rights. Furthermore, this situation must be an instance of URA. For example, if AGENT owns OBJECT, then there exists a situation which consists of AGENT possessing certain "full use" rights to use OBJECT and this situation is an instance of FullUseRights.
label: User Rights Relation
userRightsRelation

comment: This relation is used to indicate that an instance of BinaryPredicate is pseudo-antisymmetic via a particular equivalence relation on a given collection. (pseudo_antisymmetricViaOn PRED EQ COL) means that if INS1 and INS2 are instances of COL and (PRED INS1 INS2) and (PRED INS2 INS1), then (EQ INS1 INS2).
label: Pseudoantisymmetric Via On
pseudo-antisymmetricViaOn

comment: (connectedInSystem X Y SYS) means that there is a path PATH in the PathSystem SYS such that (pathBetweenInSystem PATH X Y SYS) holds, or else X and Y are the same point in SYS. This predicate applies to a particular PathSystem, and the connectedness is an equivalence relation on that system, i.e., it is reflexive, transitive and symmetrical on that system.
label: Connected In System
connectedInSystem

comment: (interArgGenls PRED INDEPENDENT-ARG INDEPENDENT-COL DEPENDENT-ARG DEPENDENT-COL) means that, when a subset of INDEPENDENT-COL appears as argument # INDEPENDENT-ARG to PRED, argument # DEPENDENT-ARG in that assertion is constrained to be a subset of DEPENDENT-COL.
label: Inter Arg Genls
interArgGenls

comment: (suppliedWithThrough PT1 COL PT2) means that the instance of PartiallyTangible PT1 is supplied with instances of the Collection COL through the instance of PartiallyTangible PT2 (on their way from their origin to PT1). Like the predicate suppliedWith (q.v.), suppliedWithThrough is very general. In various assertions PT1 might, for instance, be a Cell, a Person, a Business, or a GeographicalRegion; and PT3 might, for example, be a Hose, a Railway, a GeographicalRegion, or a BloodVessel. The range of possible supplies is similarly broad.
label: Supplied With Through
suppliedWithThrough

comment: A ternary MetaRelation predicate for stating that a certain kind of complex, partly genls based relationship holds between the third argument to a given function and the corresponding value that is returned. (interArg2ResultGenls FUNC INDEPENDENT-ARG-COL DEPENDENT-ARG-COL) means that, when a subcollection of INDEPENDENT-ARG-COL appears as the third argument to FUNC, then -- regardless of what the other arguments to FUNC might be -- the value (if any) of that function for those arguments is a subcollection of DEPENDENT-ARG-COL. That is: if INST is a subcollection of INDEPENDENT-ARG-COL and (FUNC ARG1 ARG2 INST ...) = VALUE, then VALUE is a subcollection of DEPENDENT-ARG-COL. Note that, unlike (e.g.) the InterArgTypePredicates, interArg3ResultGenls _cannot_ be used to put semantic well-formedness constraints on functions. See also the similar but more flexible quaternary interArgResultGenl.
label: Inter Arg 3 Result Genls
interArg3ResultGenls

comment:
A TaxonomicPredicateForCollections that relates two collections to their nearest common generalizations represented in the Cyc Knowledge Base. (nearestCommonGenls COL1 COL2 NEAREST-GENL) means that (i) NEAREST-GENL in known in the Cyc Knowledge Base to subsume (via genls) both COL1 and COL2 and (ii) there is no proper specialization of NEAREST-GENL that is known to subsume both COL1 and COL2.

Note that nearestCommonGenls is not functional with respect to its third argument, as a pair of collections might have several nearest common generalizations, all orthogonal to each other. Note also that this predicate is notAssertible, since it must always be recomputed from the current state of the represented genls heirarchy.

See also nearestCommonIsa and nearestCommonSpecs.
label: Nearest Common Genls
nearestCommonGenls

comment: (registryKeySetToValueOnComputer KEY VALUE COMP) means that, on the Computer COMP, the RegistryKey KEY in the WindowsRegistry found on COMP is set to VALUE. See also registryKeyNotSetToValueOnComputer.
label: Registry Key Set To Value On Computer
registryKeySetToValueOnComputer

comment:
(closestEventOfTypePriorToContainsInstanceOfWithValueFor EVT1 EVT2 TYPE CONTAINED-TYPE PROPERTY) means that EVT1 is the nearest event of TYPE prior to EVT2 that contains some instance of CONTAINED-TYPE that has some value for PROPERTY. This entails that 
  
  (thereExists ?VALUE
   (thereExists ?CONT1
    (and
      (PROPERTY ?CONT1 ?VALUE)
      (#$cCF-contains EVT1 CONT1)
      (isa ?CONT1 CONTAINED-TYPE))))
In medical contexts it is assumed that both events involve the same patient.
label: Closest Event Of Type Prior To Contains Instance Of With Value For
closestEventOfTypePriorToContainsInstanceOfWithValueFor

comment: (hasImmunityWithRespectToDisease ORG IMM DISEASE-TYPE) means that ORG, an instance of Organism_Whole, has the type of immunity IMM, an #$ImmunityAttribute, with respect to diseases of the type DISEASE-TYPE. Org is also said insusceptible to diseases of the type DISEASE-TYPE. See immuneWithRespectToDisease. Contrast with hasImmunityWithRespectToOrg and immuneWithRespectToPathogen.
label: Has Immunity With Respect To Disease
hasImmunityWithRespectToDisease

comment: (decileRange DECILE_STRUCTURE N INTERVAL) means that the Nth decile in DECILE_STRUCTURE spans INTERVAL.
label: Decile Range
decileRange

comment: An instance of TernaryPredicate and SlotCalculationFormulaPredicate, used to state a method of calculating the value of a slot (c.f., ScalarIntervalSlot) for a given argument through subtraction. (slotCalculationFormula_Subtraction SLOT MINUEND-SLOT SUBTRAHEND-SLOT) means that for any valid arg1 for SLOT ARG, the value of VALUE in (SLOT ARG VALUE) can be arrived at by subtracting SUBTRAHEND-SLOT-VALUE in (SUBTRAHEND-SLOT ARG SUBTRAHEND) from MINUEND in (MINUEND-SLOT ARG MINUEND).
label: Slot Calculation Formula Subtraction
slotCalculationFormula-Subtraction

comment: (agentStaysViableInSubstanceFor_BCW AGENTTYPE SUBSTANCETYPE DURATION) means that, other things being equal, if an instance of the BiochemicallyHarmfulSubstance type AGENTTYPE remains in an instance of SUBSTANCETYPE for a time interval with duration DURATION, it will retain its capacity to harm living organisms throughout that interval.
label: Agent Stays Viable In Substance For BCW
agentStaysViableInSubstanceFor-BCW

comment: (tenureInRank RANK MMO AGENT DURATION) means that, in the context of the assertion, AGENT holds the rank RANK in MMO, and has held that RANK for DURATION. More specifically, if it holdsIn time interval TEMP that (tenureInUnitPosition POSITION MMO AGENT) and INT is any time interval of duration DURATION that is temporallyFinishedBy TEMP, then (RANK MMO AGENT) holdsIn INT.
label: tenure in rank
tenureInRank

comment: enables_RemovesIncapacitatingFactors expresses the notion that an agent is 'enabled' by an event in the following sense: the event removes all factors that are 'incapacitating', i.e., that would render the agent certainly incapable of performing the action in question. More accurately, (enables_RemovesIncapacitatingFactors SIT AGENT ACT_TYPE) is true iff, in the given circumstances, SIT obtains, there are no factors that would make AGENT certainly incapable of performing an instance of ACT_TYPE, and SIT is the cause of there being no such incapacitating factors. Hence enables_RemovesIncapacitatingFactors does not imply that the agent is capable of doing ACT_TYPE_TOKEN: it merely entails that the probability of the agent's succeeding at tokens of ACT_TYPE is non-zero. Example: snow plowing enables people to drive after a snowstorm in this sense -- since a heavy snow cover on roadways incapacitates driving.
label: Enables Removes Incapacitating Factors
enables-RemovesIncapacitatingFactors

comment: (interArgGenl1_2 REL INDEPENDENT-COL DEPENDENT-COL) means that, when an instance of INDEPENDENT-ARG-COL appears as the first argument to REL, the second argument is constrained to be a spec of DEPENDENT-ARG-COL.
label: Inter Arg Isa Genl 1 2

comment: (interArgGenl2_1 PRED INDEPENDENT-COL DEPENDENT-COL) means that for assertions using PRED, when the first argument to PRED is a subcollection of INDEPENDENT-COL, then the second argument to PRED must be a subcollection of DEPENDENT-COL.

(changeOfSymptomIntensity TIME COND ORG QCA) indicates whether ORG is experiencing more or less discomfort as a result of COND over the time period TIME. comment: (transportThroughAmountDuring PT1 COL PT2 THING AMOUNT) means that the ScalarInterval AMOUNT is a measure of the amount of instances of the Collection COL transported by the instance of PartiallyTangible PT1 through the instance of PartiallyTangible PT2 during the temporal extent of the TemporalThing THING. PT1 might, for example, be a Country or a Business. PT2 might, in the case of oil transport, for instance, be a GeographicalRegion or a Pipeline. THING will often be a calendar time period; but it may also be, for instance, a particular Event. In the case of oil transport, for example, AMOUNT might be a Volume (a number of barrels) indicating the total quantity of oil transported (by PT1 through PT2). Alternatively, AMOUNT might be a Rate, characterizing the average rate of transport of instances of COL by PT1 through PT2 during the temporal extent of THING. Oil transport, for example, might be expressed in terms of so many million barrels per day.

comment: (sksiSourceRegistered SKS) is true iff the SKSI removal module data structures for SKS have been 'registered'. Additionally, it must be true that a connection to the source can be established (See sksiSourceAccessible) and that the removal modules have been 'acivated' (see sksiSourceActivated). SKS is queryable (see sksiSourceQueryable) iff all three of these conditions are true.

That is, (RELN ARG1 ARG2 INDEPENDENT-ARG ARG4 ...) is semantically well-formed only if ARG4 is an instance of DEPENDENT-ARG-COL.

For an explanation of semantic well-formedness, see CycLExpression_Assertible and its direct specializations. See interArgEqualsIsa for a similar but more general predicate that is quintary, allowing the user to specify the positions of the independent and dependent arguments.

comment: (languageUnsupported LANGUAGE) means that LANGUAGE is not supported by the UIA -- i.e., the user cannot successively conduct a KE session through the UIA by entering LANGUAGE input.

(focalTermPositionForFormulaTemplate TEMPLATE POS TOPIC) means that the term in position POS is the focal term in TEMPLATE for TOPIC. The same template can have a different focal term for different topics. Within one topic, the position(s) denoted as focal term(s) will always refer to the same instance. For example, if (formulaForFormulaTemplate HasMembersTemplate (hasMembers (SomeExampleFn Organization) (SomeExampleFn Person))), then HasMembersTemplate might be an instance of a FormulaTemplateTopicType, PersonTopic, where (templateTypeForFocalTermType Person PersonTopic). In this case, (focalTermPositionForFormulaTemplate HasMembersTemplate (FormulaArgPositionFn 2) HasMembersTemplate). On the other hand, HasMembersTemplate might also be an instance of a FormulaTemplateTopicType, OrganizationTopic, where (templateTypeForFocalTermType Organization OrganizationTopic). In this case, (focalTermPositionForFormulaTemplate HasMembersTemplate (FormulaArgPositionFn 1) OrganizationTopic).

comment: The predicate helpfulActions is used to indicate that an agent engaged in a particular effort would (normally) increase the chances of success in that effort by taking a certain role in events of a certain kind. (helpfulActions ENDEAVOR SIT-TYPE ROLE DEGREE) means that the PurposefulAction ENDEAVOR would (normally) be helped along if its agent participated as described by ROLE in a situation of the type SIT-TYPE. DEGREE is an instance of GenericValuePredicate used to suggest how helpful such an occurrence would be for succeeding in ENDEAVOR. For example, for an agent trying to win in a football or soccer game, performing instances of InterceptingAPass contributes to a highToVeryHighAmountOf success in that game.
label: Helpful Actions

comment:
This predicate is a TemporallyQualifiableRelation that can be used to assert that an agent is fully able to carry out a certain role in a certain type of situation. (capableOf AGENT SITTYPE ROLE) means that AGENT is able to perform ROLE in Situations of the type SITTYPE. This entails that AGENT is qualified in all the relevant ways to fill that ROLE; i.e. AGENT is physicallyCapableOf playing that ROLE in instances of SITTYPE -- and, given that AGENT is the appropriate sort of agent -- is also anatomicallyCapableOf, fiscallyCapableOf, legallyCapableOf, and skillCapableOf playing that ROLE in instances of SITTYPE.

Contrast this predicate with the more general behaviorCapable: (behaviorCapable OBJ SITTYPE ROLE) does not imply that OBJ can unquestionably play ROLE in instances of SITTYPE since extrinsic factors may prevent it from doing so; for example, (behaviorCapable RonaldReagan Reading performedBy) may be true at a time when (capableOf RonaldReagan Reading performedBy) is not (e.g. at a time when Reagan is literate but blindfolded).
label: capability
capableOf

comment: (vulnerableTo THREAT-OBJ OBJECT HARM-TYPE) means that THREAT-OBJ poses harm of type HARM-TYPE to OBJECT when the two are appropriately situated. In other words, when THREAT-OBJ can affect OBJECT, it is likely that OBJECT will be damaged in some way. However, OBJECT's vulnerability persists even if it never happens to be affected by THREAT-OBJ. The point of stating blanket object-object vulnerabilities is to facilitate the representation of vulnerabilities that transcend particular situations. However, reference to a situation is required to draw specific conclusions about increased likelihood of damage, for it is not until the objects are related in a designated situation that we can draw significant inferences about fluctuating likelihoods.
label: Vulnerable To
vulnerableTo

Note that TIME-PERIOD refers to the date or time period during which the stocks were bought, not necessarily the period during which they gained or lost value.

comment:
An ExistentialQuantifier (q.v.) and a specialized (albeit higher arity) version of thereExists (q.v.). Compared to the latter, standard existential quantifier, thereExistAtLeast has an extra argument-place for specifying how many things (at the most) satisfy a given condition (specified by an #$ELSentence-Assertible, in which the also-specified #$ELVariable will typically occur free). A closed sentence of the form (thereExistAtMost NUM VAR SENT) means that there are at most NUM distinct things that satisfy SENT, i.e. that render SENT true when taken as the value of VAR. For example, the sentence 

  (thereExistAtMost 7 ?X (isa ?X Sea))

means that there are at most seven seas.

In the degenerate case where VAR does not appear free in SENT, then (thereExistAtMost NUM VAR SENT) is equivalent to SENT.

See also thereExistAtLeast, thereExistExactly.
label: There Exist At Most
thereExistAtMost

comment:
A ternary predicate that relates a given Spheroid to its "poles". (polesOfSpheroid POINT1 POINT2 SPHEROID) holds if and only if POINT1 and POINT2 are the antipodal $#Points at which SPHEROID intersects one of its axes (see axisOfSurfaceOfRevolution).

Note that if SPHEROID is an OblateSpheroid or a ProlateSpheroid it has exactly one axisOfSurfaceOfRevolution and thus exactly one pair of poles. If SPHEROID is a perfect Sphere, on the other hand, any Line_Straight that passes through its center (see centroidOfObject) is an axisOfSurfaceOfRevolution; thus it will have an infinite number of pairs of poles.
